research/history/round_summaries/round_0047.json:20:    "summary": "Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `64` to `32` to test whether the recipe improvement extends one more step down the allowed support ladder. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=32` control (`0.249427`), then `gated` has earned a meaningful lower-cost foothold; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above the control, treat the current `gated` advantage as largely confined to `K>=64`.",
