research/history/logs/agent_action_0036.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `gated` family may only be competitive at the largest support, so stepping `K` down from `128` to `96` while holding `EF=12`, `optimizer=signum`, and `lr=1.6e-3` tests one question only: does `gated` remain competitive on the adjacent frontier point, or is its apparent edge confined to `K=128`?","summary":"Round 35 answered the preprocess probe: Hadamard did not improve the anchored `gated` recipe, leaving no meaningful recipe knobs unexplored in the prescribed order. The next single-variable move is therefore `K`. Use the plain `gated` anchor and drop only `K` to `96`. This is the highest-value neighboring check because there is already a strong `topk` control at `K=96` (`0.171856`), so the run directly tells us whether `gated` has broader family viability or whether it should be treated as a narrow `K=128` specialization. Read the curve shape as well as the endpoint: if `gated@96` is smooth and beats or matches the `topk@96` control comfortably, keep the family alive across K; if it is clearly worse or unstable, treat `gated` as exhausted outside the single `K=128` point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the same family, preserves EF at 12, changes exactly one primary variable (`K`), and only moves K after the LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess probes failed to improve the anchored recipe. Choosing `K=96` minimizes extrapolation because it is adjacent to the current gated anchor and has a matched topk frontier point for direct comparison.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 36 begins the first K probe for gated after recipe tuning was exhausted: gated, K=96, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3.","Compare gated@96 against the existing topk@96 control and judge curve shape, not just terminal FVU; this determines whether gated generalizes beyond the isolated K=128 win."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated@96` is competitive with or better than `topk@96`, gated deserves at least one more K-mapping round within the allowed grid.","If `gated@96` clearly trails `topk@96`, stop spending mainline rounds on gated except as the recorded K=128 incumbent."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0073.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 71 showed that `two_stage_residual` can benefit modestly from a higher `signum` learning rate, but Round 72 was policy-rejected because it tried to combine the optimizer test with that LR shift in a single `param_only` move. The next single mainline question remains the optimizer question, and it must be isolated cleanly from the archived reference recipe: with `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed, does switching `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam` produce a healthier curve or competitive final FVU, or does this family still clearly prefer `signum`?",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0073.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the `two_stage_residual` mainline and answer the optimizer question without coupling it to the recent LR finding. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed at the current reference recipe, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge this run by full curve shape against the signum reference, not just the endpoint: if `adam` is competitive and smooth, it earns one LR callback next; if it is clearly worse, keep `signum` and move on to the next recipe axis.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0073.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0073.json:101:    "description": "Stay on the `two_stage_residual` mainline and answer the optimizer question without coupling it to the recent LR finding. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed at the current reference recipe, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge this run by full curve shape against the signum reference, not just the endpoint: if `adam` is competitive and smooth, it earns one LR callback next; if it is clearly worse, keep `signum` and move on to the next recipe axis.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0003.stdout.log:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 2 的 6e-4 明显劣于 8e-4，说明当前 topk/signum 主线更像是欠步长而不是过冲；本轮只把学习率上调到 1e-3，检验更积极的步长是否能在相同 family/optimizer/K 下带来更快且仍稳定的收敛，并刷新 K=128 的 FVU。","summary":"继续围绕 topk 主线推进，不开新 family，不换优化器，不动 K。本轮唯一主变量仍是 LR：从参考配方 8e-4 上调到 1e-3，回答“signum+topk 在当前设置下是否更需要稍大的学习率”这个单一问题。","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"这轮保持单变量且遵循主线顺序，先把 LR 维度补全到高于 baseline 的一侧，再决定是否切 optimizer。风险是 1e-3 可能带来震荡，但这正是本轮要验证的核心问题；若曲线恶化，后续就有充分理由结束 signum 的 LR 扫描并转向 optimizer 对比。","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 3 继续只调 LR，补完 signum 在 baseline 以上一侧的步长测试。","r2 的 6e-4 比 baseline 更差，初步说明问题不像是 LR 过大，更可能是步长偏小导致收敛不足。","本轮重点看曲线是否出现更快下降且仍稳定；若 1e-3 出现明显震荡或最终更差，就可结束 signum 的主线 LR 扫描并转向 optimizer 比较。"],"next_hypotheses":["如果 1e-3 优于 8e-4，下一轮继续只调 LR，在 8e-4 到 1e-3 之间或略高处做细化。","如果 1e-3 与 8e-4 接近但更不稳，下一轮可结束 signum 的 LR 扫描，按顺序只改 optimizer。","如果 1e-3 明显更差且有震荡，说明 signum 的合适 LR 区间已基本摸清，下一轮应切到 optimizer 维度。"],"primary_variable":"lr"}
