research/history/logs/agent_round_0003.stdout.log:49:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 2 的 6e-4 明显劣于 8e-4，说明当前 topk/signum 主线更像是欠步长而不是过冲；本轮只把学习率上调到 1e-3，检验更积极的步长是否能在相同 family/optimizer/K 下带来更快且仍稳定的收敛，并刷新 K=128 的 FVU。","summary":"继续围绕 topk 主线推进，不开新 family，不换优化器，不动 K。本轮唯一主变量仍是 LR：从参考配方 8e-4 上调到 1e-3，回答“signum+topk 在当前设置下是否更需要稍大的学习率”这个单一问题。","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"这轮保持单变量且遵循主线顺序，先把 LR 维度补全到高于 baseline 的一侧，再决定是否切 optimizer。风险是 1e-3 可能带来震荡，但这正是本轮要验证的核心问题；若曲线恶化，后续就有充分理由结束 signum 的 LR 扫描并转向 optimizer 对比。","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 3 继续只调 LR，补完 signum 在 baseline 以上一侧的步长测试。","r2 的 6e-4 比 baseline 更差，初步说明问题不像是 LR 过大，更可能是步长偏小导致收敛不足。","本轮重点看曲线是否出现更快下降且仍稳定；若 1e-3 出现明显震荡或最终更差，就可结束 signum 的主线 LR 扫描并转向 optimizer 比较。"],"next_hypotheses":["如果 1e-3 优于 8e-4，下一轮继续只调 LR，在 8e-4 到 1e-3 之间或略高处做细化。","如果 1e-3 与 8e-4 接近但更不稳，下一轮可结束 signum 的 LR 扫描，按顺序只改 optimizer。","如果 1e-3 明显更差且有震荡，说明 signum 的合适 LR 区间已基本摸清，下一轮应切到 optimizer 维度。"],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:20:    "summary": "Adopt the reproduced Hadamard recipe as the current `gated` reference and begin K mapping under that stronger setting. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `K` from `128` to `96`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory as well as the endpoint: if the improved recipe yields a smooth curve and clearly beats the old `gated@96` control (`0.168960`), then the preprocess gain transfers to a lower-cost point and the family deserves at least one more K step; if it falls back toward the earlier K96 result or loses its curve advantage, keep the improved recipe mainly as a K128 anchor.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:104:    "description": "Adopt the reproduced Hadamard recipe as the current `gated` reference and begin K mapping under that stronger setting. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `K` from `128` to `96`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory as well as the endpoint: if the improved recipe yields a smooth curve and clearly beats the old `gated@96` control (`0.168960`), then the preprocess gain transfers to a lower-cost point and the family deserves at least one more K step; if it falls back toward the earlier K96 result or loses its curve advantage, keep the improved recipe mainly as a K128 anchor.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0049.json:20:    "summary": "Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `24` to `16` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=16` control (`0.308437`), then `gated` has established a meaningful foothold in the low-K regime; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=24` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0049.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0049.json:104:    "description": "Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `24` to `16` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=16` control (`0.308437`), then `gated` has established a meaningful foothold in the low-K regime; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=24` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0013.stdout.log:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `signum` learning-rate sweep has now mapped a narrow optimum region around `1.7e-3` to `1.75e-3`, with no clear additional gain from pushing LR higher. This round changes only the loss-shaping axis by lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` from the current implicit baseline `0.03125` to `0.015625` while keeping `topk/signum/K128/EF12/LR=1.7e-3` fixed, to test whether a weaker auxiliary dead-feature pressure improves late-stage reconstruction once the main LR regime is already near its peak.","summary":"Stay on the `topk` mainline and move to the next recipe axis after LR refinement: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=1.7e-3` fixed, and reduce `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.015625` to answer whether lighter auxiliary regularization yields a better training curve and lower final FVU.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the active family unchanged and modifies only one non-core recipe variable, which fits the single-variable rule and avoids the optimizer-callback policy trap encountered earlier. The risk is that lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` may weaken dead-feature management and hurt utilization, but at this stage the more important question is whether the current LR-tuned regime is now over-regularized in reconstruction terms.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.7e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.015625"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The signum LR sweep suggests the practical optimum is near `1.7e-3`; pushing to `1.75e-3` did not yield a meaningful additional gain.","With LR mostly mapped, the next clean single-variable question is whether current loss shaping is slightly over-constraining reconstruction.","Judge this round by full curve shape plus terminal FVU: if lower `AUXK_ALPHA` improves late descent without obvious instability, the mainline recipe should shift on the loss axis rather than continuing micro-LR sweeps."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.015625` improves FVU and keeps the curve smooth, continue tuning aux loss strength within the same topk recipe.","If the lower aux weight hurts stability or feature health without improving reconstruction, revert to `0.03125` and treat LR-tuned signum as the current clean anchor.","If the effect is neutral, the topk mainline may be recipe-saturated at K=128 and the next useful step will be a K move once policy order permits."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
