research/history/round_summaries/round_0012.json:78:    "description": "Continue the topk mainline with one more narrow signum LR refinement: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `K=128`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and raise `LR` from `1.7e-3` to `1.75e-3` to answer whether the best stable point sits between the successful `1.7e-3` run and the degraded `1.8e-3` run.",
research/history/logs/agent_action_0073.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 71 showed that `two_stage_residual` can benefit modestly from a higher `signum` learning rate, but Round 72 was policy-rejected because it tried to combine the optimizer test with that LR shift in a single `param_only` move. The next single mainline question remains the optimizer question, and it must be isolated cleanly from the archived reference recipe: with `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed, does switching `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam` produce a healthier curve or competitive final FVU, or does this family still clearly prefer `signum`?","summary":"Stay on the `two_stage_residual` mainline and answer the optimizer question without coupling it to the recent LR finding. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed at the current reference recipe, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge this run by full curve shape against the signum reference, not just the endpoint: if `adam` is competitive and smooth, it earns one LR callback next; if it is clearly worse, keep `signum` and move on to the next recipe axis.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"mainline_improvement","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active mainline family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, uses an allowed `K`, and changes exactly one primary variable: `optimizer`. It directly fixes the Round 72 policy failure by reverting to the current mainline reference recipe instead of carrying forward the `LR=2.4e-3` adjustment into the optimizer test. The tradeoff is that this tests `adam` against the conservative anchor rather than the best observed signum LR, but that is the only policy-clean way to isolate the optimizer branch this round.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 72 was rejected on policy grounds because it coupled the optimizer change with the earlier LR adjustment; the rejection does not answer the optimizer-quality question itself.","Round 73 should isolate the optimizer axis cleanly by testing `adam` on the current `two_stage_residual` reference recipe at `K=128`, `EF=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, judging the whole curve rather than endpoint alone."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adam` is competitive with or better than the `signum` reference, give `adam` exactly one LR callback next within `two_stage_residual`.","If `adam` is clearly worse or noisier, keep `signum` as the settled optimizer and move to the loss or preprocess question next.","If `adam` is mixed, do not change K yet; use at most one optimizer-local LR probe only if the curve is plausibly salvageable."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0085.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` clearly weaker than the current `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, the next and only justified matched architecture probe is `lowrank_residual_vq`. It preserves the same low-rank coarse-trunk intuition and static-library export contract while swapping staged residual selection for a harder discrete coarse assignment. If that discrete variant cannot materially challenge the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor under the exact same `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=2.0e-3` recipe, then hard residual-VQ is not worth continuing in the current LUTurbo-aligned regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching only `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_residual_vq` while keeping the mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the baseline loss/runtime settings unchanged. Judge the probe by the full curve, not just endpoint FVU: if `lowrank_residual_vq` stays smooth and materially pressures the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, it remains worth keeping in reserve; if it is clearly weaker or less stable, close the family-worthiness question and return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual_vq","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 85 matched-probe rule: one probe only, one main variable only, and `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` remain fixed. I chose `lowrank_residual_vq` because it is a genuinely different but still LUTurbo-compatible decomposition pattern with stronger prior signal than simpler selector-only families. The main risk is that hard assignment raises brittleness and may underperform on curve smoothness even if early descent looks acceptable, which is why the full trajectory matters more than the final scalar alone.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual_vq"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 85 uses the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_residual_vq` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Interpret this as a family-worthiness screen only: because hard residual-VQ can add discrete-selection brittleness, only a clear and stable quality advantage justifies future follow-up."],"next_hypotheses":["Return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless, per the operator instruction.","If `lowrank_residual_vq` is clearly worse or less stable, keep focus on mainline loss/preprocess clarification rather than reopening more architecture variants immediately.","If it wins clearly, note it as a reserve candidate but still resume mainline recipe clarification next round before any further architecture churn."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
