research/history/logs/agent_round_0222.stdout.log:622:research/history/round_summaries/round_0051.json:20:    "summary": "Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `8` to `4` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the minimum allowed support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=4` control (`0.462789`), then `gated` has established a full low-K transfer across the entire allowed grid; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=8` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.",
