research/history/logs/agent_action_0083.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`adam` at the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor failed catastrophically, so the optimizer question is now cleanly resolved in favor of `signum`. The next single question should move to the loss axis rather than K or another architecture change: dropping `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0` tests whether the current mainline is being mildly over-regularized and whether a cleaner reconstruction objective improves the mid/late training curve under the settled `signum` recipe.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline and revert to the stable `signum` reference recipe, changing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0` while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed. Judge the run by the full curve against the current anchor, especially whether removing the auxiliary loss improves or smooths late descent; if it regresses or destabilizes, restore the default loss and only then consider preprocess.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, explicitly keeps `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and changes exactly one primary variable on top of the settled `signum` anchor. The main risk is that the auxiliary term may still be helping latent usage even if its endpoint effect is small, but after the optimizer branch crashed the cleanest remaining mainline question is loss regularization rather than opening preprocess or moving K prematurely.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 83 closes the optimizer branch for `lowrank_two_stage_residual`: `adam` at the matched K128/EF12/LR=2.0e-3 anchor was a catastrophic failure, so `signum` remains the settled mainline optimizer.","This round opens the loss-axis check by testing `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` on the exact stable `signum` reference recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` regresses or destabilizes, restore `0.03125` and test exactly one preprocess variable next, such as `USE_HADAMARD=1` if still unexplored on this family.","If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` improves clearly, run exactly one clean confirmation on that loss setting before moving to preprocess or K.","Do not move K until the K128 mainline has a settled optimizer and at least one resolved loss/preprocess verdict."],"primary_variable":"loss"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0066.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 65 established `two_stage_residual` as the new mainline by materially beating the previous `gated` K128 control under the matched `signum`/`2.0e-3` recipe, so the highest-value next step is to convert that one-off probe into a clean mainline baseline before touching learning rate or optimizer. This round answers one question only: does the same `two_stage_residual` K128 EF12 `signum` `2.0e-3` recipe reproduce a similarly strong curve as a stable baseline worth tuning from, or was Round 65 an overoptimistic single run.","summary":"Run a clean baseline repeat for the new `two_stage_residual` mainline at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, changing no recipe variable beyond promoting the family into baseline confirmation.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"confirm_baseline","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"baseline","self_review":"This follows the mainline progression rule by staying within the same family and using the recommended next step of establishing a clean baseline before any LR or optimizer change. The round changes no substantive training variable, so the result will be easy to attribute and will tell us whether the promising staged-residual curve is robust enough to tune further.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 66 promotes `two_stage_residual` from matched probe winner to mainline candidate by running a clean baseline repeat before any recipe tuning.","Judge this round primarily by reproducibility of the training curve shape and final FVU relative to Round 65, not just by whether the endpoint is slightly above or below 0.1278.","If the baseline reproduces cleanly, the next mainline question should be a single learning-rate adjustment inside `two_stage_residual`; if it fails to reproduce, investigate stability before changing optimizer or K."],"next_hypotheses":["If the clean baseline reproduces the strong Round 65 curve, test one learning-rate adjustment within `two_stage_residual` next.","If the clean baseline is materially worse or less stable, rerun only if needed to separate variance from recipe instability before changing optimizer.","If the curve is strong early but plateaus oddly, use the next round for a single LR change rather than touching K or architecture."],"primary_variable":"baseline_confirmation"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0162.stdout.log:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 probe family 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 是单个静态字典库上的固定向量，alpha_i 是单样本 top-k 选出的稀疏系数，因此最终表示是单静态向量库上的有限加权和，可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为直接兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 0.5x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束，并显著低于当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 的约 1.25x。本轮严格保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 与主要 recipe 不变，只将 architecture 从 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 改为 topk，回答唯一问题：在当前低 EF 可部署 regime 下，这条最朴素、最低复杂度的单库稀疏路线是否仍值得继续，还是其表示能力会明显落后于带 trunk、soft-codebook 和 staged refinement 的主线结构。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 topk 明显落后于当前主线，则说明最简单单库稀疏路线在当前 regime 下不值得继续，下一轮回到主线。","若 topk 与当前主线差距小于预期且运行代价更优，则记录其为更简单的低成本备选，但下一轮仍按要求回到主线。","若 topk 意外优于当前主线，则说明当前主线 family 的系统级收益需要重新审视，但本轮仅做架构价值判断，不连续展开新 family。"],"notes_to_memory":["topk 满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性为直接兼容。","本轮严格是 matched architecture probe：EF、K、optimizer、LR 与主要 recipe 全部固定，只改 architecture。","r159-r161 已依次检验去掉 second stage、去掉 soft-codebook coarse branch、以及更低成本 factorized 单库路线的价值；本轮补充最朴素直接兼容单库 baseline，完成当前低 EF regime 下的主干结构对照。","评估时必须同时检查 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，避免把质量差异与吞吐波动混淆。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这轮遵守架构探针规则，只改一个主变量 architecture，并保持主线的 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变。选择 topk 是因为它是当前尚未在这一严格 matched 配方下补齐的最简单直接兼容基线，能用一次最低复杂度对照回答“主线结构是否真的必要”这个剩余问题。","summary":"插入一个严格匹配的架构探针：将当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 替换为 topk，其余 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 全部保持不变，用一轮干净对照判断这种最简单的直接兼容单库架构是否值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
