research/history/logs/agent_round_0020.stdout.log:74:research/history/results.tsv:20:r19_1774530135	1774530135	ok	keep	0.380331814289093	8	topk	12				/root/sparsify-ascend/checkpoints/research_agent/round_0019/round0019_standard_1774529775_dp2_bs1_ga8_ef12_k8_20260326_205621	8ecdaf1e971dec7f81eac3ef8e6c9f4a85282331			Continue the active topk low-K boundary search: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `K` from `16` to `8` to test whether the practical LUTurbo cost-quality frontier extends below `K=16`.	This stays on the active `topk` family, changes exactly one primary variable (`k`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule and allowed-K set, and follows directly from the observed `K=16` curve shape. The main risk is that `K=8` may push the recipe past the useful regime, but `K=16` still improved through the end rather than hard-plateauing, so the next clean question is whether the true boundary sits at `K=8` or between `8` and `16`.	/root/sparsify-ascend/research/history/logs/round0019_standard_1774529775.log
research/history/logs/agent_round_0020.stdout.log:131:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 19 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=8` suffered a large quality drop and much heavier dead-feature pressure, with the late curve nearly flattening but not fully collapsing. This round changes only `K`, moving from `8` to `4`, to answer the single remaining boundary question: whether the current export-compatible topk recipe has any usable signal left at the absolute minimum allowed K, or whether `K=8` already marks the effective floor.","summary":"Finish the current low-K boundary sweep on the active topk mainline: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `K` from `8` to `4` to locate the hard lower bound of the present topk/signum regime.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `topk` family, changes exactly one primary variable (`k`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule and allowed-K set, and closes the current K-only frontier scan cleanly. The main risk is that `K=4` may be clearly past the useful regime, but `command=\"stop\"` is disallowed and this is the most informative remaining single-variable question because it determines whether `K=8` is merely weak or already beyond the practical floor.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"4"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 19 (`K=8`) reached `FVU=0.380331814289093`, a large degradation from `K=16`, while late-phase improvement became very small.","At `K=8`, late `dead_pct` rose to about `0.39` and `auxk` stayed high at about `0.37`, indicating strong capacity stress and likely growing online compensation burden.","Even though the late curve nearly flattened at `K=8`, it did not fully collapse, so running `K=4` is the cleanest way to locate the hard lower boundary of the current topk/signum/EF12 recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=4` collapses or adds very little usable signal, treat `K=8` or `K=16` as the practical floor and return to non-K recipe tuning on the same family.","If `K=4` is surprisingly stable, compare it against `K=8` strictly as a deployment tradeoff point rather than against the K128 anchor.","After the hard lower bound is mapped, the next mainline question should move back to recipe tuning within the surviving low-K regime rather than continuing K-only descent."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0050.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 49 answered the `K=16` question positively: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) continued to transfer downward and now owns the `K=16` frontier with a materially better endpoint than the prior control. The next single question is where this benefit finally fails under extreme support pressure: if we keep the same improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `8`, does `gated` still preserve enough quality to remain the best ultra-low-cost point, or does the family advantage break once support becomes very tight?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `16` to `8` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=8` control (`0.380332`), then `gated` has established a meaningful foothold in the ultra-low-K regime; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=16` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the current mainline logic because the baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been resolved on this recipe, and the recent K sweep has now shown successful transfer at `K=96`, `K=64`, `K=32`, `K=24`, and `K=16`. The main risk is that `K=8` may fall outside the regime where the improved gating recipe remains effective, but that is exactly the highest-value remaining single-variable question for locating the LUTurbo cost-quality break point.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"8"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 49 established that the improved `gated` recipe transfers down to `K=16`: it beat the previous `K=16` control and now holds that frontier point.","Round 50 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether the same recipe still wins at `K=8`, where LUTurbo online cost drops further but support pressure tightens sharply."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@8` clearly beats the existing `K=8` control with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=4` under the same recipe to locate the final break point.","If `gated@8` fails to beat the control or shows clearly worse curve shape, stop the downward sweep and treat `K=16` as the lowest strong gated point under the current recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0081.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`LR=1.6e-3` slightly regressed from the stable `2.0e-3` anchor, so the signum LR question is still unresolved on the upward side. A symmetric probe at `LR=2.4e-3` is the cleanest next move: it tests whether the stronger `lowrank_two_stage_residual` backbone still benefits from a slightly larger step size via faster early/mid descent without destabilizing late training.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`, keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and the baseline aux/runtime settings fixed. Judge the run by the full trajectory versus the `2.0e-3` and `1.6e-3` runs, especially whether the higher LR preserves stability while improving early/mid descent and final FVU; if it overshoots or degrades late, close the signum LR branch and keep `2.0e-3` as the operative mainline LR.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the required mainline sequence: same family, same K, same optimizer, EF explicitly fixed to 12, and only one primary variable changes. The risk is that `2.4e-3` may overshoot on a backbone that already looked well-tuned at `2.0e-3`, but that is exactly the remaining single-variable question before it is defensible to stop LR tuning and move to optimizer.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 81 completes the symmetric signum LR bracket for the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12 mainline by probing `LR=2.4e-3` after `1.6e-3` regressed slightly.","Interpretation should emphasize curve shape: if `2.4e-3` improves early speed but harms late stability or finish, keep `2.0e-3` as the mainline LR and open the optimizer branch next."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=2.4e-3` also regresses or destabilizes, lock `signum` + `LR=2.0e-3` as the mainline recipe and switch only `OPTIMIZER` next.","If `LR=2.4e-3` wins clearly, run exactly one clean confirmation on that higher-LR anchor before trying optimizer.","Do not touch loss, preprocess, or K until the signum LR verdict is closed for `lowrank_two_stage_residual` at K128."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0231.stdout.log:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"group_topk"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"group_topk","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"候选 family: group_topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；group_topk 只改变单样本在线侧的支持形成方式，先在每个静态分组内选 winner，再做全局保留，不改变 decoder 端的单库有限加权和，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路，兼容性判断为直接兼容。相对 r215 只改一个 env 参数 `ARCHITECTURE=group_topk`，保持 `K=192`、`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`、`signum`、`LR=0.003` 及其余配置不变，测试在约 0.44x 总成本处，用组内竞争带来的更均匀支持分配能否优于当前同成本 `topk@K192` 的 FVU=0.16352，或者至少给出比 plain topk 更有价值的系统信号。选择这个 probe 的原因是：r230 已经说明“极短 factorized scorer”虽然很便宜但质量塌陷，因此下一步更值得测试的是不缩短 decoder 契约、也不抬高成本、只改支持分配规则的同成本单库架构。默认 `group_topk_size=4` 时，EF=1 对应 768 latents 可分成 192 组，恰好允许 `K=192` 的有效运行，成本与 topk 同阶且满足 LUTurbo 总成本硬约束。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `group_topk@K192` 在同成本下优于 `topk@K192`，且 tokens_per_sec、duration_sec 没有明显恶化，则可相对本轮继续单变量切到 `K=128` 或 `K=224` 的同 family 映射，判断这条组竞争支线是否值得进入 `<0.5x` 主前沿。","如果 `group_topk` 质量与 topk 接近但运行更差，则将其记为负面系统信号，说明单库组竞争没有带来有效收益，不再继续占用主线轮次。","如果 `group_topk` 明显差于 `topk@K192`，则关闭这条同成本 grouped selector 支线，转向其他低成本 family，而不是继续在单库支持规则上做更多小改。"],"notes_to_memory":["r230 已证明 factorized_topk 的极低 encoder 成本并没有转化为可用质量：虽然 total_cost 只有约 0.30x，但 FVU=0.3909，远差于同区间 topk。","当前更高价值的问题不是继续压 factorized scorer 的 hidden，而是在不改变单库导出契约、也不增加成本的前提下，测试另一种支持分配机制能否改善 `<0.5x` 区域的质量。","`group_topk` 在 EF=1、K=192、group_topk_size=4 下是有效配置；评估时必须同步看 FVU、tokens_per_sec、duration_sec、final_total_tokens，避免把极小质量变化误判成正收益。"],"reference_round":215,"self_review":"这轮严格遵守单变量原则：相对有效参考轮 r215 只改 `ARCHITECTURE`，不联动 K、EF、optimizer、LR 或其他参数。选择 `group_topk` 而不是继续沿 jumprelu 或 factorized_topk 做邻域微调，是因为前者在当前低开销区间尚未得到干净的低 EF probe，同时能以与 `topk@K192` 几乎相同的成本，直接回答“更结构化的支持分配是否值得”这个独立问题。主要风险是 grouped 约束可能过强导致质量下滑，但这正是本轮需要以最小变量改动确认的内容。","summary":"相对 r215 的 `topk@EF1,K192` 做一次严格 param_only architecture probe，仅切到 `group_topk`。目标是在保持约 0.44x 总成本不变的前提下，测试组内竞争式支持分配能否在 `<0.5x` 区域形成比 plain topk 更好的 cost-FVU 权衡。","touched_files":[]}
