research/history/logs/agent_round_0231.stdout.log:717:research/history/logs/agent_action_0229.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"K","value":"224"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"frontier_mapping","hypothesis":"候选 family: jumprelu。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；JumpReLU 只改变单样本在线侧的阈值化支持形成与系数计算，不改变 decoder 端的单库有限加权和，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路，兼容性判断为直接兼容。相对 r228 只改一个 env 参数 `K=224`，保持 `ARCHITECTURE=jumprelu`、`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`、`JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH=0.05`、`JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD=0.02`、`signum`、`LR=0.003` 不变，测试在 r228 已经于更低部署成本点压过同区间 topk 的前提下，继续缩短查表链路后是否仍能保持明显质量优势，从而把 jumprelu 前沿从约 0.48x 进一步扩展到约 0.47x。该改动只降低 deployment 查表成本，不增加 encoder 成本，预计 total_cost 约从 0.48x 降到 0.47x，仍满足 LUTurbo 总成本硬约束。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `jumprelu@K224` 仍明显优于当前同区间 `topk@K224` 的 FVU=0.15281，且训练时长未恶化，则继续相对本轮单变量下探到 `K=192`，补齐更低部署成本侧的 Pareto 形状。","如果 `K=224` 的 FVU 仅小幅变差但仍优于 topk，且运行代价接近或优于 r228，则可将 jumprelu 视为 `<0.5x` 区域沿 K 轴可稳定外推的直兼容主线。","如果 `K=224` 的 FVU 退化到接近或差于同区间 topk，则停止 jumprelu 的 K 下探线，转向新的低成本 family，而不是继续消耗在这条高 K 依赖支线上。"],"notes_to_memory":["r228 已证明 `jumprelu@K240` 在更低部署成本点仍优于同区间 topk：FVU=0.14756 对比 `topk@K240` 的 0.14833，同时 duration=391s，没有出现比近期 jumprelu 轮更差的系统代价。","当前最高信息量问题是 jumprelu 的质量优势能否继续沿 K 轴向更低 deployment 成本扩展，而不是继续在 `K=240` 单点上做 recipe 微调。","评估本轮时必须同步比较 FVU、tokens_per_sec、duration_sec、final_total_tokens；若质量收益极小但训练明显更慢，应视为负面信号。"],"reference_round":228,"self_review":"这轮严格遵守单变量原则：相对 r228 只改 `K`，不联动 architecture、EF、LR、bandwidth、init_threshold 或其他 recipe。选择继续下探到 `K=224`，是因为 r228 已经满足开放假设的前半条件：在更低 deployment 成本处仍压过同区间 topk，且总时长没有恶化；此时继续沿同一成本轴补点，比再次切到高不确定性新 family 更能直接服务于 `<0.5x` Pareto 前沿补全。主要风险是 jumprelu 的改进对极高 K 过于敏感，但这正是本轮要隔离回答的单一问题。","summary":"相对 r228 的 `jumprelu@EF1,K240,JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH=0.05,JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD=0.02` 做一次严格 param_only frontier probe，仅将 `K` 下调到 `224`。目标是在进一步降低总成本的同时，验证 jumprelu 能否继续压过当前 `topk@0.47x` 邻近点，从而把 `<0.5x` 区域更低 deployment 成本侧的 Pareto 前沿补完整。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0231.stdout.log:727:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"group_topk"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"group_topk","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"候选 family: group_topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；group_topk 只改变单样本在线侧的支持形成方式，先在每个静态分组内选 winner，再做全局保留，不改变 decoder 端的单库有限加权和，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路，兼容性判断为直接兼容。相对 r215 只改一个 env 参数 `ARCHITECTURE=group_topk`，保持 `K=192`、`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`、`signum`、`LR=0.003` 及其余配置不变，测试在约 0.44x 总成本处，用组内竞争带来的更均匀支持分配能否优于当前同成本 `topk@K192` 的 FVU=0.16352，或者至少给出比 plain topk 更有价值的系统信号。选择这个 probe 的原因是：r230 已经说明“极短 factorized scorer”虽然很便宜但质量塌陷，因此下一步更值得测试的是不缩短 decoder 契约、也不抬高成本、只改支持分配规则的同成本单库架构。默认 `group_topk_size=4` 时，EF=1 对应 768 latents 可分成 192 组，恰好允许 `K=192` 的有效运行，成本与 topk 同阶且满足 LUTurbo 总成本硬约束。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `group_topk@K192` 在同成本下优于 `topk@K192`，且 tokens_per_sec、duration_sec 没有明显恶化，则可相对本轮继续单变量切到 `K=128` 或 `K=224` 的同 family 映射，判断这条组竞争支线是否值得进入 `<0.5x` 主前沿。","如果 `group_topk` 质量与 topk 接近但运行更差，则将其记为负面系统信号，说明单库组竞争没有带来有效收益，不再继续占用主线轮次。","如果 `group_topk` 明显差于 `topk@K192`，则关闭这条同成本 grouped selector 支线，转向其他低成本 family，而不是继续在单库支持规则上做更多小改。"],"notes_to_memory":["r230 已证明 factorized_topk 的极低 encoder 成本并没有转化为可用质量：虽然 total_cost 只有约 0.30x，但 FVU=0.3909，远差于同区间 topk。","当前更高价值的问题不是继续压 factorized scorer 的 hidden，而是在不改变单库导出契约、也不增加成本的前提下，测试另一种支持分配机制能否改善 `<0.5x` 区域的质量。","`group_topk` 在 EF=1、K=192、group_topk_size=4 下是有效配置；评估时必须同步看 FVU、tokens_per_sec、duration_sec、final_total_tokens，避免把极小质量变化误判成正收益。"],"reference_round":215,"self_review":"这轮严格遵守单变量原则：相对有效参考轮 r215 只改 `ARCHITECTURE`，不联动 K、EF、optimizer、LR 或其他参数。选择 `group_topk` 而不是继续沿 jumprelu 或 factorized_topk 做邻域微调，是因为前者在当前低开销区间尚未得到干净的低 EF probe，同时能以与 `topk@K192` 几乎相同的成本，直接回答“更结构化的支持分配是否值得”这个独立问题。主要风险是 grouped 约束可能过强导致质量下滑，但这正是本轮需要以最小变量改动确认的内容。","summary":"相对 r215 的 `topk@EF1,K192` 做一次严格 param_only architecture probe，仅切到 `group_topk`。目标是在保持约 0.44x 总成本不变的前提下，测试组内竞争式支持分配能否在 `<0.5x` 区域形成比 plain topk 更好的 cost-FVU 权衡。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0110.stdout.log:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"Round 110 should answer exactly one mainline recipe question on `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`: whether optimizer choice helps on the controller-declared reference recipe. The family already has a clean baseline at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and although `LR=2.4e-3` looked promising, the last round was policy-rejected because optimizer and LR were effectively coupled. Holding the official reference recipe fixed and changing only `OPTIMIZER` to `adam` is the cleanest compliant test of whether this family has optimizer headroom before any optimizer-local LR callback.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `adam` is competitive with or better than matched `signum` at `LR=2.0e-3`, give `adam` exactly one LR callback next within `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`.","If `adam` is clearly worse or unstable on the matched reference recipe, keep `signum` as the optimizer and move to the next single-axis mainline recipe question before touching `K`.","Do not change loss, preprocess, or `K` until the optimizer branch is resolved cleanly on an accepted baseline."],"notes_to_memory":["Round 110 corrects Round 109's policy mistake by isolating the optimizer comparison on the controller's current mainline reference recipe for `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`.","Judge this run by the whole training curve versus the archived `signum` reference at `K=128`, `EF=12`, `LR=2.0e-3`, especially early stability and mid/late descent shape, not just final FVU.","Even if prior `signum` runs at `LR=2.4e-3` were slightly better, keep this round focused on the single accepted optimizer question before opening any optimizer-local LR callback."],"primary_variable":"optimizer","self_review":"This stays on the required family, keeps `K=128` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and changes only one primary axis: optimizer. It matches the round policy order and avoids repeating Round 109's mixed optimizer-plus-LR error. The tradeoff is that it tests `adam` against the official `LR=2.0e-3` anchor rather than the unofficial `2.4e-3` signum setting, but that is the cleaner and safer comparison under the current controller policy.","summary":"Run a single optimizer-isolation experiment on the current `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline reference recipe: keep `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`.","touched_files":[]}
