al FVU.","Even if prior `signum` runs at `LR=2.4e-3` were slightly better, keep this round focused on the single accepted optimizer question before opening any optimizer-local LR callback."],"primary_variable":"optimizer","self_review":"This stays on the required family, keeps `K=128` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and changes only one primary axis: optimizer. It matches the round policy order and avoids repeating Round 109's mixed optimizer-plus-LR error. The tradeoff is that it tests `adam` against the official `LR=2.0e-3` anchor rather than the unofficial `2.4e-3` signum setting, but that is the cleaner and safer comparison under the current controller policy.","summary":"Run a single optimizer-isolation experiment on the current `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline reference recipe: keep `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0049.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 48 answered the `K=24` question positively: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) continued to transfer downward and now owns the `K=24` frontier with a materially better endpoint than the prior control. The next single question is where this benefit finally breaks under stronger support pressure: if we keep the same improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `16`, does `gated` still preserve enough quality to remain the best low-cost point, or does the family advantage disappear once support becomes this tight?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `24` to `16` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=16` control (`0.308437`), then `gated` has established a meaningful foothold in the low-K regime; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=24` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the current mainline logic because the baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been resolved on this recipe, and the recent K sweep has now shown successful transfer at `K=96`, `K=64`, `K=32`, and `K=24`. The main risk is that `K=16` may fall outside the regime where the improved gating recipe remains effective, but that is exactly the highest-value remaining single-variable question for locating the LUTurbo cost-quality break point.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 48 established that the improved `gated` recipe transfers down to `K=24`: it beat the previous `K=24` control and now holds that frontier point.","Round 49 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether the same recipe still wins at `K=16`, where LUTurbo online cost drops further but support pressure tightens again."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@16` clearly beats the existing `K=16` control with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=8` under the same recipe to locate the next break point.","If `gated@16` fails to beat the control or shows clearly worse curve shape, stop the downward sweep and treat `K=24` as the lowest strong gated point under the current recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0093.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` was the first recent matched probe to land relatively close to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, so the next most informative architecture-only question is whether that coarse static codebook branch remains viable when the sparse residual selector is made cheaper. `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` preserves the same LUTurbo-compatible static-library decomposition as the soft-codebook probe, but replaces full global residual selection with group-local winner selection. If it stays reasonably close under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then this family may offer a better quality-versus-online-selection-cost tradeoff than the mainline; if it falls back to the weaker grouped-single-stage pattern, then the earlier soft-codebook result should be treated as requiring full global selection to matter.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the round policy by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. It is a stronger LUTurbo-aligned probe than opening a heavier two-stage soft-codebook branch, because grouped local competition directly targets lower online selection cost while retaining the promising coarse static codebook decomposition seen in Round 92. The risk is that the grouped selector may erase most of the quality gain that made `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` interesting, in which case this family should be deprioritized quickly.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 93 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for combining a coarse static codebook branch with cheaper group-local sparse selection; the key question is whether the Round 92 soft-codebook signal survives a more deployment-friendly selector.","Return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome; do not turn this into a multi-round soft-codebook branch sequence."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is clearly weaker than both `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` and the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, discard grouped soft-codebook variants and resume mainline tuning next round.","If `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` remains surprisingly close to the mainline, record it as a potentially lower-selection-cost branch but still return to `lowrank_two_stage_residual` next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0048.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 47 answered the `K=32` question positively: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) did not collapse when support was cut in half again, and it now owns the `K=32` frontier with a materially better endpoint than the old control. The next single question is where that transfer finally breaks for LUTurbo-relevant cost reduction: if we keep the same improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `24`, does `gated` still preserve enough quality to remain the best point at that lower online cost, or does the advantage disappear below `K=32`?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `32` to `24` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=24` control (`0.272262`), then `gated` has established a meaningful mid-low-K foothold; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=32` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the current mainline logic because the baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been resolved on this recipe, and the recent K sweep has now shown successful transfer at `K=96`, `K=64`, and `K=32`. The main risk is that `K=24` may fall outside the regime where the improved gating recipe remains effective, but that is exactly the highest-value remaining single-variable question for mapping the LUTurbo cost-quality boundary.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 47 established that the improved `gated` recipe transfers down to `K=32`: it beat the previous `K=32` control and now holds that frontier point.","Round 48 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether the same recipe still wins at `K=24`, where LUTurbo online cost drops further but support pressure tightens again."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@24` clearly beats the existing `K=24` control with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=16` under the same recipe to locate the next break point.","If `gated@24` fails to beat the control or shows clearly worse curve shape, stop the downward sweep and treat `K=32` as the lowest strong gated point under the current recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0097.stdout.log:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 95 and 96 established a clean, repeatable `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128 baseline at `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, so the next single mainline question is the first within-family learning-rate probe. Lowering `LR` to `1.6e-3` tests whether this asymmetric soft-codebook two-stage recipe is currently slightly underdamped and could trade a bit of early speed for better late-stage descent and a lower terminal FVU; the decision should come from the whole curve shape versus the archived baseline, not just the last point.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the prescribed sequence after a clean baseline repeat: stay on the same family, keep `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and change exactly one primary variable, `lr`. The main risk is that `1.6e-3` may simply slow a recipe that is already well tuned at `2.0e-3`, but that is the highest-value first LR-localization question before opening the optimizer branch.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 97 is the first LR probe for the confirmed `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline baseline at `K=128`, `EF=12`, and `signum`.","Judge this run by the full trajectory against the archived `LR=2.0e-3` baseline, especially whether the lower step size improves late descent or only slows the whole curve.","If `LR=1.6e-3` regresses or converges too slowly, the next LR probe should return upward rather than continuing downward."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=1.6e-3` improves endpoint or late-curve shape versus `2.0e-3`, archive it as the new mainline LR for `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`.","If `LR=1.6e-3` is clearly slower or worse, test only the symmetric upward probe at `LR=2.4e-3` next before opening the optimizer branch.","Do not change optimizer, loss, preprocess, or `K` until the signum LR bracket is localized."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
