research/history/logs/agent_round_0097.stdout.log:59:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 95 and 96 established a clean, repeatable `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128 baseline at `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, so the next single mainline question is the first within-family learning-rate probe. Lowering `LR` to `1.6e-3` tests whether this asymmetric soft-codebook two-stage recipe is currently slightly underdamped and could trade a bit of early speed for better late-stage descent and a lower terminal FVU; the decision should come from the whole curve shape versus the archived baseline, not just the last point.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the prescribed sequence after a clean baseline repeat: stay on the same family, keep `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and change exactly one primary variable, `lr`. The main risk is that `1.6e-3` may simply slow a recipe that is already well tuned at `2.0e-3`, but that is the highest-value first LR-localization question before opening the optimizer branch.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 97 is the first LR probe for the confirmed `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline baseline at `K=128`, `EF=12`, and `signum`.","Judge this run by the full trajectory against the archived `LR=2.0e-3` baseline, especially whether the lower step size improves late descent or only slows the whole curve.","If `LR=1.6e-3` regresses or converges too slowly, the next LR probe should return upward rather than continuing downward."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=1.6e-3` improves endpoint or late-curve shape versus `2.0e-3`, archive it as the new mainline LR for `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`.","If `LR=1.6e-3` is clearly slower or worse, test only the symmetric upward probe at `LR=2.4e-3` next before opening the optimizer branch.","Do not change optimizer, loss, preprocess, or `K` until the signum LR bracket is localized."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0090.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After the simpler low-rank single-stage selectors (`lowrank_residual`, `lowrank_gated_residual`, `lowrank_jumprelu_residual`, and `lowrank_grouped_residual`) all failed against the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, the most informative remaining matched architecture probe is `whitened_lowrank_residual`. It keeps the same low-rank trunk and single-stage static-library residual decode, but changes only the residual conditioning before support selection. This answers a clean question: was the mainline gain coming from the second residual stage itself, or can a better-conditioned single-stage selector recover enough quality to be worth any further attention. If `whitened_lowrank_residual` is still clearly weaker under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then the current evidence favors the two-stage residual mechanism rather than more single-stage low-rank variants.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `whitened_lowrank_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"whitened_lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This changes exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, and keeps the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. `whitened_lowrank_residual` is a coherent remaining probe because it preserves the low-rank single-stage export path while testing whether residual conditioning, rather than an extra residual pass, is the missing ingredient. The risk is that the added normalization path may still not close the gap and may be less attractive for LUTurbo runtime than the current mainline, so this should be judged strictly as a worth-continuing screen rather than a new direction to tune immediately.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"whitened_lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 90 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `whitened_lowrank_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness probe for conditioned single-stage low-rank residual selection; the core question is whether better residual conditioning can substitute for the second residual stage.","Return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome; do not treat this as license to open a new whitening branch sequence."],"next_hypotheses":["If `whitened_lowrank_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, discard it and resume mainline tuning on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` next round.","If `whitened_lowrank_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a single-stage comparison point but still return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0119.stdout.log:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk、soft codebook、两阶段 residual 都是静态向量库上的有限加权和，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；该 family 属于扩展兼容。当前 EF=2 已稳定满足 encoder 选择成本硬约束，`signum + LR=3.0e-3` 是已复现的低成本主线锚点；将 `AUXK_ALPHA` 从 0.03125 降到 0.015625 后未见明显退化，说明辅助稀疏损失在该低 EF regime 里可能已非必要。本轮只改一个主变量 `AUXK_ALPHA`，进一步降到 `0.0`，回答唯一问题：完全去掉 auxiliary K loss 是否能减少对主重构目标的约束干扰，在不增加训练代价的前提下进一步改善 FVU 或曲线形状。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` 改善终点或曲线形状，且 `tokens_per_sec`、总耗时、`final_total_tokens` 基本不变，则再做一次 clean baseline 复现确认。","如果 `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` 出现退化，则关闭 auxk 降低分支，恢复默认 `0.03125` 或保留已验证等价的较小值，不再继续在该轴上消耗轮次。","在 loss/preprocess 轴未得到清晰正信号前，不改 K，也不改 TRUNK_RANK / NUM_CODES / STAGE1_RATIO / FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM。"],"notes_to_memory":["兼容性判断：`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 为扩展兼容；导出形式不变，仍是 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + residual 字典库的有限加权和。","`adam` 分支已爆炸，当前主线仍应固定在 `signum + LR=3.0e-3`。","本轮严格单变量，只改 `AUXK_ALPHA`；该改动不影响 encoder 选择成本，也不应显著增加训练时长，评估时继续同时检查曲线形状、`tokens_per_sec`、总耗时与 `final_total_tokens`。"],"primary_variable":"auxk_alpha","self_review":"这仍符合当前主线顺序。EF、clean baseline、LR 和 optimizer 结论都已基本清楚，而上轮把 `AUXK_ALPHA` 减半后没有负面信号，因此现在最小且可归因的后续问题就是测试 auxiliary loss 是否可以彻底移除。相比切换到更重的 preprocess 改动，这个问题更干净、代价更低。","summary":"保持 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual / EF=2 / K=128 / signum / LR=3.0e-3` 主线不变，仅将 `AUXK_ALPHA` 进一步降到 `0.0`，测试低成本 regime 下是否可以完全去掉 auxiliary K loss 来改善重构质量。","touched_files":[]}
