research/history/logs/agent_round_0223.stdout.log:584:research/history/round_summaries/round_0026.json:20:    "summary": "Run a runtime-stabilization check on the exact active topk reference recipe: the same `gated` mainline and probe only the learning-rate axis. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, explicitly pin the reference aux/runtime knobs, and raise `LR` from `1.6e-3` to `2.0e-3`. Read the whole curve, not just terminal FVU: if the higher LR preserves stability while improving mid-to-late descent below the refreshed `0.149936` control, then the current anchor was slightly conservative; if it becomes noisier or finishes worse, keep `1.6e-3` as the gated LR anchor and stop the LR branch.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:3076:research/history/logs/agent_round_0040.stdout.log:84:research/history/results.tsv:40:r39_1774539654	1774539654	ok	keep	0.148156076669693	128	gated	12				/root/sparsify-ascend/checkpoints/research_agent/round_0039/round0039_standard_1774539084_dp2_bs1_ga8_ef12_k128_20260326_233130	583257da77822fd7781b4701d5d19f522c346304			Continue on the same `gated` mainline and probe only the learning-rate axis. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, explicitly pin the reference aux/runtime knobs, and raise `LR` from `1.6e-3` to `2.0e-3`. Read the whole curve, not just terminal FVU: if the higher LR preserves stability while improving mid-to-late descent below the refreshed `0.149936` control, then the current anchor was slightly conservative; if it becomes noisier or finishes worse, keep `1.6e-3` as the gated LR anchor and stop the LR branch.	This stays on the active family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `lr`. It also follows the prescribed order now that the clean baseline has been backfilled successfully. The main risk is that `2.0e-3` could overdrive training, but the evidence so far points the other way: `1.2e-3` was clearly slower/worse, and the refreshed `1.6e-3` baseline was still improving late.	/root/sparsify-ascend/research/history/logs/round0039_standard_1774539084.log
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:3077:research/history/logs/agent_round_0040.stdout.log:94:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 39 improved the `gated` K128 anchor from `0.149936` to `0.148156` and the whole curve was better from start to finish while still improving late, so the LR branch has not saturated yet. The next single question is whether this gain continues one more small step upward: does `LR=2.4e-3` preserve the healthy curve shape and improve further over the new `2.0e-3` anchor, or does it begin to overdrive the recipe?","summary":"Stay on the same `gated` mainline and continue the learning-rate sweep with one adjacent confirmation step. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, explicitly pin the reference aux/runtime knobs, and raise only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`. Judge this round by full trajectory shape, not just terminal FVU: if early and mid training remain as smooth as Round 39 and the late descent goes lower than `0.148156`, then the LR optimum is still above the current anchor; if the curve gets noisier, flatter, or regresses, stop the LR branch and lock `2.0e-3` as the mainline setting.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the search on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `lr`. It also follows the stated policy to do one more nearby LR confirmation after a clean improvement, instead of prematurely switching axes or opening a new family. The main risk is overshooting into instability, but that is precisely the single question this round is meant to answer.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 39 established a new `gated@128` anchor at `LR=2.0e-3`, improving both endpoint and full-curve shape over the refreshed `1.6e-3` baseline.","Round 40 continues the same LR branch with one adjacent upward confirmation at `LR=2.4e-3` to determine whether the current gain was the start of a better regime or already near the stability limit."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated` at `LR=2.4e-3` improves again with a similarly healthy curve, consider one final tight confirmation near this region before moving on to optimizer.","If `gated` at `LR=2.4e-3` degrades or becomes visibly less stable, stop the LR branch and keep `LR=2.0e-3` as the gated mainline anchor before moving to the next recipe axis."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:3078:research/history/logs/agent_action_0038.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `gated` mainline has already shown smooth, still-improving curves at `K=128`, `K=96`, and `K=64`, but Round 38 should first fill the missing clean-baseline step in the prescribed order. Re-running the exact `gated` reference recipe with all reference aux/runtime knobs explicitly pinned answers one question only: does the true anchor still reproduce a clean curve under the current stack before we spend another round on lower `K` or renewed recipe tuning?","summary":"Run a clean control on the current `gated` mainline reference recipe. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=1.6e-3`, and explicitly lock the known reference aux/runtime settings so the next comparison is grounded in a fresh, fully specified anchor curve. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just terminal FVU: recent `gated` runs at `K=96` and `K=64` were still improving late, so we need a refreshed `K=128` control before deciding whether to continue down the K ladder or revisit LR.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the EF=12 constraint, and avoids opening a new branch. It also repairs the sequencing gap in the current mainline by adding the missing clean baseline before any further K move. The main risk is that it may not improve the frontier numerically, but right now the more important value is a fresh, comparable anchor curve for the next decision.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 38 backfills the missing clean-baseline step for the active `gated` mainline with the exact reference recipe explicitly pinned at `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3`.","Recent `gated` K sweeps at `K=96` and `K=64` both had smooth, still-improving curves, so a refreshed `K=128` control is needed before interpreting any further K descent or LR changes."],"next_hypotheses":["If the clean `gated@128` control reproduces the expected anchor with a healthy late curve, resume the K ladder and test `K=32` next to locate where `gated` stops beating `topk`.","If the refreshed baseline comes in materially different from the recorded anchor, treat baseline reproducibility as the immediate issue and avoid drawing more family-quality conclusions from the recent K sweep alone."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
