research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:3145:research/history/logs/agent_round_0176.stdout.log:296:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j`, with the only architectural change versus the mainline being a fixed front-loaded sparse budget split (`stage1_k≈0.75K`, `stage2_k≈0.25K`). This is `扩展兼容` because LUTurbo can export the low-rank trunk, soft codebook, and residual dictionary as static libraries and execute them in the usual `trunk lookup + codebook lookup + two residual lookups + weighted sum` pipeline. Because this family keeps the same trunk/codebook/residual components as the mainline and only reallocates K across the two residual stages, its encoder selection cost should remain within the same feasible regime as the current mainline rather than triggering policy rejection. The probe answers one question only: at low-cost EF=2, is front-loading the residual budget intrinsically better than the symmetric two-stage split, or should this family be deprioritized.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune a single cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.","If the asymmetric probe underperforms or slows training without clear FVU benefit, mark the family as not worth continuing in the low-EF feasible regime."],"notes_to_memory":["`lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is LUTurbo `扩展兼容`: export path is identical to the mainline soft-codebook two-stage family; only stage budget allocation changes.","This is the cleanest remaining matched architecture probe because it preserves the mainline's static libraries and likely feasible encoder cost, avoiding another likely policy-reject like routed/bucketed variants.","When reviewing the run, check not just FVU but also `tokens_per_sec`, total runtime, and `final_total_tokens` to see whether any gain is offset by slower training."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Single-variable discipline is preserved: only `ARCHITECTURE` changes, while `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, and `LR` stay fixed. I am avoiding another clearly over-budget probe and choosing a matched variant that isolates one architectural question while remaining compatible with LUTurbo export and likely feasible under the selection-cost constraint.","summary":"Probe `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` as the one matched architecture change against the current mainline recipe. It is LUTurbo-exportable (`扩展兼容`), keeps the same static trunk/codebook/residual libraries, and tests whether a front-loaded two-stage residual budget is worth continuing in the low-EF feasible regime.","touched_files":[]}
