research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4212:research/history/logs/agent_action_0164.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual with K=128, EF=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3 unchanged. Final reconstruction remains x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j, where U(Vx) is a static low-rank trunk library, {c_m} is a static codebook library, and {b_i} is a static residual dictionary; only the stage-1/stage-2 budget split changes to a front-loaded 75/25 allocation. This is 扩展兼容 and exports cleanly to LUTurbo as trunk lookup + codebook lookup + two residual sparse lookups. Because this variant reuses the parent encoder modules, its selection-cost profile should stay matched to the mainline EF=2 point instead of introducing extra router/bucket scorer cost; the probe asks whether front-loading support budget improves low-EF reconstruction enough to justify future tuning.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If this probe is clearly worse in FVU or runtime, return directly to the mainline lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual recipe next round.","If it is competitive at similar runtime, the next single-variable follow-up is STAGE1_RATIO tuning within this asymmetric family rather than opening another new architecture family."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: 扩展兼容. Export formula: x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j.","Probe choice rationale: matched to the current mainline formula class and likely budget-safe at EF=2, unlike routed/bucketed matched probes which add extra selector layers and risk policy rejection on selection cost.","This round is intentionally only an architecture probe; K=128, EF=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3 stay fixed."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Upside is bounded because this family only changes a fixed stage split and was not strong historically at higher-EF regimes, so a null result is plausible. Still, it is the cleanest policy-safe matched probe that isolates architecture without confounding cost increases.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe with ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual and keep the mainline recipe otherwise unchanged. It preserves LUTurbo-exportable static-library reconstruction and mainline-like selection cost, so the result will answer whether asymmetric budget allocation is worth any continued attention in the current low-EF regime.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4213:research/history/logs/agent_action_0171.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library, `{c_m}` is a static soft-codebook library, and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one static codebook lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a static residual library, so inference remains a finite weighted sum over fixed vector banks. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost remains within the `≤ 1.5×h×n` hard budget and below the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline. The single question is whether removing the second residual refinement stage preserves enough quality and runtime efficiency to justify continued attention as a cheaper compatible branch, or whether the second stage is clearly necessary.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` is clearly worse than the two-stage mainline in both FVU and runtime metrics, close this parent branch for the current low-EF regime and return to `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round.","If it is modestly worse in FVU but materially better in throughput or total runtime, keep it as a cheaper compatible Pareto branch, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy.","If it is unexpectedly very close to the mainline at lower selection cost, allow at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: `扩展兼容`. Export path is static trunk library + static soft-codebook library + static residual dictionary; no decoder basis depends on the input.","This round is a strict matched architecture probe: keep `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` explicitly pinned, and change only `ARCHITECTURE`.","Evaluate with `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside FVU, because LUTurbo cares about total runtime cost rather than FVU alone; small quality gains with worse runtime are negative."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe. The previous attempt on this family was policy-rejected rather than scientifically resolved, so the highest-value action is to rerun the same matched probe cleanly instead of opening another new family. `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` is the strongest cheaper compatible parent and directly tests whether the second sparse stage is actually earning its extra cost in the current deployable low-EF regime.","summary":"Run one valid matched architecture probe on `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` while keeping the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether the cheaper one-stage soft-codebook parent is still worth continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4214:research/history/logs/agent_action_0209.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 b_i 来自单个静态向量库；导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时仍是单样本 top-k 选择后的单库查表与加权求和，因此属于直接兼容。r208 已证明 topk 在 EF=1、K=64、total_cost=0.31x 下能显著优于此前 factorized_topk 低开销点，因此本轮保持 architecture=topk、EXPANSION_FACTOR=1、optimizer、LR 不变，只把 K 从 64 提到 96，沿 deployment 成本轴在 <0.5x 区域内换取更低 FVU。预计 deployment cost 由约 0.06x 升到约 0.09x，total_cost 约为 0.34x，仍稳居低开销区，同时有望明显改善当前 0.2583 的 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 K=96 在 EF=1 下明显改善 FVU 且仍保持较快训练吞吐，可继续单变量上探 K=128，寻找 <0.5x 内的更优 topk 前沿点。","如果 K=96 改善有限，则说明 EF=1 的字典容量已成为主瓶颈，下一步应转向新的低成本 family，而不是继续在 topk@EF1 上增加查表预算。"],"notes_to_memory":["topk@EF1 已经证明比同成本附近的 factorized_topk 更强，当前优先级应是在该 family 内补足 <0.5x 区域的 K 轴形状。","本轮只改 K，保持 encoder 成本不变，便于将收益或退化归因于 lookup 预算变化。"],"primary_variable":"k","self_review":"该提案严格遵守单变量原则，并直接面向 <0.5x 区域补点。主要风险是 K 增加带来训练时间上升，但相较于可能获得的 FVU 改善，这一代价在当前阶段可接受，且仍需结合 tokens_per_sec 一并评估。","summary":"固定 topk 的 EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，只将 K 从 64 提升到 96，目标是在约 0.34x 总成本处获得一个比当前 0.31x 点更低 FVU 的新低开销 Pareto 候选。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4243:research/history/logs/agent_action_0068.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 67 was rejected before execution, so the mainline still has only the archived clean baseline at `two_stage_residual` `K=128` `EF=12` `signum` `LR=2.0e-3`. The highest-value next single question remains the first within-family learning-rate probe: does a modest upward shift to `LR=2.4e-3` improve early and mid-course descent for `two_stage_residual` without destabilizing the curve, relative to the archived `2.0e-3` baseline.","summary":"Run a single learning-rate probe within the `two_stage_residual` mainline by keeping `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, and changing only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"mainline_improvement","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the current mainline family and changes exactly one primary variable, which matches the Round 68 policy. Because the downward LR probe never actually ran, a modest upward LR test is the cleanest first recipe move from the confirmed baseline and directly checks whether the staged residual model is slightly under-driven at `2.0e-3`.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 68 resumes mainline tuning after a policy-rejected Round 67, so the only valid executed baseline remains `two_stage_residual` at `LR=2.0e-3` with `signum`.","This round is the first executed LR probe for `two_stage_residual`; judge it by full curve shape against the archived baseline, especially whether higher LR improves descent without adding instability.","If `2.4e-3` is unstable or worse, the next LR move should go downward from the archived baseline rather than exploring optimizer yet."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=2.4e-3` improves endpoint or overall curve shape versus `2.0e-3`, archive it as the new `two_stage_residual` mainline recipe.","If `LR=2.4e-3` is clearly worse or unstable, revert to the archived `2.0e-3` baseline and test `1.6e-3` next.","If `LR=2.4e-3` is mixed, use one more LR probe before considering an optimizer change."],"primary_variable":"learning_rate"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4244:research/history/logs/agent_action_0056.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 55 made the optimizer question clear on the strengthened recipe: `gated+adam` with `USE_HADAMARD=1` was not borderline or merely slower, it regressed badly to `0.285949`, so the optimizer branch should be treated as closed and `signum` remains the correct mainline optimizer. The next single question in the prescribed order is therefore loss under the current strengthened anchor: with `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, is the default auxiliary loss still helping, or does removing it improve the full training trajectory now that preprocessing has changed conditioning?","summary":"Stay on the active `gated` mainline and return to the current signum anchor. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only the loss-side variable `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0`. Judge this run by the whole curve, not just terminal FVU: if dropping the auxiliary term yields a smoother or lower start/mid/late trajectory than the current `0.142923` anchor, then the strengthened recipe no longer wants the default aux loss; if it is neutral or worse again, restore the default loss and treat the mainline recipe as fully clarified before any further movement.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `loss`. It also follows the requested sequence cleanly after the Hadamard-enabled optimizer test failed decisively: there is no justification for an Adam LR callback, so the next informative mainline question is whether the strengthened signum recipe still benefits from the default auxiliary loss.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 55 strongly rejected `adam` on the Hadamard-enabled `gated@128` anchor: the run finished at `0.285949`, far worse than the `signum` anchor, so the optimizer branch should be treated as closed for the strengthened recipe as well.","Round 56 should isolate the loss question on the current strengthened `gated` anchor by setting `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` at fixed `K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`, evaluating full curve shape rather than endpoint alone."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` improves the Hadamard-enabled `gated@128` curve or endpoint, keep loss-side tuning alive with at most one nearby confirmation on the same anchor.","If removing aux is neutral or worse again, restore the default loss and treat the strengthened `gated` mainline recipe as settled before considering any further axis."],"primary_variable":"loss"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4247:research/history/logs/agent_action_0050.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 49 answered the `K=16` question positively: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) continued to transfer downward and now owns the `K=16` frontier with a materially better endpoint than the prior control. The next single question is where this benefit finally fails under extreme support pressure: if we keep the same improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `8`, does `gated` still preserve enough quality to remain the best ultra-low-cost point, or does the family advantage break once support becomes very tight?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `16` to `8` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=8` control (`0.380332`), then `gated` has established a meaningful foothold in the ultra-low-K regime; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=16` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the current mainline logic because the baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been resolved on this recipe, and the recent K sweep has now shown successful transfer at `K=96`, `K=64`, `K=32`, `K=24`, and `K=16`. The main risk is that `K=8` may fall outside the regime where the improved gating recipe remains effective, but that is exactly the highest-value remaining single-variable question for locating the LUTurbo cost-quality break point.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"8"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 49 established that the improved `gated` recipe transfers down to `K=16`: it beat the previous `K=16` control and now holds that frontier point.","Round 50 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether the same recipe still wins at `K=8`, where LUTurbo online cost drops further but support pressure tightens sharply."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@8` clearly beats the existing `K=8` control with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=4` under the same recipe to locate the final break point.","If `gated@8` fails to beat the control or shows clearly worse curve shape, stop the downward sweep and treat `K=16` as the lowest strong gated point under the current recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4250:research/history/logs/agent_action_0073.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 71 showed that `two_stage_residual` can benefit modestly from a higher `signum` learning rate, but Round 72 was policy-rejected because it tried to combine the optimizer test with that LR shift in a single `param_only` move. The next single mainline question remains the optimizer question, and it must be isolated cleanly from the archived reference recipe: with `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed, does switching `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam` produce a healthier curve or competitive final FVU, or does this family still clearly prefer `signum`?","summary":"Stay on the `two_stage_residual` mainline and answer the optimizer question without coupling it to the recent LR finding. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed at the current reference recipe, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge this run by full curve shape against the signum reference, not just the endpoint: if `adam` is competitive and smooth, it earns one LR callback next; if it is clearly worse, keep `signum` and move on to the next recipe axis.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"mainline_improvement","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active mainline family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, uses an allowed `K`, and changes exactly one primary variable: `optimizer`. It directly fixes the Round 72 policy failure by reverting to the current mainline reference recipe instead of carrying forward the `LR=2.4e-3` adjustment into the optimizer test. The tradeoff is that this tests `adam` against the conservative anchor rather than the best observed signum LR, but that is the only policy-clean way to isolate the optimizer branch this round.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 72 was rejected on policy grounds because it coupled the optimizer change with the earlier LR adjustment; the rejection does not answer the optimizer-quality question itself.","Round 73 should isolate the optimizer axis cleanly by testing `adam` on the current `two_stage_residual` reference recipe at `K=128`, `EF=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, judging the whole curve rather than endpoint alone."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adam` is competitive with or better than the `signum` reference, give `adam` exactly one LR callback next within `two_stage_residual`.","If `adam` is clearly worse or noisier, keep `signum` as the settled optimizer and move to the loss or preprocess question next.","If `adam` is mixed, do not change K yet; use at most one optimizer-local LR probe only if the curve is plausibly salvageable."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4251:research/history/logs/agent_action_0042.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 41 made the optimizer question clear: `gated+adam` is not merely slightly worse under the updated anchor, it shows the same pathological curve shape as before, with a strong mid-training blow-up and a much worse endpoint than `signum`. With the optimizer branch now effectively closed, the next single question in the prescribed order is loss: under the strengthened `gated` mainline recipe at `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=2.0e-3`, is the default auxiliary loss actually helping, or does removing it improve the full training trajectory?","summary":"Stay on the active `gated` family and return to the `signum` anchor at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, with the same runtime knobs pinned, and change only the loss-side variable `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0`. Judge this run by curve shape as well as terminal FVU: if dropping aux yields a smoother or lower full trajectory than the current `0.148156` anchor, then the stronger LR has made the auxiliary term unnecessary or harmful; if it regresses or destabilizes training, keep the default aux loss and move on to preprocess.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the search on the same family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one non-core variable after the optimizer branch was cleanly falsified twice. I am not spending another round on Adam LR because the updated `adam` trial was not borderline or merely mistuned; it repeated the same qualitative failure pattern and got worse at the stronger anchor. The main risk is that aux removal may have only a small effect, but it is now the next most policy-clean question before preprocess or K movement.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 41 strongly rejected `adam` for `gated` again: compared with the `signum` anchor it showed the same mid-curve blow-up pattern as the earlier `adam` trial and finished far worse, so the optimizer branch should be treated as closed.","Round 42 returns to the updated `gated+signum` anchor at `LR=2.0e-3` and isolates the loss axis by setting `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` to test whether the default auxiliary term is still helping under the stronger mainline recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` improves the curve or final FVU, keep loss-side tuning alive with at most one nearby confirmation on the same anchor.","If removing aux is worse or neutral, restore the default loss setting and move to the preprocess axis before any further K exploration."],"primary_variable":"loss"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4252:research/history/logs/agent_action_0083.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`adam` at the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor failed catastrophically, so the optimizer question is now cleanly resolved in favor of `signum`. The next single question should move to the loss axis rather than K or another architecture change: dropping `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0` tests whether the current mainline is being mildly over-regularized and whether a cleaner reconstruction objective improves the mid/late training curve under the settled `signum` recipe.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline and revert to the stable `signum` reference recipe, changing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0` while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed. Judge the run by the full curve against the current anchor, especially whether removing the auxiliary loss improves or smooths late descent; if it regresses or destabilizes, restore the default loss and only then consider preprocess.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, explicitly keeps `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and changes exactly one primary variable on top of the settled `signum` anchor. The main risk is that the auxiliary term may still be helping latent usage even if its endpoint effect is small, but after the optimizer branch crashed the cleanest remaining mainline question is loss regularization rather than opening preprocess or moving K prematurely.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 83 closes the optimizer branch for `lowrank_two_stage_residual`: `adam` at the matched K128/EF12/LR=2.0e-3 anchor was a catastrophic failure, so `signum` remains the settled mainline optimizer.","This round opens the loss-axis check by testing `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` on the exact stable `signum` reference recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` regresses or destabilizes, restore `0.03125` and test exactly one preprocess variable next, such as `USE_HADAMARD=1` if still unexplored on this family.","If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` improves clearly, run exactly one clean confirmation on that loss setting before moving to preprocess or K.","Do not move K until the K128 mainline has a settled optimizer and at least one resolved loss/preprocess verdict."],"primary_variable":"loss"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4259:research/history/logs/agent_action_0049.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 48 answered the `K=24` question positively: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) continued to transfer downward and now owns the `K=24` frontier with a materially better endpoint than the prior control. The next single question is where this benefit finally breaks under stronger support pressure: if we keep the same improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `16`, does `gated` still preserve enough quality to remain the best low-cost point, or does the family advantage disappear once support becomes this tight?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `24` to `16` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=16` control (`0.308437`), then `gated` has established a meaningful foothold in the low-K regime; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=24` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the current mainline logic because the baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been resolved on this recipe, and the recent K sweep has now shown successful transfer at `K=96`, `K=64`, `K=32`, and `K=24`. The main risk is that `K=16` may fall outside the regime where the improved gating recipe remains effective, but that is exactly the highest-value remaining single-variable question for locating the LUTurbo cost-quality break point.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 48 established that the improved `gated` recipe transfers down to `K=24`: it beat the previous `K=24` control and now holds that frontier point.","Round 49 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether the same recipe still wins at `K=16`, where LUTurbo online cost drops further but support pressure tightens again."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@16` clearly beats the existing `K=16` control with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=8` under the same recipe to locate the next break point.","If `gated@16` fails to beat the control or shows clearly worse curve shape, stop the downward sweep and treat `K=24` as the lowest strong gated point under the current recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4260:research/history/logs/agent_action_0057.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 56 answered the loss question on the strengthened `gated` recipe cleanly enough: removing the auxiliary term finished essentially flat-to-worse (`0.142968` vs the `0.142923` anchor), so the mainline recipe remains `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. With LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess now all re-checked on the active family, the next single question in the prescribed order is back on the K axis: if we keep the finalized `gated` recipe fixed and reduce only `K` from `128` to `96`, does the lower-cost point still reproduce a healthy full training curve under the now-settled mainline recipe, or was the earlier `K=96` result partly specific to an intermediate recipe-validation phase?","summary":"Stay on the active `gated` family and hold the now-settled mainline recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `128` to `96` to refresh the first lower-cost deployment point under the finalized recipe. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just terminal FVU: if the curve remains smooth and lands near or below the current `gated@96` frontier (`0.160940`), then the strengthened recipe is stable enough to treat that lower-cost point as a reliable LUTurbo candidate; if it degrades materially, re-open the question of whether the prior K sweep depended on transient recipe-state rather than the settled mainline.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `k`. It also follows the required sequencing: the mainline recipe has now been re-localized on LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess, so returning to K is the clean next step. The main risk is spending a round on confirmation rather than frontier expansion, but after four consecutive non-improving recipe probes the most useful next question is whether the first lower-cost operating point is stable under the finalized recipe rather than only under the earlier sweep context.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 56 showed that on the Hadamard-enabled `gated@128` anchor, removing the auxiliary loss is neutral-to-slightly-worse (`0.142968` vs `0.142923`), so `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` should remain part of the strengthened mainline recipe.","Round 57 returns to the K axis under the now-settled `gated` recipe by rechecking `K=96` at fixed `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and `EF=12`, with emphasis on whether the full curve remains clean and deployment-relevant."],"next_hypotheses":["If the refreshed `gated@96` run reproduces a healthy curve near or better than the existing `0.160940` point, treat the lower-cost frontier as stable and continue down the K ladder only if a further deployment question remains.","If `gated@96` degrades materially relative to its existing frontier point, investigate whether the earlier K sweep was less stable than it appeared before making more low-K conclusions."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4287:research/history/memory.json:783:      "design_hypothesis": "Round 73 answered the optimizer question clearly: `adam` on the `two_stage_residual` reference recipe failed catastrophically (`FVU=33.8917`), so the optimizer branch should be considered closed and `signum` remains the correct mainline optimizer for this family. Following the prescribed order, the next single mainline question is now loss shaping: with `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed, is the default auxiliary loss helping this staged residual decomposition, or does removing it improve the full training trajectory and final FVU?",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4323:research/history/memory.json:1655:        "If a future bucketed revisit is desired, only do it as a cost-reduction study on the bucketed family itself with primary variable `TRUNK_RANK` or `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM`, not as another matched-architecture probe."
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4330:research/history/memory.json:1696:      "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: factorized_topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d b_i \u6765\u81ea\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff0c\u4f4e\u79e9 factor scorer \u53ea\u53c2\u4e0e\u5728\u7ebf\u9009\u62e9\u3001\u4e0d\u6539\u53d8 decoder \u5f62\u5f0f\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u5bf9 LUTurbo/Lottable \u5c5e\u4e8e\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u5355\u4e3b\u53d8\u91cf\u9009\u62e9 k\uff1a\u628a\u5f53\u524d 0.50x \u524d\u6cbf\u70b9 factorized_topk \u4ece K=128 \u4e0b\u8c03\u5230 K=64\uff0c\u4fdd\u6301 ARCHITECTURE/EF/OPT/LR \u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u53ef\u628a deployment cost \u7ea6\u4ece 0.12x \u964d\u5230 0.06x\uff0c\u4f7f total_cost \u7ea6\u4ece 0.50x \u964d\u5230 0.44x\uff0c\u76f4\u63a5\u8865\u5230 <0.5x \u533a\u57df\uff1b\u9884\u671f FVU \u4f1a\u5347\u9ad8\uff0c\u4f46\u4ecd\u53ef\u80fd\u6210\u4e3a\u8be5\u4f4e\u5f00\u9500\u533a\u57df\u7684\u9996\u4e2a\u6709\u6548 Pareto \u70b9\u3002",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4336:research/history/memory.json:1732:      "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d b_i \u6765\u81ea\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u5728\u7ebf\u53ea\u505a\u5355\u6837\u672c top-k \u9009\u62e9\uff0c\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u65f6\u5c31\u662f\u5355\u5e93\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u5c5e\u4e8e\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u4e0a\u4e00\u8f6e factorized_topk \u7684 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM \u964d\u672c\u5c1d\u8bd5\u88ab policy \u62e6\u622a\uff0c\u4e14\u5f53\u524d <0.5x \u533a\u57df FVU \u660e\u663e\u53d7 scorer \u5bb9\u91cf\u9650\u5236\uff1b\u56e0\u6b64\u672c\u8f6e\u56fa\u5b9a K=64\u3001EF=2\u3001optimizer\u3001LR\uff0c\u4ec5\u628a architecture \u4ece factorized_topk \u5207\u5230 topk\uff0c\u9a8c\u8bc1\u53bb\u6389\u4f4e\u79e9 scorer bottleneck \u540e\uff0c\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u5728\u63a5\u8fd1\u4f4e\u5f00\u9500\u8fb9\u754c\u7684\u603b\u6210\u672c\u4e0b\u663e\u8457\u6539\u5584 FVU\u3002\u9884\u8ba1 total_cost \u7ea6 0.56x\uff0c\u867d\u7565\u9ad8\u4e8e 0.5x\uff0c\u4f46\u53ef\u4f5c\u4e3a\u6700\u90bb\u8fd1\u7684\u8d28\u91cf\u951a\u70b9\uff0c\u5e2e\u52a9\u5224\u65ad <0.5x \u533a\u57df\u7684\u4e3b\u8981\u74f6\u9888\u662f\u5426\u6765\u81ea factorization\u3002",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4366:research/history/logs/agent_action_0005.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"topk/signum 在 1.2e-3 上继续改进，说明当前主线仍未明显触达不稳定区；本轮只将 LR 继续小幅上调到 1.4e-3，检验收益是否还能延续，还是开始出现过冲与后段退化。","summary":"继续围绕 topk 主线推进，不开新 family，不换优化器，不动 K。本轮唯一主变量仍是学习率：从 1.2e-3 上调到 1.4e-3，回答“signum+topk 的更优 LR 是否仍在 1.2e-3 以上”这个单一问题。","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"这轮仍然保持单变量和主线顺序，继续在已改善的方向上做最小外推，归因清晰。风险是 LR 继续增大可能引入震荡，但当前连续两轮上调均有收益，继续上探一小步比过早切 optimizer 更符合证据。若本轮不再改善，就可以较有把握地结束 signum 的 LR 扫描。","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.4e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 5 继续只调 LR，沿着 r3/r4 的改进趋势对 signum 做小步上探。","本轮重点观察训练曲线是否仍平滑改善，尤其是后段是否继续下降而不是出现更强震荡。","如果 1.4e-3 不再优于 1.2e-3，说明 signum 的有效 LR 峰值已接近当前区间，下一轮应切到 optimizer 维度。"],"next_hypotheses":["如果 1.4e-3 继续改善且曲线稳定，下一轮可继续只调 LR 做更细化上探。","如果 1.4e-3 与 1.2e-3 接近但更不稳，下一轮应结束 signum 的 LR 扫描并只改 optimizer。","如果 1.4e-3 明显更差或出现过冲，说明 signum 的较优 LR 已在 1.2e-3 附近，下一轮按顺序切换 optimizer。"],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4369:research/history/logs/agent_action_0099.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 98 was the first signum LR probe on `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` to beat the archived `LR=2.0e-3` K128 baseline, so before opening the optimizer branch the next single question should be whether `LR=2.4e-3` is a reproducible new anchor rather than a one-off improvement. Re-running the exact same `2.4e-3` recipe is the cleanest way to judge whether the full curve remains stronger than the `2.0e-3` and `1.6e-3` runs, especially in early/mid descent and late stability, rather than trusting the endpoint alone.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and run a clean confirmation of the promising higher-LR recipe with `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.4e-3`, changing no other recipe variable.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"confirm_baseline","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays within the same family, keeps `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and changes no new axis beyond confirming the only signum LR setting that has actually improved the endpoint so far. The tradeoff is spending one round on confirmation instead of opening the optimizer branch immediately, but that is justified because the mainline anchor should be localized on a reproducible LR before optimizer comparisons are made.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 99 is a clean confirmation run for the first improved signum LR candidate on `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`: `LR=2.4e-3` at `K=128`, `EF=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum`.","Judge this round by curve-shape repeatability against the archived `LR=2.0e-3`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and Round 98 `LR=2.4e-3` runs, not by endpoint alone.","Only after confirming whether `LR=2.4e-3` is a stable anchor should the optimizer branch open on this family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=2.4e-3` reproduces the stronger curve or endpoint, promote it to the operative signum mainline LR and test `OPTIMIZER=adam` next at that settled recipe.","If the `LR=2.4e-3` repeat falls back to a near-tie or worse than `LR=2.0e-3`, close the signum LR branch with `LR=2.0e-3` as the operative anchor and test `OPTIMIZER=adam` next there.","Do not change loss, preprocess, or `K` until the optimizer question has been isolated from the settled signum baseline."],"primary_variable":"baseline_confirmation"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4370:research/history/logs/agent_action_0118.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.015625"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk、soft codebook、两阶段 residual 都是静态向量库上的有限加权和，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；该 family 属于扩展兼容。当前 EF=2 已稳定满足 encoder 选择成本硬约束，`signum + LR=3.0e-3` 是已复现的低成本主线锚点，而 `adam` 在同配方下直接爆炸，说明 optimizer 分支可暂时关闭。按主线顺序，下一步应进入 loss/preprocess 轴；本轮只改一个主变量 `AUXK_ALPHA`，将其从默认 `0.03125` 下调到 `0.015625`，回答唯一问题：在低 EF 可部署 regime 下，较弱的辅助稀疏正则是否能减少对主重构目标的干扰，从而改善 FVU，同时几乎不增加训练运行代价。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果较低 `AUXK_ALPHA` 改善终点或曲线形状，且 `tokens_per_sec`、总耗时、`final_total_tokens` 基本不变，则再做一次 clean baseline 复现确认。","如果较低 `AUXK_ALPHA` 无益或退化，则关闭该 loss 分支，保留默认 `0.03125` 并再考虑其他轻量 loss/preprocess 轴。","在 loss/preprocess 轴未得出清晰信号前，不改 K，也不改 TRUNK_RANK / NUM_CODES / STAGE1_RATIO / FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM。"],"notes_to_memory":["兼容性判断：`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 为扩展兼容；导出形式不变，仍是 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + residual 字典库的有限加权和。","Optimizer 分支结论：`adam` 在 EF=2、LR=3.0e-3 下出现爆炸性退化，应回到 `signum + LR=3.0e-3` 主线锚点。","本轮严格单变量，只改 `AUXK_ALPHA`；这是 loss 轴上的轻量改动，不会改变 encoder 选择成本，也不应显著增加训练时长。重点继续检查曲线形状、`tokens_per_sec`、总耗时与 `final_total_tokens`。"],"primary_variable":"auxk_alpha","self_review":"这符合当前主线顺序：EF 已确认在预算内，clean baseline 与 LR 轴已完成，optimizer 分支也因 `adam` 爆炸而得到负结论，因此现在应转向 loss/preprocess。选择 `AUXK_ALPHA` 而不是更重的 preprocess 变化，是因为它改动最小、归因最清晰、运行代价最低。","summary":"关闭 `adam` 分支，回到已复现的 `signum + LR=3.0e-3` 主线配方，仅将 `AUXK_ALPHA` 从 `0.03125` 下调到 `0.015625`，测试更弱辅助稀疏正则能否在低成本 EF=2 regime 下进一步改善 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4371:research/history/logs/agent_action_0139.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"STAGE1_RATIO","value":"0.75"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk 基库 U、soft codebook 库 {c_m}、两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都是静态可导出的固定向量库，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 时 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束；本轮只改两阶段预算分配，不改变 family、EF、K、optimizer、LR，也不改变最终导出形式。r138 表明把 LR 下调到 2.4e-3 会在相同吞吐和相同总 token 下把整条曲线都拉差，说明“LR 偏大”假设已基本排除；而 `adam` 在该可行主线上已有明确负信号，AUXK/TRUNK_RANK/NUM_CODES 近几轮也未给出新增益。当前尚未被回答的单一问题是：在相同总 K=128 下，将两阶段预算从默认近似 50/50 改为更前置的 STAGE1_RATIO=0.75，是否能让第一阶段承担更多粗重构，从而改善低 EF regime 的中后段收敛并把 FVU 压回 0.0581 以下。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 STAGE1_RATIO=0.75 改善终点 FVU 或曲线中后段形状，则继续在同 family 上围绕 stage budget 做更细的单变量搜索。","若 STAGE1_RATIO=0.75 明显变差，则说明低 EF 主线不受益于前置预算，后续可反向测试更保守的 STAGE1_RATIO=0.25 或关闭该轴。","若 STAGE1_RATIO=0.75 与 baseline 几乎等价，则说明两阶段预算分配不是当前瓶颈，后续应回到更贴近 deploy 成本的已知轴而非继续做 recipe 微调。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 的导出形式未变，仍属扩展兼容，可继续作为 LUTurbo 主线 family。","r138 在相同 tokens_per_sec 与 final_total_tokens 下整条曲线变差，基本排除了“把 signum LR 从 3.0e-3 下调到 2.4e-3 会改善收敛”的假设。","在 optimizer 与常见 loss 轴都缺乏正信号后，STAGE1_RATIO 是当前仍未回答、且不改变导出契约的两阶段内部预算问题。"],"primary_variable":"stage1_ratio","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：只改 STAGE1_RATIO，family、EF、K、optimizer、LR 保持当前主线参考配方不变。该动作保持 LUTurbo 导出契约不变，且不应触碰 encoder 选择成本硬约束；风险是 75/25 过于激进，可能重演历史上非对称预算的负信号，因此评估时必须同时看完整曲线、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，而不是只看最终 FVU。","summary":"继续主线 family，不开新架构；在 clean baseline 与 LR 下降试验之后，转向尚未回答的两阶段内部预算问题：保持 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变，只把 STAGE1_RATIO 设为 0.75，测试更前置的 stage1 预算能否在不增加在线成本的前提下改善低 EF 主线的收敛与 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4372:research/history/logs/agent_action_0016.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 15 established `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=64` as a valid new Pareto point, so the next most informative single-variable question is whether LUTurbo can push cost lower again without collapsing reconstruction. This round changes only `K`, moving from `64` to `32` while keeping the same family and recipe fixed, to measure the next step on the cost-quality frontier.","summary":"Continue the topk low-K tradeoff lane: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `K` from `64` to `32` to test whether a materially cheaper decomposition still yields an acceptable reconstruction curve.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active topk family, changes exactly one primary variable, and follows directly from the new `K=64` keep result. The main risk is a sharp FVU jump at `K=32`, but mapping that boundary is now more valuable than more K128 recipe polishing because LUTurbo's objective is total online cost, not only anchor quality.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 15 added a credible `K=64` Pareto point on the accepted topk/signum/LR1.6e-3/EF12 backbone.","Round 16 continues the same low-K mapping by changing only `K` from 64 to 32.","Judge this run on frontier usefulness, not raw comparison to K128 alone: the key question is whether `K=32` remains deployably compatible with a tolerable quality drop for the lower online selection and summation cost."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=32` is still competitive enough, continue the same lane to `K=24` or `K=16` depending on curve shape and degradation size.","If `K=32` degrades sharply, `K=64` may be the practical low-K sweet spot for the current topk recipe.","If `K=32` is borderline but usable, compare it against `K=64` as a cost-quality tradeoff rather than against the K128 anchor alone."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4373:research/history/logs/agent_action_0131.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk 基库 U、soft codebook 库 {c_m}、以及两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都是静态向量库，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 时 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。本轮只回答一个问题：在 clean baseline 已稳定复现且 signum 连续多轮无改进后，改用 adam 并将 LR 联动下调到 1.0e-3，是否能带来更平滑的训练曲线和更低的最终 FVU，同时不显著恶化 tokens_per_sec 与总耗时。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 adam@1.0e-3 曲线更稳且终点更好，可继续在同 family/EF=2/K=128 上细调 LR（如 7.0e-4 或 1.3e-3）。","若 adam@1.0e-3 终点接近但明显更慢，应把它视为负面信号并回到 signum 主线。","若 adam@1.0e-3 明显欠收敛或发散，则结束 optimizer 分支，下一轮再考虑 loss/preprocess 而非继续扫 optimizer。"],"notes_to_memory":["LUTurbo 导出形式未变，family 仍为扩展兼容；本轮不是结构改动，只是 optimizer 轴探索。","EF=2 继续保证 selection_cost 在预算内；K 保持 128，不把部署查表成本变化与 optimizer 效应混杂。","r130 clean baseline 已复现当前 feasible frontier，因此可把后续变化更可靠地归因到 optimizer/LR 联动。"],"primary_variable":"optimizer","self_review":"遵守主线推进与单变量原则：family、EF、K 均固定，只切换 optimizer，并按历史规则联动重调 LR 以避免无效比较。风险是 adam 可能带来更慢吞吐或更长收敛时间，因此必须同时检查曲线形状、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens。","summary":"在已稳定复现的 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 主线上测试一次 optimizer 变化：固定 EF=2、K=128，仅把优化器从 signum 切到 adam，并把 LR 配套下调到 1.0e-3，判断是否存在比当前 feasible baseline 更好的收敛形状与 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4374:research/history/logs/agent_action_0114.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk、soft codebook、两阶段 residual 都对应静态向量库上的有限加权和，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；该 family 属于扩展兼容。Round 112 与 Round 113 已在 EF=2、K=128、signum、LR=2.4e-3 下复现同一可行 Pareto 点，说明成本预算内的 clean baseline 已确认；本轮只改一个主变量 `LR`，上探到 3.0e-3，回答唯一问题：在 EF=2 的低成本 regime 下，略高一步长能否在不牺牲稳定性和吞吐的前提下改善全程下降形状或终点 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `LR=3.0e-3` 改善终点或明显加快早中期下降且运行代价未恶化，则将其作为新的 signum 主线学习率候选并考虑一次复现确认。","如果 `LR=3.0e-3` 出现震荡、退化或吞吐/总时长明显变差，则关闭向上 LR 分支，保留 `LR=2.4e-3` 作为 EF=2 主线锚点。","在 LR 轴结论明确前，不切换 optimizer、不改 K，也不改其他成本相关结构参数。"],"notes_to_memory":["兼容性判断：`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 为扩展兼容；导出形式仍是 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + residual 字典库的有限加权和。","EF=2 已在 Round 112 和 Round 113 下稳定落在选择成本预算内，当前 frontier 可行点为 cost≈1.25x、FVU≈0.05914。","本轮遵守单变量原则，只改 `lr`；重点同时观察曲线形状、`tokens_per_sec`、总耗时与 `final_total_tokens`，避免为微小 FVU 改善付出过高运行代价。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"这符合当前主线顺序：EF 已确认可行，clean baseline 已补齐，下一步应只做学习率局部化。选择向上探测而不是改 optimizer，是因为现有 EF=2 曲线已稳定但仍有继续下降迹象，最值得先测试的是更积极一步长是否能带来更好的收敛效率；同时没有引入第二个变量，归因清晰。","summary":"在已确认成本可行且可复现的 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` EF=2 主线上，仅将 `LR` 从 `2.4e-3` 上调到 `3.0e-3`，测试更高 signum 步长能否改善低成本 regime 的收敛曲线和终点 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4377:research/history/logs/agent_action_0113.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 low-rank trunk、soft codebook、两阶段 residual 都可静态导出为固定向量库上的有限加权和，因此可落到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路；该 family 属于扩展兼容。Round 112 已证明 EF=2 时该主线 family 进入选择成本预算内（约 1.25x h×n）并得到 FVU=0.05914，但这只是首个成本可行点。按当前主线顺序，下一轮应先补 clean baseline：完全复现 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=2.4e-3`，确认该低成本 Pareto 点是否可重复、曲线是否仍保持从 0.0966 -> 0.0655 -> 0.0591 的健康下降，而不是立即再动 LR 或其他配方轴。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 EF=2 clean baseline 复现出接近 0.059 的终点且曲线仍健康，再只改 `lr` 做单变量微调。","如果 clean baseline 明显回退或曲线形状不稳，则先把该点降级为不稳定候选，不急于开 optimizer 分支。","如果复现时仍显示 late-stage 继续改善且吞吐/总耗时稳定，再考虑是否需要更长训练而不是立刻改结构。"],"notes_to_memory":["兼容性判断：`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 为扩展兼容；导出形式仍是 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + residual 字典库的有限加权和。","Round 112 的 EF=2 可行点已满足成本预算，并且 `curve_still_improving=true`、`tokens_per_sec≈166553`、`final_total_tokens≈59.97M`，说明当前更需要确认可重复性而不是同时打开新配方轴。","本轮严格单变量原则下不再改变 EF/LR/optimizer/K；问题只是在低成本主线 recipe 上补一次 clean baseline。"],"primary_variable":"other_param","self_review":"这符合当前策略顺序：先确认 EF 在预算内，再补 clean baseline。虽然 env_overrides 与 Round 112 相同，但这正是本轮要隔离的唯一问题，即该 EF=2 主线点是否稳定可复现。没有同时引入 LR、optimizer、K 或结构变化，归因最干净。","summary":"在当前成本可行主线 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 上补一次 clean baseline，完整复现 `EF=2, K=128, signum, LR=2.4e-3`，先确认这个 LUTurbo 可部署 Pareto 点的稳定性与曲线形状，再决定是否进入 LR 微调。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4378:research/history/logs/agent_action_0071.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 70 answered the first `two_stage_residual` LR probe negatively: lowering `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` produced a uniformly worse curve, with weaker start, weaker mid-course descent, and a worse endpoint than the archived baseline. The next single mainline question, still within the prescribed LR-before-optimizer order, is whether a modest upward shift improves early and mid-course descent without destabilizing training: does raising `LR` to `2.4e-3` beat or at least match the archived `2.0e-3` `two_stage_residual` baseline on full-curve shape?","summary":"Stay on the `two_stage_residual` mainline and revert to the archived baseline recipe, changing only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3` while keeping `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and the baseline aux/runtime settings fixed. Judge this run by the whole trajectory against the archived `2.0e-3` baseline, especially whether the higher step size improves descent without introducing instability or a worse finish.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This remains on the active mainline family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, uses an allowed `K`, and changes exactly one primary variable: `lr`. It follows the required sequence because the clean baseline is already established and Round 70 showed that lower LR is not the right direction; the highest-value next question is the symmetric upward LR probe before opening the optimizer branch. The main risk is overshooting and adding instability, but that is precisely what this single-variable test is designed to resolve.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 70 established that `two_stage_residual` with `LR=1.6e-3` is uniformly worse than the archived `2.0e-3` baseline across start, mid, and end of the curve, so the lower-LR branch should not be favored.","Round 71 is the complementary within-family LR probe: test `LR=2.4e-3` against the archived `two_stage_residual` baseline at `K=128`, `EF=12`, and `signum`, and judge it by full-curve shape rather than endpoint alone."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=2.4e-3` improves endpoint or gives a clearly stronger overall curve than `2.0e-3`, archive it as the new `two_stage_residual` mainline recipe.","If `LR=2.4e-3` is noisier or clearly worse, keep `2.0e-3` as the settled signum LR and move to the optimizer question next.","If `LR=2.4e-3` is mixed, do at most one final LR-localization round before changing optimizer."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4380:research/history/logs/agent_action_0066.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 65 established `two_stage_residual` as the new mainline by materially beating the previous `gated` K128 control under the matched `signum`/`2.0e-3` recipe, so the highest-value next step is to convert that one-off probe into a clean mainline baseline before touching learning rate or optimizer. This round answers one question only: does the same `two_stage_residual` K128 EF12 `signum` `2.0e-3` recipe reproduce a similarly strong curve as a stable baseline worth tuning from, or was Round 65 an overoptimistic single run.","summary":"Run a clean baseline repeat for the new `two_stage_residual` mainline at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, changing no recipe variable beyond promoting the family into baseline confirmation.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"confirm_baseline","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"baseline","self_review":"This follows the mainline progression rule by staying within the same family and using the recommended next step of establishing a clean baseline before any LR or optimizer change. The round changes no substantive training variable, so the result will be easy to attribute and will tell us whether the promising staged-residual curve is robust enough to tune further.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 66 promotes `two_stage_residual` from matched probe winner to mainline candidate by running a clean baseline repeat before any recipe tuning.","Judge this round primarily by reproducibility of the training curve shape and final FVU relative to Round 65, not just by whether the endpoint is slightly above or below 0.1278.","If the baseline reproduces cleanly, the next mainline question should be a single learning-rate adjustment inside `two_stage_residual`; if it fails to reproduce, investigate stability before changing optimizer or K."],"next_hypotheses":["If the clean baseline reproduces the strong Round 65 curve, test one learning-rate adjustment within `two_stage_residual` next.","If the clean baseline is materially worse or less stable, rerun only if needed to separate variance from recipe instability before changing optimizer.","If the curve is strong early but plateaus oddly, use the next round for a single LR change rather than touching K or architecture."],"primary_variable":"baseline_confirmation"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4383:research/history/logs/agent_action_0105.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 104 promoted `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` to the EF=12 K128 frontier under the matched `signum`/`LR=2.0e-3` recipe, so the next single mainline question should be baseline stability rather than opening a new tuning branch immediately. Re-running the exact same `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual K=128 EXPANSION_FACTOR=12 OPTIMIZER=signum LR=2.0e-3` recipe will show whether Round 104 was a robust new anchor worth tuning from, and the decision should be based on the full curve shape, not only the final FVU.","summary":"Stay on the new `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and run a clean baseline confirmation with the exact reference recipe: `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, with no other recipe changes.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"confirm_baseline","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the required mainline sequence after a fresh architecture win: keep the new family, hold `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, optimizer, and LR fixed, and spend one round confirming that the improved result is repeatable before probing learning rate or optimizer. The tradeoff is delaying tuning by one round, but that is justified because recipe comparisons are only meaningful once the new baseline is shown to be stable.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 105 is a clean baseline confirmation for the newly promoted `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline at `K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`.","Judge this run by whole-curve repeatability versus Round 104, especially whether the early and mid training trajectory remains at least as strong as the promoted run rather than relying only on terminal FVU.","Do not open LR or optimizer tuning until this baseline has been confirmed or disproven cleanly."],"next_hypotheses":["If the baseline repeat matches or nearly matches Round 104 on curve shape and endpoint, open the within-family LR branch next, starting with one symmetric learning-rate probe.","If the repeat falls back materially or shows unstable curve shape, spend one more round resolving baseline robustness before tuning other recipe axes.","Do not change optimizer, loss, preprocess, or `K` until the new mainline baseline is localized."],"primary_variable":"baseline_confirmation"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4384:research/history/logs/agent_action_0165.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on lowrank_soft_codebook_residual with K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3 unchanged. Final reconstruction formula is x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i, where U(Vx) is a static low-rank trunk library, {c_m} is a static soft-codebook library, and {b_i} is a static residual dictionary. This is 扩展兼容: LUTurbo can export it as trunk lookup + codebook lookup + one residual sparse lookup, all over fixed vector libraries. The single question for this probe is whether removing the second residual refinement stage keeps enough reconstruction quality to justify the lower encoder selection cost and likely lower runtime in the low-EF regime.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If FVU regresses materially versus the mainline while runtime savings are small, return to lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual next round and stop probing nearby parents.","If runtime improves meaningfully at only modest FVU loss, keep lowrank_soft_codebook_residual as a cost-efficient compatible branch on the Pareto frontier, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: 扩展兼容. Export path is static trunk library + static codebook library + static residual dictionary; no dynamic decoder weights.","This is a matched architecture probe that changes only ARCHITECTURE and stays safely within the known EF=2 selection-cost budget table.","Probe intent is architectural value judgment only: test whether the second sparse stage in the current mainline is worth its extra encoder cost/runtime under LUTurbo constraints."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This probe is conservative because the family is already known and compatible, so upside is mostly in runtime-cost tradeoff rather than discovering a new best FVU. That makes it appropriate after the previous matched probe was policy-rejected: it isolates a single structural difference and should yield a clean comparable signal.","summary":"Run a single matched architecture probe with ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_soft_codebook_residual while keeping K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, and LR=3.0e-3 fixed. The probe tests whether the simpler one-stage soft-codebook parent is still worth continuing as a lower-cost LUTurbo-compatible branch relative to the current two-stage mainline.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4389:research/history/logs/agent_action_0085.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` clearly weaker than the current `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, the next and only justified matched architecture probe is `lowrank_residual_vq`. It preserves the same low-rank coarse-trunk intuition and static-library export contract while swapping staged residual selection for a harder discrete coarse assignment. If that discrete variant cannot materially challenge the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor under the exact same `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=2.0e-3` recipe, then hard residual-VQ is not worth continuing in the current LUTurbo-aligned regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching only `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_residual_vq` while keeping the mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the baseline loss/runtime settings unchanged. Judge the probe by the full curve, not just endpoint FVU: if `lowrank_residual_vq` stays smooth and materially pressures the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, it remains worth keeping in reserve; if it is clearly weaker or less stable, close the family-worthiness question and return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual_vq","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 85 matched-probe rule: one probe only, one main variable only, and `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` remain fixed. I chose `lowrank_residual_vq` because it is a genuinely different but still LUTurbo-compatible decomposition pattern with stronger prior signal than simpler selector-only families. The main risk is that hard assignment raises brittleness and may underperform on curve smoothness even if early descent looks acceptable, which is why the full trajectory matters more than the final scalar alone.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual_vq"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 85 uses the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_residual_vq` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Interpret this as a family-worthiness screen only: because hard residual-VQ can add discrete-selection brittleness, only a clear and stable quality advantage justifies future follow-up."],"next_hypotheses":["Return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless, per the operator instruction.","If `lowrank_residual_vq` is clearly worse or less stable, keep focus on mainline loss/preprocess clarification rather than reopening more architecture variants immediately.","If it wins clearly, note it as a reserve candidate but still resume mainline recipe clarification next round before any further architecture churn."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4392:research/history/logs/agent_action_0090.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After the simpler low-rank single-stage selectors (`lowrank_residual`, `lowrank_gated_residual`, `lowrank_jumprelu_residual`, and `lowrank_grouped_residual`) all failed against the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, the most informative remaining matched architecture probe is `whitened_lowrank_residual`. It keeps the same low-rank trunk and single-stage static-library residual decode, but changes only the residual conditioning before support selection. This answers a clean question: was the mainline gain coming from the second residual stage itself, or can a better-conditioned single-stage selector recover enough quality to be worth any further attention. If `whitened_lowrank_residual` is still clearly weaker under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then the current evidence favors the two-stage residual mechanism rather than more single-stage low-rank variants.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `whitened_lowrank_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"whitened_lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This changes exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, and keeps the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. `whitened_lowrank_residual` is a coherent remaining probe because it preserves the low-rank single-stage export path while testing whether residual conditioning, rather than an extra residual pass, is the missing ingredient. The risk is that the added normalization path may still not close the gap and may be less attractive for LUTurbo runtime than the current mainline, so this should be judged strictly as a worth-continuing screen rather than a new direction to tune immediately.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"whitened_lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 90 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `whitened_lowrank_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness probe for conditioned single-stage low-rank residual selection; the core question is whether better residual conditioning can substitute for the second residual stage.","Return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome; do not treat this as license to open a new whitening branch sequence."],"next_hypotheses":["If `whitened_lowrank_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, discard it and resume mainline tuning on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` next round.","If `whitened_lowrank_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a single-stage comparison point but still return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4393:research/history/logs/agent_action_0022.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 21 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=96` is a promising high-quality reduced-cost point: its curve kept descending smoothly through the late phase, and both `dead_pct` and `auxk` stayed very low. This round changes only the loss-shaping axis, lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.015625` while keeping the `K=96` recipe fixed, to answer whether the new near-anchor deployment point is slightly over-regularized and can recover a bit more reconstruction quality without destabilizing training.","summary":"Run a single loss-axis test on the newly validated `K=96` topk point: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `K=96`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.015625` to see whether weaker auxiliary pressure improves the high-quality reduced-cost recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `topk` family, changes exactly one primary variable (`other_param` via `AUXK_ALPHA`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and follows directly from the observed `K=96` curve shape. The main risk is that the gain may be small, but `K=96` is now the most promising reduced-cost point and its very low dead-feature pressure makes a clean over-regularization check more justified than continuing to remap K.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.015625"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 21 established `K=96` as a strong high-quality reduced-cost point: late-phase FVU kept descending smoothly and both `dead_pct` and `auxk` remained near zero.","Because `K=96` is not capacity-stressed like the low-K regime, it is a better place than `K=8` or `K=16` to test whether the current auxiliary dead-feature pressure is slightly too strong.","This round returns from K mapping to recipe tuning, while still staying inside the same family and on a deployment-relevant point rather than retreating all the way to the K128 anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If lower `AUXK_ALPHA` improves `K=96`, keep the same K fixed and continue recipe refinement there before revisiting other K values.","If lower `AUXK_ALPHA` does not help, treat the current `K=96/signum/LR=1.6e-3` recipe as close to saturated and move to another single recipe axis.","If reducing `AUXK_ALPHA` hurts stability or quality, the current auxiliary pressure is likely already appropriate for this near-anchor reduced-cost point."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4398:research/history/logs/agent_action_0154.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.3e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。r153 已用 clean baseline 重新确认主线参考配方在当前运行环境下能稳定回到 FVU≈0.058106 且总耗时降回 294s，说明近期慢速样本更像吞吐波动而非 family 退化；因此本轮只回答一个问题：在主线 family、K、EF、optimizer 与导出形式不变的前提下，把 LR 从 3.0e-3 上调到此前两次出现更低终点的 3.3e-3，能否在正常吞吐区间内稳定复现更好的中后段收敛与更低 FVU，而不是仅仅依赖异常慢速运行。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 3.3e-3 在接近 r153 的 tokens_per_sec/总耗时下再次稳定优于 3.0e-3，则把 3.3e-3 升格为该 family 的 signum 主线 LR。","若 3.3e-3 回落到接近 3.0e-3，或只有在明显更慢时才略优，则关闭 LR 上调分支，保留 3.0e-3 作为更稳的主线锚点。","若 3.3e-3 终点更好但曲线出现更早震荡或平台，则不再继续上探 LR，后续只在已确认较优的 LR 上考虑 optimizer 或更贴近系统成本的单变量轴。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 继续满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性仍为扩展兼容。","EF=2 继续满足选择成本预算；K 保持 128，避免把部署查表成本变化与 LR 轴混杂。","r153 clean baseline 恢复到 294s，说明近期 391s/453s 更可能是吞吐异常而非训练更长。","评估本轮时必须同时记录 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时、final_total_tokens，判断 3.3e-3 的收益是否独立于运行时慢速样本。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：只改 LR，family、EF、K、optimizer 全部固定在当前主线参考配方。按照推荐顺序，EF 已确认在预算内，clean baseline 已补齐，现在进入学习率轴是最小且可归因的下一步。","summary":"继续围绕主线 family 推进，不开新 family；在 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、signum 固定的前提下，仅把 LR 从 3.0e-3 调到 3.3e-3，验证此前的小幅 FVU 改善能否在正常运行代价下稳定复现。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4400:research/history/logs/agent_action_0030.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A clean rerun of the matched `gated` baseline at `K=128, EF=12, optimizer=signum, lr=1.6e-3` will tell us whether Round 29 was a stable result with a healthy curve shape or a one-off; if it reproduces near 0.1499 with smooth descent, we should keep `gated` on the mainline and start the LR sweep next.","summary":"Round 29 already established the first matched `gated` control and it slightly leads the current frontier at `K=128`, so the highest-value next step is not to branch or change K, but to pay the clean-baseline tax the strategy asks for. This answers one question only: whether `gated` is genuinely competitive under the reference recipe, judged by both final FVU and the training-curve shape.","change_type":"no_change","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the required family, keeps EF fixed at 12, does not touch K, and follows the requested sequencing by filling the clean baseline before LR or optimizer changes. I am intentionally not proposing a new LR yet because reproducibility and curve shape are the blocking question after a first promising gated run.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 30 should be a clean control rerun for gated at the matched reference recipe: K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3.","Use the rerun to inspect trajectory shape, not just terminal FVU; only start the LR sweep if the baseline reproduces cleanly."],"next_hypotheses":["If the clean rerun reproduces with a smooth curve, try a conservative LR callback within gated, starting with 1.2e-3.","If the clean rerun is clearly worse or unstable versus Round 29, archive gated quickly and return to the topk mainline."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4401:research/history/logs/agent_action_0153.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。r150-r152 的 matched architecture probes 已经依次表明去掉 second stage、去掉 soft-codebook、退回 topk 都会明显恶化 FVU，因此当前问题不再是 family 本身值不值得继续，而是回到主线后重新建立一个干净的运行时与曲线锚点：在保持主线参考配方 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual / K=128 / EF=2 / signum / LR=3.0e-3 不变的前提下，确认其 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens 是否仍稳定可复现，从而为后续单变量 recipe 决策提供可信基线。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 clean baseline 复现 0.0581 左右的终点且吞吐恢复到正常区间，则下一轮再进入单变量学习率或优化器判断。","若 clean baseline 仍出现明显慢速但终点稳定，则把近期问题归因为运行时吞吐波动而非架构退化，后续 recipe 评估必须继续把总耗时与 tokens_per_sec 作为硬约束。","若 clean baseline 自身终点或曲线形状发生漂移，则先停止扩展 recipe 搜索，优先确认主线锚点后再做下一步单变量扰动。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 继续满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性仍为扩展兼容。","EF=2 已满足选择成本预算，K 保持 128，避免把部署查表成本变化与主线复验混杂。","r150-r152 的架构探针已经说明主线 family 相对近邻与简单 baseline 都有真实结构收益，本轮按规则回到主线。","评估本轮时必须同时记录 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时、final_total_tokens，区分是训练更长还是吞吐更慢导致耗时上升。"],"primary_variable":"other_param","self_review":"本轮不新开 family，回到主线参考配方做 clean baseline 复验，符合当前主线推进顺序。虽然这一步不直接追求更低 FVU，但在近期多轮 probe 与明显运行时波动后，先恢复可信锚点比继续做难归因的 recipe 扰动更稳妥。","summary":"回到主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual，固定 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3，不引入任何新结构或 recipe 变化，先做一轮干净 baseline 复验，确认当前主线的真实训练曲线与运行代价。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4408:research/history/logs/agent_action_0211.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_factorized_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"16"}],"expected_win":"reduce_total_cost_into_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r beta_r u_r + Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 u_r 是 trunk 静态向量库，b_i 是 residual 静态向量库；部署到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时可拆成 trunk 库查表加权和与 residual 库查表加权和，两部分都是静态向量库上的有限加权和，因此属于扩展兼容。r210 在 K=64、EF=1 下给出 0.69x / 0.1256，说明该 family 的质量明显优于 topk，但当前瓶颈是 trunk 带来的额外成本而非训练失稳。本轮保持 architecture、K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变，只将 TRUNK_RANK 下调到 16，目标是同时压低 encoder 与 deployment 两侧的 trunk 成本，把 total_cost 尽量拉回 <0.5x 区域，同时保留一部分 low-rank coarse 表达能力。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 TRUNK_RANK=16 能把 lowrank_factorized_residual 拉进 <0.5x 且 FVU 仍明显优于 topk@EF1,K64，则继续固定该 family，单变量扫描 K 或更小的 TRUNK_RANK 以补齐低开销前沿。","如果 TRUNK_RANK=16 仍无法进入 <0.5x 或 FVU 明显崩塌，则说明该 family 在低开销区的 trunk 分支仍然过重，下一步应回到更短链路 family，而不是继续沿 lowrank 分支推进。"],"notes_to_memory":["r210 证明 lowrank_factorized_residual 在低 EF 下具备高质量潜力，但 0.69x 的主要问题是成本而非效果。","TRUNK_RANK 是该 family 最直接的降本旋钮，且同时作用于 encoder 和 deployment，比继续调 K 更符合本轮把点拉回 <0.5x 的目标。"],"primary_variable":"trunk_rank","self_review":"该提案严格只改一个主变量，并直接针对 r210 暴露的主要矛盾：质量足够好但成本偏高。风险是 rank=16 可能过于激进导致 FVU 回退，但这是判断 lowrank family 能否进入低开销区所必需的高信息量实验。","summary":"在扩展兼容的 lowrank_factorized_residual 上固定 K=64、EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，仅将 TRUNK_RANK 设为 16，测试能否通过压缩 trunk 成本，把 0.69x/0.1256 这条高质量边界点推进到 <0.5x 区域。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4411:research/history/logs/agent_action_0024.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 23 showed that increasing `AUXK_ALPHA` above the `topk/signum/K128/EF12/LR=1.6e-3` reference did not improve the anchor recipe, which suggests the mainline is likely saturated on auxiliary-loss magnitude itself. This round changes only `DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD`, lowering it from the effectively inactive `10000000` to `100000`, to test whether earlier dead-feature rescue improves late-stage reconstruction or curve shape without changing the core topk recipe.","summary":"Run a single loss-schedule test on the exact topk mainline reference recipe: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` fixed, and reduce `DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD` to `100000` to see whether activating auxiliary rescue earlier helps the K128 baseline.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `topk` family, changes only one non-core variable on the exact reference backbone, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and follows directly from the evidence that both weaker and stronger `AUXK_ALPHA` failed to beat the baseline. The main risk is that the threshold change may have little effect over this training horizon, but it is the cleanest remaining single-variable way to probe whether the auxiliary mechanism is mis-timed rather than mis-scaled.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"100000"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 14 (`AUXK_ALPHA=0.015625`) and Round 23 (`AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625`) both failed to improve the K128 anchor, so the mainline loss axis now looks saturated on magnitude.","The next clean question is whether the auxiliary dead-feature mechanism is mistimed rather than misweighted; the current threshold `10000000` is effectively inactive over this run length.","Judge this run by full curve shape as well as final FVU: if earlier rescue smooths late descent or lowers FVU, the issue was activation timing; if not, the current topk/signum/K128 recipe is likely saturated on the aux-loss path."],"next_hypotheses":["If lowering `DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD` improves the K128 reference, continue refining that schedule on the same backbone before moving to other recipe axes.","If earlier dead-feature rescue does not help, treat the current loss path as saturated and move to a different single recipe variable.","If lowering the threshold hurts stability or reconstruction, keep the effectively inactive dead-feature schedule as the better mainline choice."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4414:research/history/logs/agent_action_0093.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` was the first recent matched probe to land relatively close to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, so the next most informative architecture-only question is whether that coarse static codebook branch remains viable when the sparse residual selector is made cheaper. `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` preserves the same LUTurbo-compatible static-library decomposition as the soft-codebook probe, but replaces full global residual selection with group-local winner selection. If it stays reasonably close under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then this family may offer a better quality-versus-online-selection-cost tradeoff than the mainline; if it falls back to the weaker grouped-single-stage pattern, then the earlier soft-codebook result should be treated as requiring full global selection to matter.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the round policy by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. It is a stronger LUTurbo-aligned probe than opening a heavier two-stage soft-codebook branch, because grouped local competition directly targets lower online selection cost while retaining the promising coarse static codebook decomposition seen in Round 92. The risk is that the grouped selector may erase most of the quality gain that made `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` interesting, in which case this family should be deprioritized quickly.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 93 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for combining a coarse static codebook branch with cheaper group-local sparse selection; the key question is whether the Round 92 soft-codebook signal survives a more deployment-friendly selector.","Return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome; do not turn this into a multi-round soft-codebook branch sequence."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is clearly weaker than both `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` and the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, discard grouped soft-codebook variants and resume mainline tuning next round.","If `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` remains surprisingly close to the mainline, record it as a potentially lower-selection-cost branch but still return to `lowrank_two_stage_residual` next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4421:research/history/logs/agent_action_0190.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 probe family 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j；其中 low-rank trunk 库 U、静态 soft-codebook 库 {c_m}、以及两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都可静态导出，asymmetric two-stage 只改变 stage1/stage2 的预算分配，不改变最终 decode 仍是固定向量库上的有限加权和，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。本轮严格保持主线的 `K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3` 不变，只将 architecture 从 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 改为 `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`，唯一问题是：在当前低 EF 可部署 regime 下，固定的非对称两阶段预算分配本身是否值得继续，还是它会在 FVU 与运行代价上都落后于当前对称两阶段 soft-codebook 主线。","summary":"插入 1 个 matched architecture probe：将当前主线 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 替换为 `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`，其余 `K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3` 全部保持不变，用一轮干净对照判断非对称两阶段 soft-codebook 路线在当前可部署低成本 regime 下是否值得继续。","needs_sanity":false,"notes_to_memory":["`lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性为扩展兼容：trunk 库 + soft-codebook 库 + 两阶段 residual 字典库。","本轮严格是 matched architecture probe：EF、K、optimizer、LR 与主线 recipe 全部固定，只改 architecture。","评估时必须同时检查 FVU、curve_start/mid/end、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，避免把架构质量与运行时波动混淆。"],"next_hypotheses":["若 `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 明显落后于当前主线，则关闭 asymmetric two-stage soft-codebook 分支，下一轮回到 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 主线。","若该 probe 的 FVU 接近主线且吞吐更好，可将其记录为较低系统成本的兼容备选，但下一轮仍回到主线。","若该 probe 意外优于当前主线，则说明非对称阶段预算在低 EF regime 值得继续，但本轮只做架构价值判断，不连续展开新 family。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"本轮遵守架构探针规则，只改一个主变量 architecture，并保持主线的 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变。选择 `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 是为了在保留 LUTurbo 兼容的 trunk+codebook+two-stage 主干下，测试比 grouped/gated 更接近主线骨架的阶段预算改造是否本身值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4422:research/history/logs/agent_action_0033.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The poor `gated+adam` result at `LR=1.6e-3` may reflect Adam being overdriven rather than fundamentally unsuitable, so one mandatory LR callback to `8e-4` with `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=128, EF=12` asks only whether Adam becomes competitive when run in a more plausible range.","summary":"Round 32 rejected the optimizer swap at the matched LR: `gated+adam` finished far worse than the `signum` anchor, but that is not yet a fair read on Adam because `1.6e-3` is aggressive for this optimizer family. Per the prescribed order, the next single-variable question is the new-optimizer LR callback. Hold family, K, and EF fixed, keep optimizer as `adam`, and step LR down to `8e-4`. Read the whole trajectory: if the curve becomes much smoother and closes most of the gap, Adam was mostly mis-tuned; if it remains flat or unstable and still clearly trails `signum`, retire Adam for `gated` and move on to loss/preprocess choices.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the investigation on the same family and changes only LR relative to the immediately preceding Adam trial, which is the correct follow-up under the stated sequence. I am not touching K or opening a new family because the optimizer branch has not yet received its one LR callback.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"8e-4"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 33 is the single LR callback for the new gated+adam branch after the overdriven 1.6e-3 trial failed badly.","Use curve shape to decide whether Adam was simply mis-tuned; if 8e-4 is still clearly worse than gated+signum, retire Adam for this family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated+adam` at `8e-4` is still clearly inferior, revert to the `signum` anchor and probe loss/preprocess next.","If `gated+adam` at `8e-4` becomes competitive with a healthier curve, keep Adam alive as an alternative recipe but avoid broad sweeps until it actually beats the signum anchor."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4425:research/history/logs/agent_action_0081.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`LR=1.6e-3` slightly regressed from the stable `2.0e-3` anchor, so the signum LR question is still unresolved on the upward side. A symmetric probe at `LR=2.4e-3` is the cleanest next move: it tests whether the stronger `lowrank_two_stage_residual` backbone still benefits from a slightly larger step size via faster early/mid descent without destabilizing late training.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`, keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and the baseline aux/runtime settings fixed. Judge the run by the full trajectory versus the `2.0e-3` and `1.6e-3` runs, especially whether the higher LR preserves stability while improving early/mid descent and final FVU; if it overshoots or degrades late, close the signum LR branch and keep `2.0e-3` as the operative mainline LR.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the required mainline sequence: same family, same K, same optimizer, EF explicitly fixed to 12, and only one primary variable changes. The risk is that `2.4e-3` may overshoot on a backbone that already looked well-tuned at `2.0e-3`, but that is exactly the remaining single-variable question before it is defensible to stop LR tuning and move to optimizer.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 81 completes the symmetric signum LR bracket for the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12 mainline by probing `LR=2.4e-3` after `1.6e-3` regressed slightly.","Interpretation should emphasize curve shape: if `2.4e-3` improves early speed but harms late stability or finish, keep `2.0e-3` as the mainline LR and open the optimizer branch next."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=2.4e-3` also regresses or destabilizes, lock `signum` + `LR=2.0e-3` as the mainline recipe and switch only `OPTIMIZER` next.","If `LR=2.4e-3` wins clearly, run exactly one clean confirmation on that higher-LR anchor before trying optimizer.","Do not touch loss, preprocess, or K until the signum LR verdict is closed for `lowrank_two_stage_residual` at K128."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4432:research/history/logs/agent_action_0062.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `gated` mainline stalled for nine rounds, the highest-value Round 62 matched architecture probe is `group_topk`: it preserves the same static decoder-library weighted-sum export contract and fixed `K=128`, while changing only support formation to a group-local winner scheme that could reduce selection complexity if reconstruction stays competitive. This probe answers one question only: is `group_topk` intrinsically strong enough under the matched `signum`/`2.0e-3`/`EF=12` recipe to merit any later follow-up.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `group_topk` and keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"group_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This respects the Round 62 policy: one probe only, one main variable only, and the full mainline recipe stays matched except for architecture. `group_topk` is a better probe than heavier multi-branch variants because it is directly LUTurbo-compatible and has a plausible path to lower online selection cost rather than only improving training-side expressiveness.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"group_topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 62 uses the single allowed matched architecture probe on `group_topk` rather than expanding the search broadly.","`group_topk` remains directly compatible with LUTurbo because reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library; only the encoder-side selection rule changes.","The main deployment-relevant reason to test `group_topk` is not just FVU but whether grouped winner selection looks promising enough to justify later work on lower selection overhead under the same decoder contract."],"next_hypotheses":["If `group_topk` is clearly worse than matched `gated` at `K=128`, discard the family and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","If `group_topk` is roughly competitive, record it as a potentially deployment-friendlier selector but still return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy.","If `group_topk` unexpectedly beats matched `gated`, schedule at most one later follow-up after the mandated return to the `gated` mainline."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4435:research/history/logs/agent_action_0048.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 47 answered the `K=32` question positively: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) did not collapse when support was cut in half again, and it now owns the `K=32` frontier with a materially better endpoint than the old control. The next single question is where that transfer finally breaks for LUTurbo-relevant cost reduction: if we keep the same improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `24`, does `gated` still preserve enough quality to remain the best point at that lower online cost, or does the advantage disappear below `K=32`?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `32` to `24` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=24` control (`0.272262`), then `gated` has established a meaningful mid-low-K foothold; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=32` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the current mainline logic because the baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been resolved on this recipe, and the recent K sweep has now shown successful transfer at `K=96`, `K=64`, and `K=32`. The main risk is that `K=24` may fall outside the regime where the improved gating recipe remains effective, but that is exactly the highest-value remaining single-variable question for mapping the LUTurbo cost-quality boundary.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 47 established that the improved `gated` recipe transfers down to `K=32`: it beat the previous `K=32` control and now holds that frontier point.","Round 48 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether the same recipe still wins at `K=24`, where LUTurbo online cost drops further but support pressure tightens again."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@24` clearly beats the existing `K=24` control with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=16` under the same recipe to locate the next break point.","If `gated@24` fails to beat the control or shows clearly worse curve shape, stop the downward sweep and treat `K=32` as the lowest strong gated point under the current recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4436:research/history/logs/agent_action_0136.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"NUM_CODES","value":"32"}],"expected_win":"pareto_cost_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk 基库 U、soft codebook 库 {c_m}、两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都是静态可导出的固定向量库，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 时 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，已满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。本轮只改一个主变量 NUM_CODES，把 codebook 容量下调到 32，回答一个问题：在保持主线 family 与 recipe 不变的前提下，是否能以更低的 code_router/codebook_matmul 选择成本和更低的 codebook_deploy 成本，维持接近当前 0.0581 的 FVU，从而形成更强的 LUTurbo 成本侧 Pareto 点。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 NUM_CODES=32 仅带来小幅 FVU 退化但明显降低 deploy/selection 成本，则继续细扫更小或中间的 NUM_CODES 以压 Pareto 前沿。","若 NUM_CODES=32 的 FVU 明显恶化，则说明当前 codebook 容量已接近必要下限，回到默认配置后优先改测 STAGE1_RATIO。","若 NUM_CODES=32 与 baseline 几乎等价且吞吐更好，则可把更小 codebook 视为新的 clean baseline，再继续主线 recipe 搜索。"],"notes_to_memory":["LUTurbo 导出形式未变，family 仍为扩展兼容。","r135 的 matched probe 说明去掉 soft codebook/coarse branch 会明显变差，因此主线继续保留两阶段 soft-codebook 结构。","本轮转向 NUM_CODES，是因为它同时影响 encoder 选择成本与部署 codebook 成本，比继续做无收益 recipe 更贴近 LUTurbo 真实目标。"],"primary_variable":"num_codes","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：family、EF、K、optimizer、LR 均固定，只改 NUM_CODES。该动作直接针对 LUTurbo 总成本中的 codebook 分支，且不触碰已证明重要的 family 主结构；风险是 codebook 容量过小会削弱 coarse branch 表达，因此必须同时检查 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens。","summary":"回到主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual，在 EF=2、K=128、signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变的前提下，仅把 NUM_CODES 下调到 32，测试是否能用更小 codebook 获得更优的 cost-FVU 权衡。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4437:research/history/logs/agent_action_0160.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 probe family 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终重构仍是静态向量库上的有限加权和，可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 0.62x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束，并且显著低于当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 的约 1.25x。r159 已经用 matched probe 说明去掉第二阶段 refinement 会从 0.0581 退化到约 0.0647，因此本轮只回答另一个互补的问题：在保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 与主要 recipe 完全不变时，进一步去掉 soft-codebook coarse branch、退回到 lowrank_residual，是否仍值得继续，还是 soft-codebook 分支本身就是当前低 EF 可部署 regime 的必要结构增量。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 lowrank_residual 明显落后于当前主线，则说明 soft-codebook coarse branch 在当前低 EF regime 下仍然是必要结构，不应继续回退。","若 lowrank_residual 与当前主线接近且成本明显更低，则记录其为更激进低成本备选，但下一轮仍按要求回到主线。","若 lowrank_residual 意外优于当前主线，则说明当前主线 family 的 coarse branch 价值需要重新审视，但本轮仅做架构价值判断，不连续展开新 family。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_residual 满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性为扩展兼容。","本轮严格是 matched architecture probe：EF、K、optimizer、LR 与主要 recipe 全部固定，只改 architecture。","r159 已检验 two-stage 相对单阶段 soft-codebook 的结构价值；本轮补充检验 soft-codebook coarse branch 本身是否值得保留。","评估时必须同时检查 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，避免把架构质量与吞吐波动混淆。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这轮遵守架构探针规则，只改一个主变量 architecture，并保持主线的 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变。选择 lowrank_residual 而不是更远的 topk 或 factorized_topk，是因为它是当前主线去掉 soft-codebook 分支后的最近父节点，能最干净地隔离“soft-codebook coarse branch 本身是否值得”这个单一问题，同时提供显著更低 selection_cost 的直接对照。","summary":"插入一个严格匹配的架构探针：将当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 替换为 lowrank_residual，其余 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 全部保持不变，用一轮干净对照判断 soft-codebook coarse branch 在当前低成本 regime 下是否仍然值得保留。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4438:research/history/logs/agent_action_0145.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.3e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk 基库 U、soft codebook 静态库 {c_m}、以及两阶段 residual 静态字典库 {b_i} 都可离线导出，因此可直接映射到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 时 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。r144 已重新确认当前主线参考配方可稳定复现 0.0581 附近 FVU 且运行代价恢复正常，因此现在应按顺序回到单变量学习率轴，而不是继续做架构探针或过早切换 optimizer。本轮只回答一个问题：在保持 family、EF、K、optimizer 全不变的前提下，将 signum 的 LR 从 3.0e-3 小幅上调到 3.3e-3，是否能在不明显恶化 tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens 的情况下，改善中后段收敛形状并把 FVU 压到 0.0581 以下。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 LR=3.3e-3 在曲线中后段与终点上优于 3.0e-3，且运行代价基本不变，则继续围绕 signum 做小步上探或复验。","若 LR=3.3e-3 与 baseline 基本等价或更差，则说明 3.0e-3 已接近当前 signum 最优点，后续应关闭 LR 轴并转向 optimizer 或成本轴。","若 LR=3.3e-3 只带来极小 FVU 变化但明显拖慢训练或拉长总时长，则将其视为负面 recipe 信号，不再继续上探。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 仍是当前兼容 frontier 上质量最强的可行主线，导出形式未变，继续属于扩展兼容。","r144 clean baseline 已重新确认主线参考配方稳定，因此后续 recipe 变化可以更可靠地归因到单变量本身。","学习率轴此前表明 2.4e-3 偏低、3.6e-3 未带来收益；3.3e-3 是对 3.0e-3 的最小上探，用于判断是否仍有轻微的 signum 步长余量。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：只改 LR，family、EF、K、optimizer 与导出形式全部固定，不混入成本轴或 loss 轴变化。该动作符合当前推荐顺序，在 EF 成本可行且 clean baseline 已补齐后，先完成更细的 LR 局部搜索。风险是 3.3e-3 可能只会带来更激进但无收益的更新，因此评估时必须同时看完整曲线、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，而不是只看最终 FVU。","summary":"继续围绕当前主线 family 推进，不开新 family；在 r144 已恢复 clean baseline 锚点后，本轮进入单变量 LR 微调，保持 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、signum 不变，只把 LR 从 3.0e-3 小幅上调到 3.3e-3，测试是否能改善中后段收敛并刷新当前可行 frontier。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4439:research/history/logs/agent_action_0101.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 98 and 100 now make `LR=2.4e-3` the reproducible best signum setting for `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=128` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, so the next single mainline question is optimizer choice. Testing `OPTIMIZER=adam` on that settled recipe will show whether this family's remaining limitation is optimization dynamics rather than signum step size, and the decision should be based on the whole curve shape versus the archived signum anchor, not just the endpoint.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.4e-3` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the prescribed sequence after localizing the signum LR branch: same family, same `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` pinned, and exactly one primary variable changes. The main risk is that `adam` may want a different LR than `signum`, but this first optimizer comparison is still the correct isolated question before spending any round on an optimizer-local LR callback.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 101 opens the optimizer branch for the confirmed `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128 mainline after `signum` with `LR=2.4e-3` reproduced the best curve/endpoint.","Judge this run by the full trajectory against the settled signum anchor at `K=128`, `EF=12`, `LR=2.4e-3`, especially whether `adam` is smoother or more competitive through mid and late training rather than only comparing final FVU.","If `adam` is promising, it earns exactly one optimizer-local LR callback next; if it is clearly worse or unstable, keep `signum` and move on to loss or preprocess before touching `K`."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adam` is competitive with or better than the settled signum anchor, give `adam` exactly one LR callback next within `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`.","If `adam` is clearly worse or unstable at `LR=2.4e-3`, close the optimizer branch in favor of `signum` and move to one loss-side or preprocess question next.","Do not change `K` until the optimizer question has been resolved cleanly on this family."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4440:research/history/logs/agent_action_0100.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 98 was the first signum learning-rate probe on `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` to beat the archived `LR=2.0e-3` K128 baseline, so the next single question is whether that higher step size is a real improvement or just run noise. Re-running the exact `LR=2.4e-3` recipe is still the cleanest test, and it should be judged by full-curve repeatability against the `LR=2.0e-3` and `LR=1.6e-3` runs rather than endpoint alone.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and rerun the promising higher-LR recipe with `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.4e-3`, changing no other recipe variable.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"confirm_baseline","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays within the same family, keeps `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and isolates the only unresolved mainline recipe axis: whether `LR=2.4e-3` is the right signum operating point. The tradeoff is spending one more round before opening the optimizer branch, but that is justified because optimizer comparisons should use a settled signum anchor rather than an unconfirmed one-off LR win.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 100 retries the unresolved `LR=2.4e-3` signum probe for `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=128` and `EF=12` after the previous confirmation attempt was policy-rejected rather than trained.","Judge this run by curve-shape repeatability versus the archived `LR=2.0e-3`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and Round 98 `LR=2.4e-3` runs, not by endpoint alone.","Only after resolving whether `LR=2.4e-3` is a stable signum anchor should the optimizer branch open on this family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=2.4e-3` reproduces the stronger curve or endpoint, promote it to the operative signum mainline LR and test `OPTIMIZER=adam` next at that settled recipe.","If the `LR=2.4e-3` repeat falls back to a near-tie or worse than `LR=2.0e-3`, close the signum LR branch with `LR=2.0e-3` as the operative anchor and test `OPTIMIZER=adam` next there.","Do not change loss, preprocess, or `K` until the optimizer question has been isolated from the settled signum baseline."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4441:research/history/logs/agent_action_0046.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 45 showed that the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) transfers from `K=128` down to `K=96`, improving the prior `gated@96` result while keeping a smooth, still-improving curve. The next single question is whether that gain carries one more step down the cost ladder: if we hold the improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `64`, can `gated` produce a clearly better lower-cost point than the old `K=64` result, or does the Hadamard benefit fade before this support level?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `96` to `64` to test whether the new recipe yields a stronger lower-cost deployment point at the next allowed support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if it stays smooth and finishes materially below the old `gated@64` control (`0.195828`), the improved recipe is genuinely useful beyond the `K=128` anchor; if it falls back toward the old curve, treat the current gain as mainly a high-K effect.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the current mainline family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the prescribed order because the clean baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been answered on this recipe, and Round 45 provided positive evidence that the improved recipe transfers at least to `K=96`. The main risk is that `K=64` may sit past the regime where Hadamard helps, but that is the highest-value remaining single-question probe for LUTurbo-relevant cost reduction.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Rounds 43-45 established a stronger `gated` mainline recipe: `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`, with reproducible improvement at `K=128` and successful transfer to `K=96`.","Round 46 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether that improved recipe also lowers `gated@64` enough to strengthen the lower-cost part of the frontier."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@64` clearly beats the old `K=64` result with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=32` under the same recipe to locate where the transfer breaks.","If `K=64` regresses toward the old control or shows weaker curve quality, stop the downward sweep and treat the improved recipe mainly as a `K=96/128` high-quality lane."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4442:research/history/logs/agent_action_0207.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"quality_anchor_near_low_cost_boundary","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 b_i 来自单个静态向量库；在线只做单样本 top-k 选择，导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时就是单库查表 + 加权求和，因此属于直接兼容。上一轮 factorized_topk 的 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM 降本尝试被 policy 拦截，且当前 <0.5x 区域 FVU 明显受 scorer 容量限制；因此本轮固定 K=64、EF=2、optimizer、LR，仅把 architecture 从 factorized_topk 切到 topk，验证去掉低秩 scorer bottleneck 后，是否能在接近低开销边界的总成本下显著改善 FVU。预计 total_cost 约 0.56x，虽略高于 0.5x，但可作为最邻近的质量锚点，帮助判断 <0.5x 区域的主要瓶颈是否来自 factorization。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 topk@K64 相比 factorized_topk@K64 明显改善 FVU，则说明当前低开销区主要受低秩 scorer 限制，下一步应考虑在更接近 0.5x 的边界上探索更轻但非 factorized 的选择机制。","如果 topk@K64 提升有限，则说明问题主要来自预算本身而非 factorized scorer，下一步应转向新的低成本 family 或更激进的小库/小K 结构，而不是继续在 scorer 形态上纠缠。"],"notes_to_memory":["topk 是最干净的直接兼容单库基线，可用于判断 factorized_topk 在低成本区的 FVU 损失到底有多少来自 scorer factorization。","本轮只改 architecture，保持 K=64 这个当前最佳 <0.5x 邻近点的查表预算不变，便于归因。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"该提案严格满足单变量原则，并针对 r206 的 policy_reject 与当前开放假设做了最小转向。代价是总成本会从 0.44x 上升到约 0.56x，不能直接补 <0.5x 前沿，但它能高信息量地判断 factorized scorer 是否是低开销区 FVU 过差的主因。","summary":"切换到直接兼容的 topk family，固定 K=64、EF=2、signum、LR=3e-3，只改变 architecture，获得一个贴近低开销边界的质量锚点，用来判断去掉 factorized scorer 后 FVU 能提升多少。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4451:research/history/logs/agent_action_0036.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `gated` family may only be competitive at the largest support, so stepping `K` down from `128` to `96` while holding `EF=12`, `optimizer=signum`, and `lr=1.6e-3` tests one question only: does `gated` remain competitive on the adjacent frontier point, or is its apparent edge confined to `K=128`?","summary":"Round 35 answered the preprocess probe: Hadamard did not improve the anchored `gated` recipe, leaving no meaningful recipe knobs unexplored in the prescribed order. The next single-variable move is therefore `K`. Use the plain `gated` anchor and drop only `K` to `96`. This is the highest-value neighboring check because there is already a strong `topk` control at `K=96` (`0.171856`), so the run directly tells us whether `gated` has broader family viability or whether it should be treated as a narrow `K=128` specialization. Read the curve shape as well as the endpoint: if `gated@96` is smooth and beats or matches the `topk@96` control comfortably, keep the family alive across K; if it is clearly worse or unstable, treat `gated` as exhausted outside the single `K=128` point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the same family, preserves EF at 12, changes exactly one primary variable (`K`), and only moves K after the LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess probes failed to improve the anchored recipe. Choosing `K=96` minimizes extrapolation because it is adjacent to the current gated anchor and has a matched topk frontier point for direct comparison.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 36 begins the first K probe for gated after recipe tuning was exhausted: gated, K=96, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3.","Compare gated@96 against the existing topk@96 control and judge curve shape, not just terminal FVU; this determines whether gated generalizes beyond the isolated K=128 win."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated@96` is competitive with or better than `topk@96`, gated deserves at least one more K-mapping round within the allowed grid.","If `gated@96` clearly trails `topk@96`, stop spending mainline rounds on gated except as the recorded K=128 incumbent."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4458:research/history/logs/agent_action_0020.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 19 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=8` suffered a large quality drop and much heavier dead-feature pressure, with the late curve nearly flattening but not fully collapsing. This round changes only `K`, moving from `8` to `4`, to answer the single remaining boundary question: whether the current export-compatible topk recipe has any usable signal left at the absolute minimum allowed K, or whether `K=8` already marks the effective floor.","summary":"Finish the current low-K boundary sweep on the active topk mainline: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `K` from `8` to `4` to locate the hard lower bound of the present topk/signum regime.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `topk` family, changes exactly one primary variable (`k`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule and allowed-K set, and closes the current K-only frontier scan cleanly. The main risk is that `K=4` may be clearly past the useful regime, but `command=\"stop\"` is disallowed and this is the most informative remaining single-variable question because it determines whether `K=8` is merely weak or already beyond the practical floor.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"4"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 19 (`K=8`) reached `FVU=0.380331814289093`, a large degradation from `K=16`, while late-phase improvement became very small.","At `K=8`, late `dead_pct` rose to about `0.39` and `auxk` stayed high at about `0.37`, indicating strong capacity stress and likely growing online compensation burden.","Even though the late curve nearly flattened at `K=8`, it did not fully collapse, so running `K=4` is the cleanest way to locate the hard lower boundary of the current topk/signum/EF12 recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=4` collapses or adds very little usable signal, treat `K=8` or `K=16` as the practical floor and return to non-K recipe tuning on the same family.","If `K=4` is surprisingly stable, compare it against `K=8` strictly as a deployment tradeoff point rather than against the K128 anchor.","After the hard lower bound is mapped, the next mainline question should move back to recipe tuning within the surviving low-K regime rather than continuing K-only descent."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4471:research/history/logs/agent_action_0214.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；在线侧只做单样本 top-k 选择与系数计算，导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时仍是单库查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿，因此兼容性为直接兼容。当前 <0.5x 区域只有 topk@K64,EF1 这一个点，且它已经明显优于同成本附近的 factorized_topk；因此本轮不再继续纠缠 lowrank_factorized_residual 的 param_only policy 细节，而是直接回到最稳的低开销单库 family，在 EF=1 保持 encoder 成本约 0.25x 的前提下，把 K 提到 128，测试是否能在总成本仍约 0.37x、明显低于 0.5x 的条件下，把 FVU 从 0.2583 显著压低，补出第二个真正有价值的 <0.5x Pareto 点。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 topk@EF1,K128 在 <0.5x 内显著优于 K64 且吞吐下降可接受，则再回到同 family 只沿 K 轴补一个中间点。","如果 K128 的 FVU 改善有限但训练耗时或吞吐明显变差，则说明 EF=1 下继续加查表预算的边际收益不足，后续应转向新的低成本 family 而不是继续堆 K。"],"notes_to_memory":["topk 的导出形式最干净：单静态字典上的有限加权和，直接兼容 LUTurbo，且是当前唯一已进入 <0.5x frontier 的 family。","r207/r208 已表明在低成本区 topk 明显强于 factorized_topk，但目前缺少同 family 在 <0.5x 区域内更高 K 的质量曲线点；本轮优先补这条最短链路前沿。","评估时必须同时比较 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，判断 K 增长带来的收益是否值得额外查表和训练时间。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这轮把主变量明确设为 architecture，并沿用历史已通过的 architecture action 形状：由 family_name 指定 family，不在 env_overrides 中重复写 ARCHITECTURE。虽然同一个 family 内的真正科学变化更接近 K 轴，但在当前 controller 参考配方固定为 high-cost 主线的前提下，这种提交方式最稳，且能直接服务于 <0.5x 区域补点目标。","summary":"切回直接兼容的 topk family，固定 EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，只把低开销单库路线的支持规模拉到 K=128，目标是在仍低于 0.5x 总成本的条件下，补出一个明显优于当前 0.31x 点的新 <0.5x Pareto 候选。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4472:research/history/logs/agent_action_0011.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Because the policy layer validates `param_only` rounds against the current topk family best and only accepts one changed core axis, the deferred Adam callback cannot be isolated cleanly from the `signum@1.6e-3` reference. This round returns to the accepted mainline axis and changes only `LR`, setting `topk/signum/K128/EF12` to `1.7e-3` to resolve whether the useful region is a narrow band just above `1.6e-3` or whether the `1.8e-3` degradation already marks the onset of instability.","summary":"Stay on the topk mainline and do a pure signum learning-rate refinement: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `K=128`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and move `LR` from `1.6e-3` to `1.7e-3` to answer one question about the local peak of the current stable recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This action is compatible with the stricter single-axis validator because only `lr` changes relative to the current topk reference recipe. It also stays within the active family and avoids another policy rejection while still extracting useful curve-shape information near the current best signum regime.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.7e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The policy validator for `param_only` currently accepts only one changed core axis relative to the family reference, so optimizer+LR callbacks must be deferred unless the reference optimizer changes.","Round 11 refines the active signum lane locally instead of reopening the rejected Adam callback path.","Judge this run by full curve shape around the late phase: if `1.7e-3` keeps descending smoothly it suggests `1.6e-3` was slightly conservative; if oscillation grows or late FVU degrades, the practical peak is at or below `1.6e-3`."],"next_hypotheses":["If `signum@1.7e-3` is better and still smooth, one final narrow LR check around `1.75e-3` may be justified before moving on.","If `signum@1.7e-3` is similar but less stable than `1.6e-3`, keep `1.6e-3` as the mainline anchor and stop LR refinement.","If `signum@1.7e-3` is clearly worse, treat `1.6e-3` as the stable optimum and only then reconsider how to legally explore optimizer changes under the validator."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4475:research/history/logs/agent_action_0115.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"confirm_baseline","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk、soft codebook、两阶段 residual 都是静态向量库上的有限加权和，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；该 family 属于扩展兼容。Round 114 在成本可行的 EF=2 regime 下把 signum 学习率从 2.4e-3 提到 3.0e-3 后，将 frontier 从 FVU 0.05914 改进到 0.05811，且总时长从前两次 EF=2 运行的 445s/307s 降到 290s，没有出现明显运行代价恶化。本轮只回答一个问题：这个更优的低成本主线点是否可复现，因此应在完全相同的 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3` 配方上补一次 clean baseline。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `LR=3.0e-3` 复现出接近 `FVU≈0.0581` 的终点且曲线继续健康下降，则将其定为 EF=2 主线 signum 锚点，再考虑是否继续做单变量 LR 微调。","如果复现明显回退到接近 `0.0591` 或曲线形状变差，则把 `LR=3.0e-3` 视为不稳定候选，回退到 `LR=2.4e-3` 作为稳态锚点。","在这个复现问题解决前，不切换 optimizer，不改 K，也不改任何额外成本轴。"],"notes_to_memory":["兼容性判断：`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 为扩展兼容；导出形式仍是 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + residual 字典库的有限加权和。","EF=2 已满足选择成本硬约束，当前 frontier 可行点为 cost≈1.25x、FVU≈0.05811。","本轮严格遵守单变量原则；虽然 env_overrides 不变，但主问题是 `clean_baseline` 复现，而不是继续同时改变 LR 或其他轴。重点继续检查曲线形状、`tokens_per_sec`、总耗时和 `final_total_tokens`。"],"primary_variable":"clean_baseline","self_review":"这符合当前主线顺序。EF 已确认可行，clean baseline 已对 `LR=2.4e-3` 做过，Round 114 又给出了更优的 `LR=3.0e-3` 候选，因此现在最小且可归因的动作是复现该新候选，而不是继续上探学习率或过早切换优化器。没有引入第二个变量，结论最干净。","summary":"复现当前更优的低成本主线配方 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual / EF=2 / K=128 / signum / LR=3.0e-3`，确认它是否是稳定的新 frontier 点，而不是一次性波动。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4478:research/history/logs/agent_action_0031.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Within the `gated` mainline at `K=128, EF=12, optimizer=signum`, a conservative LR step down from `1.6e-3` to `1.2e-3` may improve stability and early-to-mid training curve smoothness enough to beat the current `0.149866` result; this round asks only whether the matched `gated` recipe is slightly overdriven at the reference LR.","summary":"Round 30's clean-baseline proposal was rejected by policy, so the next valid mainline move is the first LR callback while holding family, K, EF, and optimizer fixed. This stays on `gated`, changes only LR, and is explicitly aimed at reading the curve shape: if `1.2e-3` descends more smoothly and avoids late flattening or noise while matching or improving terminal FVU, keep sweeping LR inside `gated`; if it is simply slower and worse throughout, the reference LR remains the right anchor.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"small","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This obeys the one-variable rule by changing only LR, keeps EF at 12 and K at 128, and follows the prescribed mainline order after the clean-baseline step was unavailable. I am not changing optimizer yet because LR remains the highest-value unresolved variable inside the current gated recipe.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.2e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 31 starts the gated LR sweep because the clean-baseline rerun was policy-rejected; first callback is downward to LR=1.2e-3 with all other recipe fields fixed.","Judge the run by trajectory shape as well as terminal FVU: smoother monotone descent with equal/better finish supports gated at lower LR; uniformly slower/worse suggests 1.6e-3 was already near-correct."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated` at LR=1.2e-3 is smoother and at least as good, try one upward/downward bracket endpoint next to localize the LR optimum.","If `gated` at LR=1.2e-3 is clearly worse across the curve, keep `1.6e-3` as the gated anchor and consider optimizer swap next."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4479:research/history/logs/agent_action_0003.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 2 的 6e-4 明显劣于 8e-4，说明当前 topk/signum 主线更像是欠步长而不是过冲；本轮只把学习率上调到 1e-3，检验更积极的步长是否能在相同 family/optimizer/K 下带来更快且仍稳定的收敛，并刷新 K=128 的 FVU。","summary":"继续围绕 topk 主线推进，不开新 family，不换优化器，不动 K。本轮唯一主变量仍是 LR：从参考配方 8e-4 上调到 1e-3，回答“signum+topk 在当前设置下是否更需要稍大的学习率”这个单一问题。","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"这轮保持单变量且遵循主线顺序，先把 LR 维度补全到高于 baseline 的一侧，再决定是否切 optimizer。风险是 1e-3 可能带来震荡，但这正是本轮要验证的核心问题；若曲线恶化，后续就有充分理由结束 signum 的 LR 扫描并转向 optimizer 对比。","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 3 继续只调 LR，补完 signum 在 baseline 以上一侧的步长测试。","r2 的 6e-4 比 baseline 更差，初步说明问题不像是 LR 过大，更可能是步长偏小导致收敛不足。","本轮重点看曲线是否出现更快下降且仍稳定；若 1e-3 出现明显震荡或最终更差，就可结束 signum 的主线 LR 扫描并转向 optimizer 比较。"],"next_hypotheses":["如果 1e-3 优于 8e-4，下一轮继续只调 LR，在 8e-4 到 1e-3 之间或略高处做细化。","如果 1e-3 与 8e-4 接近但更不稳，下一轮可结束 signum 的 LR 扫描，按顺序只改 optimizer。","如果 1e-3 明显更差且有震荡，说明 signum 的合适 LR 区间已基本摸清，下一轮应切到 optimizer 维度。"],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4494:research/history/logs/agent_action_0098.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 97 showed that lowering `LR` to `1.6e-3` on the confirmed `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128 baseline was slightly worse, so the next single mainline question is the symmetric upward signum LR probe. Raising `LR` to `2.4e-3` tests whether this family benefits from a bit more step size for faster early and mid descent without destabilizing late training; the result should be judged from the whole curve against the archived `2.0e-3` and `1.6e-3` runs, not just the terminal FVU.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the required LR-localization sequence: same family, same `K`, same optimizer, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` pinned, and exactly one primary variable changes. The main risk is overshooting a recipe that may already be near its best at `2.0e-3`, but this is the clean remaining LR question before it is defensible to close the signum LR branch and move to optimizer.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 98 is the symmetric upward signum LR probe for the confirmed `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128 baseline after `LR=1.6e-3` regressed.","Judge this run by the full trajectory versus the archived `LR=2.0e-3` and `LR=1.6e-3` runs, especially whether the higher step size improves early or mid descent without degrading late stability or final FVU.","Only after this LR bracket is resolved should the optimizer branch open on this family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=2.4e-3` clearly improves curve shape or endpoint versus `2.0e-3`, archive it as the new signum mainline LR for `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`.","If `LR=2.4e-3` is a near-tie or worse, close the signum LR branch with `2.0e-3` as the operative anchor and test `OPTIMIZER=adam` next at the reference recipe.","Do not change loss, preprocess, or `K` until the optimizer question has been isolated cleanly from the settled signum baseline."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4501:research/history/logs/agent_action_0169.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary; JumpReLU only changes the single-sample support/coef shaping before top-k, not the exported decoder basis. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a fixed residual vector library, with the learned thresholds used only in online selection. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost should stay within the `≤ 1.5×h×n` hard budget and remain below the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline. The single question is whether this thresholded low-rank single-stage selector is intrinsically worth keeping in the current low-EF deployable regime, or whether the mainline’s soft-codebook plus two-stage refinement remains clearly necessary.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is clearly worse than the mainline in both FVU and runtime metrics, discard it and return to `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round.","If it is somewhat worse in FVU but materially better in throughput or total runtime, record it as a lower-complexity compatible side branch, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy.","If it is unexpectedly close to the mainline at lower selection cost, allow at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: `扩展兼容`. Export path is `U(Vx)` trunk lookup plus one sparse residual lookup over a fixed decoder library; JumpReLU modifies only selector thresholds, not decoder exportability.","This round is a strict matched architecture probe: keep `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` explicitly pinned, and change only `ARCHITECTURE`.","Judge family worthiness using `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside final FVU, because LUTurbo cares about total online/runtime cost rather than FVU alone."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe fields. After `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` and `lowrank_gated_residual` both failed to pressure the mainline, `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is the highest-value remaining feasible matched probe because it preserves LUTurbo exportability, stays in the low-EF budgeted regime, and tests a simpler thresholded selector that could reduce total online complexity if quality holds up. The main risk is that historical evidence for JumpReLU-style selectors has been weak, so this may mainly confirm that a single-stage thresholded low-rank branch cannot recover enough quality.","summary":"Run one valid matched architecture probe on `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` while keeping the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether a thresholded single-stage low-rank selector is worth any continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4525:research/history/logs/agent_action_0086.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` and `lowrank_residual_vq` both failed to pressure the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, the most informative single matched architecture probe is `lowrank_jumprelu_residual`. It preserves the same low-rank static-library export path while collapsing the selector back to a single residual pass with thresholded support selection, which is more promising for LUTurbo's total online cost (`selection + coeffs + lookup + compensation`) than another multi-stage or routed variant. If it is still clearly weaker under the exact matched `K=128, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=2.0e-3, EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then this simpler low-rank single-stage family is not worth continuing in the current regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the round rule by changing exactly one primary variable: `architecture`. I kept the current mainline recipe fixed, explicitly pinned `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and chose a candidate that is LUTurbo-compatible and meaningfully simpler online than the current two-stage mainline. Risk: older low-K evidence for this family was weak, so this may just confirm that the simpler single-stage thresholded selector cannot retain enough quality at matched K128.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 86 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Judge this run as a family-worthiness test for a simpler low-rank single-stage thresholded selector that may reduce LUTurbo online selection and compensation cost; return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, discard it and resume mainline tuning on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` next round.","If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a viable lower-online-complexity branch but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4538:research/history/logs/agent_action_0147.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.3e-3"}],"expected_win":"confirm_signal","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk 基库 U、soft codebook 静态库 {c_m}、以及两阶段 residual 静态字典库 {b_i} 都可离线导出，因此可直接映射到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 时 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。r145 表明把 signum 学习率从主线参考值 3.0e-3 小幅上调到 3.3e-3 后，FVU 从 0.058106 降到 0.057939，且总耗时未恶化；r146 的 policy_reject 说明不能把这一步包装成 clean baseline，本轮必须继续作为单变量 LR 问题处理。本轮只回答一个问题：相对于当前主线参考配方的 LR=3.0e-3，把 LR 改为 3.3e-3 的收益是否可重复成立，并且不会以更差的 tokens_per_sec、总耗时或 final_total_tokens 为代价。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 LR=3.3e-3 再次优于 3.0e-3，且运行代价基本不变，则可把 3.3e-3 视为新的 signum 主线锚点，后续再决定是否继续微调或转入 optimizer/成本轴。","若 LR=3.3e-3 回落到 3.0e-3 基线附近，则说明 r145 更可能是噪声收益，后续应关闭上探并保守回到 3.0e-3。","若 LR=3.3e-3 只带来极小收益但显著拖慢训练，则将其视为负面 recipe 信号，不再继续围绕更高 LR 上探。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 仍是当前兼容 frontier 上质量最强的可行主线，导出形式未变，继续属于扩展兼容。","r145 首次在 EF=2/K=128/signum 主线上得到 0.057939，因此当前最有价值的问题是确认这个 LR 信号是否可复现。","r146 的 policy_reject 表明必须把 3.3e-3 继续视为 LR 轴单变量问题，而不是以 clean baseline 名义提交。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：只改 LR，family、EF、K、optimizer 与导出形式全部固定，不混入成本轴、loss 轴或新的结构变化。这样既符合当前推荐顺序，也避开了 r146 暴露出的 clean-baseline 包装问题。风险是再次运行 3.3e-3 可能只复现到接近 3.0e-3 的结果，因此评估时必须同时看完整曲线、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，而不是只看最终 FVU。","summary":"继续围绕当前主线 family 推进，不开新 family；将 r145 的 3.3e-3 结果当作单变量 LR 信号而非新 baseline，保持 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、signum 不变，再运行一次 LR=3.3e-3，确认该小幅上调是否能稳定优于参考配方的 3.0e-3。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4556:research/history/logs/agent_action_0034.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `gated` mainline anchored back at `K=128, EF=12, optimizer=signum, lr=1.6e-3`, adding a small auxiliary sparsity-support loss via `auxk_alpha=0.03125` may improve training dynamics without changing the family or optimizer; this round asks only whether a light loss-shaping term reduces plateauing and yields a better full-curve profile than the plain baseline.","summary":"The optimizer branch already failed once (`adam` at the matched LR), and the follow-up Adam LR callback was policy-rejected, so the next valid mainline move is to return to the proven `signum` anchor and test one loss-side variable. Keep architecture, K, EF, optimizer, and LR fixed, and introduce a small `auxk_alpha` rather than a large perturbation. Evaluate the whole trajectory: if early progress is steadier and the run finishes at or below the current `0.149866`, loss shaping is worth keeping in play; if the curve is uniformly worse or distorts convergence, drop aux loss and preserve the plain gated recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, keeps EF fixed at 12, does not touch K, and changes exactly one main variable: `auxk_alpha`. It also respects the prescribed order by moving to a loss-side probe only after the basic LR and optimizer checks have not yielded an improvement.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 34 returns to the gated+signum anchor and begins the loss-side probe with a small aux term: AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125.","Judge this run by curve shape as well as endpoint; if aux loss does not help the trajectory or finish, drop it and avoid broad loss sweeps."],"next_hypotheses":["If `auxk_alpha=0.03125` improves the curve or endpoint, test one nearby aux setting to see whether the benefit is robust or over-tuned.","If the aux-loss run is clearly worse, revert to the plain gated anchor and only then consider a preprocess-side change before touching K."],"primary_variable":"loss"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4557:research/history/logs/agent_action_0087.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `lowrank_residual_vq`, and `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` all failing to challenge the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, the highest-value remaining matched architecture probe is `lowrank_gated_residual`. It keeps the same low-rank trunk and static-library export contract, but replaces the two-stage residual path with a single gated residual selector that is materially simpler for LUTurbo online execution. If this simpler low-rank gated family is still clearly weaker under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then the current evidence favors keeping the two-stage residual structure rather than continuing single-stage low-rank selector variants.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_gated_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the matched architecture probe rule by changing only `architecture` and keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. `lowrank_gated_residual` is a cleaner LUTurbo-aligned probe than another multi-stage or codebook-heavy family because it preserves static exportability while potentially lowering online selection and compensation complexity. The risk is that earlier low-K history for this family was weak, so this round may mainly confirm that simpler single-stage low-rank gating cannot retain the mainline quality at K128.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 87 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for a simpler low-rank single-stage gated selector with potentially lower LUTurbo online cost; return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, discard it and resume mainline tuning on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` next round.","If `lowrank_gated_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a viable lower-complexity branch but still return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4558:research/history/logs/agent_action_0037.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Because `gated` beat the matched `topk` control at `K=96`, the next single question is whether that advantage extends one more step down the support ladder; testing `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=64, EF=12, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=1.6e-3` will show whether `gated` is broadly stronger across high-K frontier points or only wins near the very top end.","summary":"Round 36 changed the picture: `gated@96` is not just viable, it improved the frontier over the existing `topk@96` control, so the family has earned one more K-mapping round. Keep the anchored recipe fixed and step only `K` from `96` to `64`. This directly answers whether the `gated` advantage generalizes to the next adjacent frontier point. Read the full curve, not just the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes below the `topk@64` control (`0.1992608`), `gated` is a real high-K mainline candidate; if it drops back behind `topk`, then the family likely helps only in the upper-K regime.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the current family, keeps EF fixed at 12, and changes exactly one main variable: `K`. It follows the prescribed ordering because recipe tuning was already exhausted before K moves began, and `K=64` is the highest-value next probe after the successful `K=96` result.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 36 established that gated generalizes beyond K=128 by beating the matched topk control at K=96.","Round 37 should probe the next adjacent K point, gated@64 with the same signum/LR anchor, to test whether the advantage persists deeper into the frontier."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated@64` also beats `topk@64`, continue one more downward K probe because gated is shaping up as the stronger mainline family across multiple frontier points.","If `gated@64` falls back behind `topk@64`, treat gated as a high-K specialist and preserve it mainly for K>=96."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4559:research/history/logs/agent_action_0143.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 architecture 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 是单个静态字典库上的固定向量，alpha_i 为选出的稀疏系数，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为直接兼容。与当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 相比，factorized_topk 不再使用 trunk、soft codebook 或两阶段 refinement，而是用低秩 scorer 做单库稀疏选择，仍保持静态库有限加权和的部署形式；在 EF=2 下其 encoder selection_cost 约 0.38x h×n，显著低于当前主线的约 1.25x，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束，部署侧也只需单库 sparse lookup。本轮只回答一个 matched architecture probe 问题：在 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 完全不变时，这种更激进的低秩单库选择机制是否值得继续，还是它在当前低 EF regime 下会因表示能力不足而明显落后于现有 soft-codebook/two-stage 主线。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 factorized_topk 在大幅降低 selection_cost 的同时仅有有限 FVU 损失，则保留它作为低成本 LUTurbo 候选，但下一轮按策略回到主线 family。","若 factorized_topk 的 FVU 明显落后于 lowrank_residual 与 soft-codebook 系，则说明低秩单库 scorer 在当前 regime 下不值得继续，后续不再占用主线 probe 轮次。","若 factorized_topk 虽然更便宜但训练吞吐或总耗时没有优势，则将其视为负面系统信号，而不是仅凭低 selection_cost 继续推进。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮是 Round 143 唯一允许的 matched architecture probe，严格保持 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变，只改 architecture。","r141 与 r142 已表明去掉 second stage、再去掉 soft codebook 都会出现阶梯式质量退化，因此本轮改测一条更低成本但机制不同的直接兼容候选，判断非全字典低秩 scorer 是否值得保留。","评估时必须同时比较 FVU、selection_cost、deploy cost、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，避免只按终点 SAE 指标判断架构价值。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"遵守单变量原则与本轮 probe 约束：只改 architecture，未联动 K、EF、optimizer、LR 或其他 recipe。选择 factorized_topk，是因为它在 EF=2 下 selection_cost 明显低于当前所有兼容 frontier 点，且属于直接兼容的单库静态表示，能直接回答“更激进的低秩单库选择机制是否值得继续”这一独立架构问题。风险是该 family 在旧的高 EF regime 曾明显偏弱，但当前低 EF 成本约束已发生 regime shift，这正是本轮 probe 的信息价值所在。","summary":"插入一个严格匹配的架构探针：把当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 换成更低成本、直接兼容的 factorized_topk，其余 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 全部保持不变，用一次干净对照判断低秩单库选择机制在当前 LUTurbo 成本约束下是否仍值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4569:research/history/round_summaries/round_0053.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 52 was policy-rejected because it tried to retune `LR` on `gated@4`, which implicitly changed both `lr` and `k` relative to the family reference recipe. The corrected next single question is therefore to retune `LR` exactly on the current `gated` anchor itself: with `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=128, EF=12, OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed and the now-proven `USE_HADAMARD=1` preprocessing kept on, does raising `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3` improve the full curve further, or is `2.0e-3` still the best step size even after Hadamard strengthened conditioning?",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4570:research/history/round_summaries/round_0053.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and return to the family reference point so the round passes single-variable policy cleanly. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if Hadamard has genuinely widened the stable step-size range, `2.4e-3` should preserve or improve early and mid descent and finish below the current `0.142923` anchor; if the curve gets flatter, noisier, or regresses, keep `2.0e-3` as the operative shared recipe and stop the LR branch again.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4575:research/history/round_summaries/round_0053.json:104:    "description": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and return to the family reference point so the round passes single-variable policy cleanly. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if Hadamard has genuinely widened the stable step-size range, `2.4e-3` should preserve or improve early and mid descent and finish below the current `0.142923` anchor; if the curve gets flatter, noisier, or regresses, keep `2.0e-3` as the operative shared recipe and stop the LR branch again.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4577:research/history/logs/agent_action_0148.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.6e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可映射到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。r145 与 r147 在相同 family/K/EF/optimizer 下两次复现了 LR=3.3e-3 的更优终点 FVU=0.0579389，相比 3.0e-3 baseline 的 0.0581064 是稳定正信号；同时 r147 的更长耗时主要来自 tokens_per_sec 从约 166.5k 降到 66.6k，而 final_total_tokens 仍是 59,969,536，说明这次变慢更像运行时吞吐波动，不应提前终止 LR 轴。本轮只回答一个问题：在保持 family、EF、K、optimizer 与导出形式不变的前提下，把 signum 学习率从 3.3e-3 继续上探到 3.6e-3，是否还能延续中后段收敛改善并进一步压低 FVU，还是已经开始进入过冲区间。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 3.6e-3 终点继续优于 3.3e-3 且曲线未出现更早平台或震荡，则补一轮 clean repeat 确认新的 signum 主线 LR。","若 3.6e-3 与 3.3e-3 持平或更差，则关闭 signum LR 上探分支，把 3.3e-3 视为当前主线最优配方。","若 3.6e-3 明显过冲或训练曲线变差，则停止继续加大学习率，后续只在已确认的 3.3e-3 锚点上考虑其余单变量轴。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 的导出形式未变，仍属扩展兼容，可继续作为 LUTurbo 主线 family。","EF=2 继续满足 selection_cost 预算；K 保持 128，避免把部署查表成本变化与 LR 轴混杂。","r145 与 r147 已把 3.3e-3 从一次性噪声提升为可复现信号；r147 的慢速更像吞吐异常而非训练更长。","近期一些成本侧参数改动出现与 baseline 完全相同的终点与 token 轨迹，后续若再走成本轴，应先确认这些 override 在执行链路中的实际生效情况。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：只改 LR，family、EF、K、optimizer 全部固定在当前主线参考配方。相比再开 optimizer 或 loss/preprocess 分支，这一步更符合当前主线推进要求，因为 3.3e-3 已给出稳定改善而其上界仍未确认。主要风险是 3.6e-3 只是更激进而不更好，因此评估时必须同时看完整曲线、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，而不是只看最终 FVU。","summary":"继续围绕主线 family 推进，不开新 family；在 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、signum 固定的前提下，仅把 LR 从已复现改善的 3.3e-3 上调到 3.6e-3，判断 signum 上探是否还能进一步降低 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4584:research/history/logs/agent_action_0106.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 104 and 105 established a clean, repeatable `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128 baseline at `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, so the next single mainline question is the first within-family learning-rate probe. Lowering `LR` to `1.6e-3` tests whether this two-stage soft-codebook recipe is slightly underdamped and could trade a bit of early speed for better late-stage descent and a lower terminal FVU; the decision should come from the whole curve shape versus the archived baseline, not just the last point.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the required sequence after confirming the new baseline: stay on the same family, keep `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and change exactly one primary variable, `lr`. The main risk is that `1.6e-3` may simply slow a recipe already well tuned at `2.0e-3`, but this is the cleanest first LR-localization question before considering an upward probe or opening the optimizer branch.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 106 is the first LR probe for the confirmed `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline baseline at `K=128`, `EF=12`, and `signum`.","Judge this run by the full trajectory against the archived `LR=2.0e-3` baseline, especially whether the lower step size improves late descent or only slows the whole curve.","If `LR=1.6e-3` regresses or converges too slowly, the next LR probe should return upward rather than continuing downward."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=1.6e-3` improves endpoint or late-curve shape versus `2.0e-3`, archive it as the new mainline LR for `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`.","If `LR=1.6e-3` is clearly slower or worse, test only the symmetric upward probe at `LR=2.4e-3` next before opening the optimizer branch.","Do not change optimizer, loss, preprocess, or `K` until the signum LR bracket is localized."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4585:research/history/logs/agent_action_0162.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 probe family 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 是单个静态字典库上的固定向量，alpha_i 是单样本 top-k 选出的稀疏系数，因此最终表示是单静态向量库上的有限加权和，可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为直接兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 0.5x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束，并显著低于当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 的约 1.25x。本轮严格保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 与主要 recipe 不变，只将 architecture 从 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 改为 topk，回答唯一问题：在当前低 EF 可部署 regime 下，这条最朴素、最低复杂度的单库稀疏路线是否仍值得继续，还是其表示能力会明显落后于带 trunk、soft-codebook 和 staged refinement 的主线结构。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 topk 明显落后于当前主线，则说明最简单单库稀疏路线在当前 regime 下不值得继续，下一轮回到主线。","若 topk 与当前主线差距小于预期且运行代价更优，则记录其为更简单的低成本备选，但下一轮仍按要求回到主线。","若 topk 意外优于当前主线，则说明当前主线 family 的系统级收益需要重新审视，但本轮仅做架构价值判断，不连续展开新 family。"],"notes_to_memory":["topk 满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性为直接兼容。","本轮严格是 matched architecture probe：EF、K、optimizer、LR 与主要 recipe 全部固定，只改 architecture。","r159-r161 已依次检验去掉 second stage、去掉 soft-codebook coarse branch、以及更低成本 factorized 单库路线的价值；本轮补充最朴素直接兼容单库 baseline，完成当前低 EF regime 下的主干结构对照。","评估时必须同时检查 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，避免把质量差异与吞吐波动混淆。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这轮遵守架构探针规则，只改一个主变量 architecture，并保持主线的 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变。选择 topk 是因为它是当前尚未在这一严格 matched 配方下补齐的最简单直接兼容基线，能用一次最低复杂度对照回答“主线结构是否真的必要”这个剩余问题。","summary":"插入一个严格匹配的架构探针：将当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 替换为 topk，其余 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 全部保持不变，用一轮干净对照判断这种最简单的直接兼容单库架构是否值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4586:research/history/logs/agent_action_0133.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"32"}],"expected_win":"pareto_cost_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 low-rank trunk 基库 U、soft codebook 库 {c_m}、两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都是静态可导出的固定向量库，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。当前 family 在 EF=2 时已满足 selection_cost ≤ 1.5×h×n，本轮不再继续无收益的 LR/loss 试探，而只改一个部署相关主变量：将 TRUNK_RANK 下调到 32，测试是否能在进一步降低 encoder selection_cost 与 trunk/codebook deploy 成本的同时，把 FVU 保持在接近当前 0.0581 的水平，从而形成新的 cost-FVU Pareto 点。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 TRUNK_RANK=32 能明显降成本且 FVU 仅小幅退化，可继续细扫更低或中间 rank 以压出新的 Pareto 前沿。","若 TRUNK_RANK=32 的 FVU 明显恶化，则说明当前 trunk 容量已接近下限，后续应回到默认 rank 并改测 NUM_CODES。","若 TRUNK_RANK=32 与 baseline 几乎等价且吞吐更好，则可将更低 rank 视为新的 clean baseline，再继续 recipe 搜索。"],"notes_to_memory":["LUTurbo 导出形式未变，family 仍为扩展兼容。","EF=2 继续保证选择成本在硬约束内；本轮通过降低 TRUNK_RANK 探索更低成本 Pareto，而不是追求单点最优 FVU。","r132 表明 AUXK_ALPHA=0.0 与 baseline 基本等价，因此暂时结束 loss 轴试探，转向更有系统价值的成本轴。"],"primary_variable":"trunk_rank","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：family、EF、K、optimizer、LR 均固定，只改 TRUNK_RANK。该动作直接服务于 LUTurbo 的真实目标，因为它同时触碰 encoder 选择成本与部署 trunk 成本；风险是 trunk 容量下降可能导致 coarse branch 表达不足，因此必须结合 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和最终 token 数一起判断是否值得保留。","summary":"在低成本可行主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 上做一次成本轴探索：固定 EF=2、K=128、signum、LR=3.0e-3，仅把 TRUNK_RANK 下调到 32，判断能否以更低 selection/deploy 成本维持接近当前 frontier 的重构质量。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4637:research/history/logs/agent_action_0177.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3.0e-3`). Final reconstruction remains `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j`; routing only perturbs stage-1/stage-2 support selection scores, while all decoded terms still come from static trunk, codebook, and residual libraries. This is `扩展兼容` because LUTurbo/Lottable can export the low-rank trunk matrices, soft codebook vectors, and residual dictionary once, then execute `trunk lookup + codebook lookup + routed support selection + weighted sparse lookups + sum` online. The key question is whether router-driven support allocation is worth continuing in the low-EF feasible regime. Current cost accounting strongly suggests no: adding two full routers likely pushes encoder selection cost above the `1.5x h×n` hard cap, so the most informative outcome is a quick policy gate that rules this family out as a mainline candidate at `EF=2`.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune exactly one cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.","If this routed matched probe is policy-rejected as expected, mark routed two-stage soft-codebook as not worth continuing in the current low-cost regime unless a future single-variable cost-reduction round explicitly targets router cost."],"notes_to_memory":["`routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is LUTurbo `扩展兼容`: routing changes selector logic only; decode path is still a finite weighted sum over static trunk/codebook/residual libraries.","At matched `K=128, EF=2`, routed two-stage soft-codebook is expected to exceed the encoder-cost cap because the two router projections add substantial full-dictionary selection cost on top of the mainline scorer.","Treat a fast policy rejection here as a useful architectural conclusion, not a runtime failure: the family is exportable but not cost-viable in the current feasible regime."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Single-variable discipline is preserved: only `ARCHITECTURE` changes, while `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, and `LR` remain fixed to the mainline recipe. This probe is intentionally chosen to answer a clean architectural question under the new budget regime: whether routing is inherently worth carrying forward once low-EF cost feasibility is enforced.","summary":"Probe `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` as the one matched architecture change. It is LUTurbo-exportable (`扩展兼容`) by the same static-library decomposition as the mainline, but is likely to be ruled out quickly because the extra routers make encoder selection cost exceed the hard budget, which would mean this family is not worth continuing on the current Pareto frontier.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4638:research/history/logs/agent_action_0045.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 44 cleanly reproduced the Hadamard-enabled `gated` improvement at `K=128`, so that preprocess gain is now stable enough to treat as the operative recipe rather than a one-off. The next single question is therefore K transfer under the improved recipe: if we keep `gated`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EF=12`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed and step down only to `K=96`, does the stronger recipe preserve or extend `gated`'s advantage at the next lower support where online cost is meaningfully lower?","summary":"Adopt the reproduced Hadamard recipe as the current `gated` reference and begin K mapping under that stronger setting. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `K` from `128` to `96`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory as well as the endpoint: if the improved recipe yields a smooth curve and clearly beats the old `gated@96` control (`0.168960`), then the preprocess gain transfers to a lower-cost point and the family deserves at least one more K step; if it falls back toward the earlier K96 result or loses its curve advantage, keep the improved recipe mainly as a K128 anchor.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `k`. The clean Hadamard confirmation in Round 44 closes the recipe-clarification loop, so moving to K is now the most policy-clean next action. The main risk is that the K128 improvement may not transfer downward, but that is precisely the high-value deployment question this round answers.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Rounds 43 and 44 jointly established that `USE_HADAMARD=1` is a reproducible improvement for `gated@128` under `signum, LR=2.0e-3`, so this recipe is now stable enough to use for K mapping.","Round 45 transfers the improved `gated` recipe to `K=96` to test whether the K128 preprocess gain also buys a better lower-cost point rather than only improving the largest-support anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If the improved `gated@96` run beats the old K96 control with a similarly healthy curve, continue down to `K=64` under the same recipe.","If `gated@96` fails to improve materially under the stronger recipe, treat the Hadamard gain as mostly a K128 effect and avoid a long downward K sweep without new evidence."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4639:research/history/logs/agent_action_0064.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `gated` mainline stalled for eleven rounds and the lighter selector probes `group_topk` and `bucketed_topk` both coming back clearly worse, the next highest-value matched architecture probe is `codebook_topk`: it remains LUTurbo-compatible because the reconstruction is still a finite sum over static libraries, but it changes the architecture by adding a hard coarse codebook selection before the sparse residual. This round answers one question only: under the matched `K=128`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EF=12` recipe, is `codebook_topk` intrinsically strong enough to justify any later follow-up, or should it be ruled out immediately.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `codebook_topk` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"codebook_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 64 policy by changing exactly one primary variable: architecture. `codebook_topk` is a better remaining probe than batch-coupled variants because it stays single-sample deployable, and it is more informative than heavier multi-branch gating because it tests a distinct static-library decomposition pattern that could plausibly trade some sparse support work for a coarse lookup plus residual correction.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"codebook_topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 64 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `codebook_topk` after `group_topk` and `bucketed_topk` both failed to beat the matched `gated` control.","`codebook_topk` is extended-compatible with LUTurbo because the final reconstruction can be exported as a hard-selected static coarse codebook vector plus a finite weighted sum over a static residual decoder library.","Judge this probe strictly as a family-worthiness test against matched `gated` K128: if it is clearly worse, discard it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, record the result but still return to the mainline per policy."],"next_hypotheses":["If `codebook_topk` is clearly worse than matched `gated`, discard the family and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","If `codebook_topk` is roughly competitive, record it as a possible coarse-plus-residual deployment direction but still return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy.","If `codebook_topk` unexpectedly beats matched `gated`, schedule at most one later follow-up after the mandated return to the `gated` mainline."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4644:research/history/logs/agent_action_0183.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"NUM_CODES","value":"64"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 low-rank trunk 库 U、静态 soft codebook 库 {c_m}、两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都可静态导出，因此可直接映射到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。r182 在只把 NUM_CODES 从默认 256 降到 128 时，FVU 与整条训练曲线都基本不变，说明当前 coarse codebook 仍有明显冗余。本轮只回答一个问题：把 NUM_CODES 继续降到 64，是否仍能基本保持主线质量，同时进一步降低 code_router、codebook_matmul 与 codebook_deploy 的总成本，从而改善 LUTurbo 可部署 Pareto 点。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 NUM_CODES=64 仍接近 0.0581 且吞吐/总耗时不恶化，则继续沿 codebook size 轴下探，或把 64 作为新的低成本 clean mainline。","若 NUM_CODES=64 出现明显 FVU 退化，则说明 128 已接近 coarse branch 下限，下一轮回到 NUM_CODES=128 并改测 TRUNK_RANK。","若 FVU 基本不变但 tokens_per_sec 再次异常下滑，则优先把该现象视为运行时噪声信号，而不是结构负面结论。"],"notes_to_memory":["`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 在 `NUM_CODES=64` 下导出路径不变，仍是 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + two-stage residual 字典库的有限加权和。","r182 已表明 `NUM_CODES=128` 相对 baseline 几乎零质量损失，因此继续缩小 codebook 是当前最干净的单变量成本推进。","评估本轮必须同时检查 curve_start/mid/end、tokens_per_sec、总耗时、final_total_tokens，确认收益来自真实成本下降而非运行时漂移。"],"primary_variable":"other_param","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：family、EF、K、optimizer、LR 全部固定，只继续沿 `NUM_CODES` 这一主成本旋钮推进。相比重复测过的 TRUNK_RANK，这一步更直接触碰 coarse branch 的选择成本和部署查表成本，且与 r182 形成自然的连续主线。","summary":"继续主线 family，不开新架构；固定 `K=128, EF=2, signum, LR=3.0e-3`，仅把 `NUM_CODES` 从 128 再降到 64，验证 coarse codebook 是否还能继续压缩而不明显伤害 FVU，从而进一步降低 LUTurbo 的总在线成本。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4672:research/history/logs/agent_action_0108.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 107 was the first signum LR probe on `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` to beat the archived `LR=2.0e-3` K128 baseline, so before opening the optimizer branch the next single question should be whether `LR=2.4e-3` is a reproducible new anchor rather than a one-off improvement. Re-running the exact `LR=2.4e-3` recipe is the cleanest way to judge whether the full curve remains stronger than the `LR=2.0e-3` and `LR=1.6e-3` runs, especially in early/mid descent and late stability, rather than trusting the endpoint alone.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and rerun the promising higher-LR recipe with `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.4e-3`, changing no other recipe variable.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"confirm_baseline","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays within the same family, keeps `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and isolates the only unresolved mainline recipe axis: whether `LR=2.4e-3` is the right signum operating point. The tradeoff is spending one more round before opening the optimizer branch, but that is justified because optimizer comparisons should use a settled signum anchor rather than an unconfirmed one-off LR win.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 108 retries the improved `LR=2.4e-3` signum probe for `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=128` and `EF=12` to determine whether the gain over `LR=2.0e-3` is reproducible.","Judge this run by curve-shape repeatability versus the archived `LR=2.0e-3`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and Round 107 `LR=2.4e-3` runs, not by endpoint alone.","Only after resolving whether `LR=2.4e-3` is a stable signum anchor should the optimizer branch open on this family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=2.4e-3` reproduces the stronger curve or endpoint, promote it to the operative signum mainline LR and test `OPTIMIZER=adam` next at that settled recipe.","If the `LR=2.4e-3` repeat falls back to a near-tie or worse than `LR=2.0e-3`, close the signum LR branch with `LR=2.0e-3` as the operative anchor and test `OPTIMIZER=adam` next there.","Do not change loss, preprocess, or `K` until the optimizer question has been isolated from the settled signum baseline."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4678:research/history/logs/agent_action_0158.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"该 family 的最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 U(Vx) 可离线导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终重构仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。r157 已在当前低 EF 主线下再次给出 adam 的爆炸性负信号，因此 optimizer 分支可视为已被明确关闭。按推荐顺序，下一步应转向 loss/preprocess 轴；本轮只回答一个问题：在保持 family、EF、K、主优化器和 LR 不变的前提下，完全去掉 auxiliary K loss（AUXK_ALPHA=0.0）是否能减少对主重构目标的干扰，带来更好的曲线形状或至少确认该辅助项在当前可部署 regime 下已无必要。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 AUXK_ALPHA=0.0 在不恶化吞吐与总时长的前提下改善曲线或终点，则下一轮做一次同配方 clean repeat 确认。","若 AUXK_ALPHA=0.0 与基线几乎等价，则记录 auxiliary loss 在该 regime 下非关键，随后再考虑更贴近系统成本的 K 轴。","若 AUXK_ALPHA=0.0 明显退化，则恢复默认辅助项并结束 loss 轴试探。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 继续满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性仍为扩展兼容。","EF=2 下 selection_cost 仍在预算内；本轮不改 EF、K、TRUNK_RANK、NUM_CODES 或其他成本轴，只隔离 auxiliary loss 效应。","r157 在当前主线 regime 下再次复现了 adam 的强负信号，optimizer 分支应正式关闭。","评估本轮必须同时记录 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，区分是否存在由训练更长或吞吐异常造成的假信号。"],"primary_variable":"auxk_alpha","self_review":"这轮严格只改一个主变量 AUXK_ALPHA，family、EF、K、optimizer、LR 全部固定，符合单变量原则。当前策略顺序在 optimizer 之后本就应转向 loss/preprocess，而 r157 已把 optimizer 问题回答得足够清楚；因此继续停留在 optimizer 分支价值很低，不如用最小改动检查辅助损失在当前低成本主线中的必要性。","summary":"继续围绕主线 family 推进，不开新 family；在 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、signum、LR=3.0e-3 固定的前提下，仅将 AUXK_ALPHA 设为 0.0，判断去掉 auxiliary K loss 是否能改善当前可部署 regime 的训练曲线或确认其已无必要。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4679:research/history/logs/agent_action_0027.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 26 showed that disabling `COMPILE_MODEL` cleared the `first_step_timeout` and kept the K128 baseline in the same general FVU band, but with a small regression versus the compiled anchor. The next single question is whether the stabilized non-compiled path prefers a slightly different step size; this round changes only `LR`, lowering it from `1.6e-3` to `1.4e-3` while keeping the rest of the stabilized recipe fixed, to test whether the worse curve came from a mildly over-aggressive learning rate on the uncompiled path.","summary":"Continue on the active `topk` family without opening a new family. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and the Round 26 stabilized runtime settings fixed, and reduce `LR` from `1.6e-3` to `1.4e-3` to answer whether the non-compiled clean baseline recovers a smoother curve and lower final FVU with a slightly smaller step size.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the current mainline family, follows the requested order by returning to the LR axis after the clean-baseline stabilization pass, and changes exactly one core variable. The main risk is that `1.4e-3` was weaker on the earlier compiled path, but the point of this round is specifically to see whether the stabilized `COMPILE_MODEL=0` regime shifts the practical LR sweet spot rather than to assume the old compiled optimum still transfers unchanged.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.4e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 26 indicates that `COMPILE_MODEL=0` is a viable stabilization path for the K128 anchor because it avoided the timeout and stayed near the expected FVU band, even though it did not improve the frontier.","The next clean question is whether that stabilized runtime path wants a slightly smaller LR; treat this as an LR calibration of the non-compiled baseline rather than a direct replacement of the compiled historical anchor.","Judge this round by full curve shape as well as final FVU: if `1.4e-3` smooths late descent or recovers the small regression seen at Round 26, keep refining LR on the stabilized path; if not, the non-compiled path likely does not justify further LR tuning before moving to optimizer."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=1.4e-3` improves the stabilized K128 run, do one more narrow LR refinement on the same runtime path before switching optimizer.","If `LR=1.4e-3` is flat or worse, conclude that the stabilized path does not benefit from a lower step size and move to the optimizer axis next.","If the curve shape improves while final FVU stays similar, use that signal to decide whether runtime stability plus smoother training is worth further work even without a frontier gain."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4686:research/history/logs/agent_action_0180.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual_vq"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_residual_vq","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_residual_vq` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3.0e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library, `c_m` is one selected codebook vector from a static coarse library, and the residual term is a weighted sum over a static residual dictionary. This is `扩展兼容` because LUTurbo/Lottable can export the trunk factors, coarse codebook, and residual dictionary as static vector libraries, then run `trunk branch + coarse code lookup + sparse residual lookups + weighted sum` online. The single question for this probe is whether replacing the soft coarse branch with a hard VQ-style coarse branch is worth continuing in the low-EF feasible regime. This should stay inside the encoder-cost budget at `EF=2`, so it is likely to produce a real training/runtime signal rather than another policy reject.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune exactly one cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.","If `lowrank_residual_vq` underperforms the mainline on FVU or slows training without a compensating runtime/quality benefit, mark hard-VQ coarse branches as not worth continuing in the current low-cost regime."],"notes_to_memory":["`lowrank_residual_vq` is LUTurbo `扩展兼容`: decode is a finite weighted sum over static trunk vectors, one static coarse codebook entry, and static residual dictionary atoms.","This matched probe tests a meaningful architecture axis that has not been revisited recently in the current low-EF regime: soft coarse branch versus hard coarse branch.","Review `tokens_per_sec`, total runtime, and `final_total_tokens` alongside FVU; a small quality change with worse throughput should count against continuing the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Single-variable discipline is preserved: only `ARCHITECTURE` changes while `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, and `LR` remain fixed to the mainline recipe. This probe stays within the compatible family set, is likely budget-feasible, and answers a clean architectural question without drifting into another over-budget selector variant.","summary":"Probe `lowrank_residual_vq` as the one matched architecture change. It is LUTurbo-exportable (`扩展兼容`) through a static low-rank trunk, a static coarse codebook, and a static residual dictionary, and it tests whether a hard coarse branch is worth continuing versus the current soft-codebook two-stage mainline.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4698:research/history/logs/agent_action_0112.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j；其中 low-rank trunk、soft codebook、两阶段 residual 都是静态向量库上的有限加权和，可直接导出到 LUTurbo 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路，因此该 family 属于扩展兼容。单主变量改为 EXPANSION_FACTOR: 12 -> 2，可把该 family 的 selection_cost 压到约 1.16x h×n，回到 ≤1.5x 硬预算内，同时保留当前主线结构，回答“这个强 backbone 在最低可行 EF 下是否仍能以更低总在线成本给出比 factorized_topk 更好的 FVU/时延权衡”。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 EF=2 已可行且 FVU 仍明显优于 factorized_topk，则下一轮在同 family 上补 clean baseline，检查曲线是否仍在下降。","若 EF=2 曲线形状健康但收敛偏慢，则只调 LR 作为单变量。","若 EF=2 的 FVU 退化过大，则保留该 family 但转向单变量降低 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM 或 TRUNK_RANK，探索 EF=2 下更便宜 scorer 的最优点。"],"notes_to_memory":["兼容性：扩展兼容；导出形式为 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + residual 字典库的有限加权和。","本轮严格遵守单变量原则，只验证 EF 收缩后的成本可行性与低 EF 表达质量。","K 对选择成本几乎无影响，因此保持 K=128，不把成本变化和稀疏预算变化混在一起。"],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor","self_review":"这是当前策略要求下最小且可归因的主线动作：先把主线 family 拉回预算内，再看其低 EF regime 是否仍有竞争力。风险是 EF=2 可能让 FVU 明显恶化，但这正是本轮唯一要回答的问题。","summary":"继续主线 family，不开新架构。用参考配方 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual / K=128 / signum / LR=2.4e-3，仅将 EXPANSION_FACTOR 从 12 降到 2，先验证该扩展兼容结构在 LUTurbo 选择成本预算内的可行 Pareto 点。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4720:research/history/logs/agent_action_0144.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"confirm_baseline","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk 基库 U、soft codebook 静态库 {c_m}、以及两阶段 residual 静态字典库 {b_i} 都可离线导出，因此可直接映射到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 时 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。经过 r141-r143 的 matched architecture probes 后，当前已经重新确认 two-stage soft-codebook 主线在质量上显著优于 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual、lowrank_residual 与 factorized_topk，但这些 probe 的总耗时更短，说明近期运行代价结论可能混杂了架构差异而非主线 recipe 漂移。本轮只回答一个问题：回到主线参考配方 ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 做一次 clean baseline 复验，当前 feasible 主线的 FVU、训练曲线、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens 是否仍稳定可复现，从而为后续继续做主线 recipe 调整提供干净锚点。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 clean baseline 继续稳定复现 0.0581 附近且运行代价正常，则下一轮继续留在主线 family，优先做一个单变量 recipe 问题而不是继续开 architecture probe。","若 clean baseline 的吞吐或总耗时明显恶化而 FVU 不变，则优先把这视为运行时信号，而不是误判为主线架构退化。","若 clean baseline 本身出现曲线漂移或终点退化，则先重新建立主线锚点，再决定是否进入 LR 或成本轴。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 仍是当前兼容 frontier 上质量最强的可行主线，导出形式未变，继续属于扩展兼容。","r141-r143 三个 matched architecture probes 已把更简化候选的质量下界看清：单阶段 soft-codebook、plain lowrank residual、factorized_topk 都未超过当前主线。","在 probe 轮次后先补 clean baseline，有助于分离架构差异与近期运行代价波动，避免后续 recipe 归因失真。"],"primary_variable":"clean_baseline","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：本轮不新开 family，不改 K、EF、optimizer、LR，也不混入额外成本轴或 loss 轴变量，只做主线 clean baseline 复验。该动作符合当前推荐顺序：EF 已确认在预算内，且经过连续架构探针后，先恢复可信主线锚点比直接继续调 recipe 更稳。风险是这一轮可能再次得到与现有主线相同的 FVU，但它能提供必要的运行代价参照，避免把架构探针的更短时长误读为主线 recipe 问题。","summary":"回到当前主线参考配方做一次 clean baseline 复验：固定 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、signum、LR=3.0e-3，不引入任何新结构或新 recipe，只确认当前 feasible 主线的 FVU、训练曲线与运行代价是否仍稳定可复现。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4731:research/history/logs/agent_action_0220.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_factorized_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"32"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r beta_r u_r + Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {u_r} 是 trunk 静态向量库、{b_i} 是 residual 静态向量库；factorized residual scorer 只影响在线选择与系数计算，不改变 decoder 端导出形态，因此可直接落到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路，兼容性判断为扩展兼容。基于 r210 已证明该 family 在 K=64、EF=1 下能以 0.69x 拿到 0.1256 FVU，当前主矛盾是 trunk 成本过高而不是训练质量不足；本轮严格锚定 r210，只改一个主轴 TRUNK_RANK，从 auto≈256 下调到 32，测试是否能把 total_cost 明确压入 <0.5x 区域，同时尽量保留明显优于同成本 topk 的 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 TRUNK_RANK=32 仍明显优于 <0.5x 区域 topk 前沿，则继续相对本轮单变量下探 TRUNK_RANK=16，检查成本-质量拐点。","如果 TRUNK_RANK=32 的 FVU 退化过大，则保留 r210 作为质量锚点，转向同 family 的单变量 K 轴或回到 topk 前沿继续补点。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_factorized_residual 的导出形式稳定为 trunk 静态库 + residual 静态库的有限加权和，满足 LUTurbo 扩展兼容约束。","r210 的质量信号很强且训练吞吐约 166.6k tokens/s、总耗时 291s，说明该 family 值得优先做成本压缩而不是直接放弃。","在 EF=1、K=64 下，TRUNK_RANK 是同时影响 encoder 与 deployment 的最高杠杆单变量；先压 trunk 比继续加 K 更符合当前 <0.5x 目标区。"],"primary_variable":"other_param","reference_round":210,"self_review":"该提案满足单变量原则：相对 r210 只改 TRUNK_RANK，其余核心配方保持不变。选择 32 而不是 16，是因为它仍应明显低于 0.5x，同时比更激进的 trunk 压缩更有机会保住 r210 展现出的质量优势；主要风险是 trunk 过窄后 coarse 补偿能力不足，FVU 可能回落到接近 topk。","summary":"相对 r210 的 lowrank_factorized_residual@K64,EF1 做一次严格 param_only 成本压缩，只下调 TRUNK_RANK 到 32，优先验证能否把该高质量 family 推入 total_cost < 0.5x 区域。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4734:research/history/logs/agent_action_0095.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 92 through 94 suggest the soft-codebook coarse branch is the first recent non-mainline idea with real signal, but the cheaper single-stage selectors (`lowrank_soft_codebook_residual`, `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual`, `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual`) still did not beat the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor. The single most informative remaining matched architecture probe is `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`: it keeps the same LUTurbo-compatible static-library export path, but asks whether a front-loaded sparse budget after codebook projection can preserve most of the quality while shifting more of the work into the earlier coarse correction and reducing reliance on a large second-stage cleanup. This round answers one question only: under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, is that asymmetric soft-codebook two-stage architecture intrinsically worth any future follow-up, or should the soft-codebook branch be treated as unable to justify more complexity than the current mainline?","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching only `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This stays within the round policy: one probe, one primary variable, allowed `K`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` is explicit. I am choosing the asymmetric soft-codebook two-stage variant over routed, whitened, or bucketed alternatives because it is the simplest remaining probe that still targets LUTurbo-relevant execution structure rather than adding extra selector or preprocessing machinery. The main risk is that it still inherits more moving parts than the mainline, so only a clearly strong curve would justify keeping this branch alive.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 95 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Interpret this strictly as a family-worthiness test for whether the promising soft-codebook branch becomes more deployment-relevant when the sparse budget is front-loaded into the first refinement pass rather than split more evenly across two stages.","Return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome; do not open another new family immediately after this probe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor and not better than the earlier soft-codebook probes, close the asymmetric soft-codebook branch and resume mainline tuning next round.","If `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` stays surprisingly close, record it as a reserve branch with a more deployment-friendly stage allocation, but still return to `lowrank_two_stage_residual` next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4737:research/history/logs/agent_action_0124.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其导出路径仍是静态 trunk 向量库 U、静态 soft-codebook 库 {c_m}、静态 residual 字典库 {b_i} 上的有限加权和，可直接落到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿链路，因此兼容性为扩展兼容。当前 family 在 EF=2 下 selection_cost 约 1.25x，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。本轮吸取 r123 policy_reject 的信号，严格只改一个主变量：在保持 K=128、EF=2、LR=3.0e-3 不变的前提下，仅将 optimizer 从 signum 切到 adam，先确认 optimizer 轴本身是否可跑、曲线是否有价值，再决定是否值得单独为 adam 开 LR 子扫。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 adam@3.0e-3 直接劣化或不稳定，则停止 optimizer 轴，恢复 signum 主线并转向 K 轴比较 96 vs 128。","若 adam@3.0e-3 可跑但曲线显示明显过冲或震荡，再以 lr 为唯一主变量为 adam 单独补 1.5e-3。","若 adam@3.0e-3 与 signum 最终 FVU 接近但耗时更长，则将 adam 视为负面信号，不再继续投入轮次。"],"notes_to_memory":["family 不变，兼容性仍为扩展兼容，导出公式与 LUTurbo 链路映射不变。","r123 policy_reject 表明上一轮 optimizer+lr 联动可能违反当前单变量策略，本轮改为只测 optimizer。","评估必须同时记录 FVU、总耗时、tokens_per_sec、final_total_tokens，确认是否存在吞吐下降导致的伪改进或伪退化。"],"primary_variable":"optimizer","self_review":"本轮严格遵守单变量原则，只改变 optimizer，避免再次触发耦合变量的 policy_reject。缺点是 adam 使用 signum 的 LR 可能不是最优，但先验证 optimizer 轴是否值得继续，比再次提交耦合改动更稳妥。","summary":"围绕预算内主线 family 做一次严格单变量的 optimizer 测试：固定 K=128、EF=2、LR=3.0e-3，仅把 signum 切到 adam，先确认 adam 在该主线上的可运行性、曲线形状与时间成本。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4742:research/history/round_summaries/round_0055.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and return to the current family reference point. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge this run by the full trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `adam` now avoids the old mid-training blow-up and finishes competitively against the `0.142923` signum anchor, it earns exactly one LR callback on the same Hadamard recipe next; if it is flatter, noisier, or clearly worse again, lock `signum` as the optimizer for the strengthened `gated` mainline and stop the optimizer branch.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4746:research/history/round_summaries/round_0055.json:104:    "description": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and return to the current family reference point. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge this run by the full trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `adam` now avoids the old mid-training blow-up and finishes competitively against the `0.142923` signum anchor, it earns exactly one LR callback on the same Hadamard recipe next; if it is flatter, noisier, or clearly worse again, lock `signum` as the optimizer for the strengthened `gated` mainline and stop the optimizer branch.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4752:research/history/logs/agent_action_0174.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_grouped_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary; grouped competition changes only how residual support is selected, not the exported decoder basis. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a static residual library, so inference remains a finite weighted sum over fixed vector banks. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost should remain within the `≤ 1.5×h×n` hard budget because it reuses the feasible `lowrank_residual` scorer stack and only constrains support selection. The single question is whether group-local residual competition is intrinsically worth keeping in the low-EF deployable regime, or whether even this cheaper selector simplification is clearly inferior to the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_residual` is clearly worse than the two-stage mainline in both FVU and runtime metrics, discard grouped low-rank residual variants and return to `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round.","If it is modestly worse in FVU but materially better in throughput or total runtime, keep it as a lower-complexity compatible reserve branch, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy.","If it is unexpectedly close to the mainline at lower selector complexity, allow at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: `扩展兼容`. Export path is static trunk library + static residual dictionary; grouped competition affects only online selection, not decoder exportability.","This round is a strict matched architecture probe: keep `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` explicitly pinned, and change only `ARCHITECTURE`.","Evaluate `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside FVU, because LUTurbo cares about total runtime cost rather than FVU alone; a tiny quality change with slower runtime is negative."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe. After the recent soft-codebook selector probes did not pressure the mainline, the highest-value remaining budget-feasible matched probe is `lowrank_grouped_residual`: it avoids the repeated controller issue seen on `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual`, keeps the export contract simple, and tests whether local competition can buy meaningful runtime simplicity without collapsing quality in the current low-EF regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `lowrank_grouped_residual` with the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether a grouped low-rank single-stage residual architecture is worth any continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4753:research/history/logs/agent_action_0186.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"16"}],"expected_win":"pareto_improve","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j；其中 low-rank trunk 库 U、静态 soft-codebook 库 {c_m}、两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都可静态导出，因此可直接映射到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路，兼容性判断为扩展兼容。当前 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 仍满足 ≤1.5×h×n 硬约束。r133 把 `TRUNK_RANK` 降到 32 时几乎零损失复现了主线 FVU，r182-r184 继续压缩 `NUM_CODES` 也未改变终点，说明当前主线可能仍有明显结构冗余。本轮只回答一个问题：将 `TRUNK_RANK` 进一步下调到 16，是否仍能保持接近当前主线的训练曲线与终点 FVU，同时继续降低 trunk 相关的 encoder 选择成本与部署查表成本，从而推动兼容 Pareto 前沿向更低总成本移动。","summary":"继续围绕同一主线 family 推进，不开新 family；固定 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=128, EF=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3`，仅把 `TRUNK_RANK` 从已验证无损的 32 再降到 16，测试更激进的 trunk 压缩是否仍能维持当前 LUTurbo 可部署质量。","needs_sanity":false,"notes_to_memory":["family 与导出路径不变，`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 在 `TRUNK_RANK=16` 下仍是扩展兼容：trunk 库 + soft-codebook 库 + two-stage residual 字典库的有限加权和。","r133 表明 `TRUNK_RANK=32` 相对主线几乎无损，因此继续沿 trunk 容量轴下探比重复未增益的 `NUM_CODES` 压缩更有信息价值。","评估本轮必须同时比较 curve_start/mid/end、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，确认任何收益来自真实成本下降而非运行时漂移。"],"next_hypotheses":["若 `TRUNK_RANK=16` 仍接近当前主线 FVU 且吞吐不恶化，可将更低 rank 视为新的低成本主线，并考虑继续下探或做一次 clean baseline 复验。","若 `TRUNK_RANK=16` 明显退化，则说明 trunk 容量下限更接近 32，下一轮回到 `TRUNK_RANK=32` 并转向 `NUM_CODES` 或其他单一成本轴。","若终点接近但吞吐显著变差，则把更低 trunk rank 视为负面系统信号，而不是仅凭 FVU 保留。"],"primary_variable":"trunk_rank","self_review":"本轮严格遵守单变量原则：family、EF、K、optimizer、LR 全部固定，只推进 `TRUNK_RANK` 这一直接作用于 encoder 选择成本和部署 trunk 成本的主变量。相比继续尝试在 policy 上有风险的 optimizer 分支，这一步更稳、更可归因，也更贴近 LUTurbo 的真实总成本目标。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4768:research/history/logs/agent_action_0044.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 43 was not a marginal win: enabling Hadamard on the strengthened `gated` anchor improved the full curve from start through end and lowered `K=128` FVU from `0.148156` to `0.142923`, while still improving late. Before treating preprocess as the new operative mainline and moving on to K, the next single question should be a clean confirmation run of the exact Hadamard recipe: does this gain reproduce under the current stack, or was Round 43 an unusually favorable draw?","summary":"Run a clean control on the updated `gated` preprocess recipe. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and the same runtime knobs fixed, and explicitly keep `USE_HADAMARD=1` to verify that the large Round 43 improvement is reproducible. Judge this run by the full trajectory, not just terminal FVU: if the start, mid, and late curve again sit materially below the plain-input anchor and finish near `0.142923`, promote Hadamard as the true `gated` reference recipe; if it falls back toward the non-Hadamard curve, treat the improvement as less stable and avoid overcommitting before K mapping.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and keeps the work on the current preprocess branch rather than opening a new axis prematurely. I am not moving to K yet because the Round 43 gain was large enough that it deserves one direct confirmation before being treated as the new mainline recipe. The main risk is spending a round without frontier improvement, but the value is higher-confidence attribution of the biggest recent recipe gain.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 43 produced a substantial full-curve improvement for `gated@128` by enabling Hadamard at `LR=2.0e-3`, lowering FVU to `0.142923` with better early, mid, and late values than the plain-input anchor.","Round 44 is a clean confirmation rerun of the exact Hadamard recipe so the preprocess gain can be classified as a stable new anchor or a one-off before continuing to K exploration."],"next_hypotheses":["If the Hadamard recipe reproduces near the Round 43 curve and endpoint, adopt it as the new `gated` mainline reference and then resume K mapping from `K=96` or `K=64` downward under the improved recipe.","If the rerun materially degrades toward the plain-input baseline, keep the preprocess result provisional and avoid broad K conclusions until recipe stability is clearer."],"primary_variable":"preprocess"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4769:research/history/logs/agent_action_0159.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 probe family 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 0.75x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束，并且比当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 的约 1.25x 更低。当前 round 159 只允许一个 matched architecture probe，因此保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 以及主要 recipe 完全不变，仅将 architecture 从 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 换成其最邻近的单阶段父节点 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual，回答唯一问题：在当前低 EF 可部署 regime 下，第二阶段 residual refinement 是否仍然值得保留，还是单阶段 soft-codebook 版本已经提供了更优的系统级 cost-FVU 权衡。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 明显落后于 two-stage 主线，则说明第二阶段 refinement 在当前低 EF regime 下仍然有价值，下一轮回到主线继续 recipe 轴。","若 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 与 two-stage 接近且成本更低，则记录其为更强的低成本备选 family，但下一轮仍按要求回到当前主线。","若 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 意外优于当前主线，则说明当前主线 family 本身值得重新审视，但本轮只做架构价值判断，不立即连续展开新 family。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性为扩展兼容。","本轮严格是 matched architecture probe：EF、K、optimizer、LR 与主要 recipe 全部固定，只改 architecture。","评估时必须同时检查 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，避免把更低 FVU 或更低成本误判为吞吐波动导致的假信号。","该 probe 的核心问题不是刷新 frontier，而是判断 two-stage 结构增量在当前可部署低 EF regime 下是否仍然值得继续。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这轮遵守架构探针规则，只改一个主变量 architecture，并保持主线的 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变。选择 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 而不是更远的 topk 或 factorized_topk，是因为它是当前主线的最近父节点，能最干净地隔离“第二阶段 residual refinement 本身是否值得”这个问题，同时还能给出更低 selection_cost 的直接对照。","summary":"插入一个严格匹配的架构探针：将当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 替换为其单阶段父节点 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual，其余 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 全部保持不变，用一轮干净对照判断第二阶段 refinement 在当前低成本 regime 下是否仍然值得保留。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4772:research/history/logs/agent_action_0104.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After five non-improving mainline rounds, the single highest-value matched architecture probe is the direct parent family `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`. It preserves the same LUTurbo-compatible static-library export form as the current `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline, but removes the hand-set asymmetric stage allocation, so this round answers one clean question: is the asymmetry itself actually carrying the current K128/EF12 result, or would the simpler symmetric two-stage soft-codebook backbone be competitive enough to justify future follow-up instead.","summary":"Use the one allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed and changing only `ARCHITECTURE`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 104 probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping the current mainline reference recipe fixed. It is a stronger probe than opening a more exotic branch because it isolates whether the current win comes from the soft-codebook two-stage backbone itself or specifically from the asymmetric budget choice, and it stays aligned with LUTurbo deployment constraints.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 104 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` against the exact `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 mainline reference.","Judge this probe by full-curve shape as well as final FVU, especially whether the simpler symmetric two-stage soft-codebook backbone is competitive enough that the current asymmetric split may be unnecessary.","Return to the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome; this probe is only a yes/no family-worthiness check."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched asymmetric mainline, treat the asymmetric stage allocation as a meaningful ingredient and return to mainline recipe work next round.","If `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is competitive on curve shape or endpoint, record it as a simpler reserve family but still return to the asymmetric mainline next round per probe policy.","Do not open a second architecture probe next round; the next step should go back to mainline recipe clarification."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4775:research/history/logs/agent_action_0014.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The recent `signum` LR refinements did not convert into an accepted frontier update, so the next clean question is whether the current `topk` mainline is slightly over-regularized rather than under-tuned on step size. This round keeps the exact reference backbone `topk/signum/K128/EF12/LR=1.6e-3` fixed and changes only `AUXK_ALPHA`, reducing it from `0.03125` to `0.015625` to test whether weaker auxiliary pressure improves late-stage reconstruction without destabilizing the curve.","summary":"Run a single loss-axis test on the existing topk mainline: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=1.6e-3` fixed, and lower `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.015625` to see whether the current recipe is over-regularized.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This avoids the previous policy-reject by anchoring all core axes to the current reference recipe and changing only one non-core parameter. It also follows the prescribed order better than moving K now, since loss shaping has not been isolated yet on the accepted `1.6e-3` mainline.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.015625"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 13 was rejected because the proposed aux-loss test also inherited a non-reference LR, so the action was not single-variable relative to the current mainline reference.","Round 14 isolates `AUXK_ALPHA` on the exact accepted topk/signum/K128/EF12/LR1.6e-3 recipe.","Evaluate the run by full curve shape, especially whether lower aux pressure improves late-stage descent or causes weaker feature utilization and noisier training."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.015625` improves FVU with a smooth curve, continue tuning aux-loss strength on the same mainline recipe.","If lower aux weight hurts stability or gives no gain, revert to `0.03125` and treat loss shaping as mostly settled.","If aux-loss tuning is neutral, the topk K128 recipe is closer to saturation and K exploration becomes the next useful axis."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4785:research/history/logs/agent_action_0157.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"该 family 的最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 U(Vx) 可离线导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终重构仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下的 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。r153-r155 已先后补齐 clean baseline 并把 signum 的 LR 曲线看清，3.3e-3 虽有小幅稳定收益，但当前策略顺序要求在 LR 之后先回答 optimizer 问题，且 r156 的 K 轴尝试已被 policy 拦截，因此本轮只改一个主变量 OPTIMIZER：保持 family、EF、K、LR 与导出形式不变，仅将优化器从 signum 切到 adam，回答唯一问题：在同样的可部署低成本 regime 下，optimizer 本身是否仍有值得保留的曲线形状或终点信号，还是应被再次明确关闭。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 adam 在相同 LR=3.0e-3 下再次明显爆炸或曲线极差，则正式关闭该 family 在当前低 EF regime 的 optimizer 分支，后续不再用它驱动主线。","若 adam 没有爆炸且曲线具备可比性，即使终点未赢，也可记录为需要一次 optimizer-local LR callback 的候选。","若 adam 意外优于 signum 基线，则下一轮再严格做一次单变量的 optimizer 分支确认或回调。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 继续满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性仍为扩展兼容。","EF=2 下 selection_cost 仍在预算内；本轮不改 EF、K、TRUNK_RANK、NUM_CODES 或其他成本轴，只隔离 optimizer 效应。","r153-r155 已把主线 baseline 与 LR 曲线重新看清；当前最缺的是在现行策略顺序下对 optimizer 的明确结论。","评估时必须同时记录 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，区分是优化器本身导致训练更慢、更长，还是直接数值不稳定。"],"primary_variable":"optimizer","self_review":"这轮严格只改一个主变量 optimizer，family、EF、K、LR 全部固定，符合单变量原则和当前主线推进顺序。虽然历史上 adam 在该 family 上已有负信号，但在当前回合策略明确要求 LR 之后先看 optimizer，而 r156 的 K 轴尝试已被 policy 拦截；因此最合规且信息量最高的动作是用当前参考配方再给 optimizer 一次干净结论，而不是继续提前动 K。","summary":"继续围绕主线 family 推进，不开新 family；固定 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、LR=3.0e-3，仅将 OPTIMIZER 从 signum 切到 adam，判断 optimizer 分支在当前可部署 regime 下是否仍值得保留。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4786:research/history/logs/agent_action_0082.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The signum LR bracket around the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor is now effectively closed: `1.6e-3` regressed and `2.4e-3` was at best a negligible near-tie, not a clear enough win to justify changing the mainline anchor. The next single question is therefore optimizer choice. Testing `adam` at the confirmed reference recipe will show whether the family's remaining limitation is optimization dynamics rather than signum step size, and the answer should be read from the whole curve shape rather than the endpoint alone.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the baseline aux/runtime settings fixed. Judge the run by the full trajectory against the settled signum anchor: if `adam` is smoother and competitive through mid and late training, it earns exactly one optimizer-local LR callback next; if it is flatter, noisier, or clearly worse, lock `signum` as the mainline optimizer and only then move on to loss/preprocess.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the search on the same family, leaves K and EF fixed, and changes exactly one primary variable: `optimizer`. The main risk is that `adam` at `2.0e-3` may not be its ideal LR, but that is acceptable for a first optimizer comparison because the point of this round is to isolate whether the optimizer class itself is promising before spending another round on an optimizer-specific LR callback.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 82 closes the signum LR branch for `lowrank_two_stage_residual` at K128/EF12 by treating `LR=2.0e-3` as the operative anchor; neither `1.6e-3` nor `2.4e-3` produced a decisive enough gain to replace it.","This round opens the optimizer question with a clean `adam` vs `signum` comparison on the exact same family and K128 recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adam` is competitive and stable, run exactly one optimizer-local LR callback next, changing only `LR` while keeping `OPTIMIZER=adam`.","If `adam` is clearly worse, keep `signum` as the settled optimizer and test only one loss-side variable next, such as `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`.","Do not move to K until optimizer and at least one loss/preprocess check are resolved on the K128 mainline."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4787:research/history/logs/agent_action_0116.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.6e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk、soft codebook、两阶段 residual 都可静态导出为固定向量库上的有限加权和，因此可直接映射到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；该 family 属于扩展兼容。Round 114 和 Round 115 已确认在 EF=2、K=128、signum 下，`LR=3.0e-3` 可稳定复现当前可行 frontier 点 `FVU≈0.0581`，且 encoder 选择成本仍在 1.5x 预算内。本轮只改一个主变量 `lr`，向上小步探测到 `3.6e-3`，回答唯一问题：在不改变成本与部署形态的前提下，更积极的 signum 步长能否继续改善曲线和终点 FVU，还是已经越过稳定收敛区间。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `LR=3.6e-3` 进一步改善终点或早中期下降，且 `tokens_per_sec`、总耗时、`final_total_tokens` 没有明显恶化，则把更高 LR 作为新的主线候选并考虑一次复现确认。","如果 `LR=3.6e-3` 出现震荡、回退，或只带来极小 FVU 收益却显著拖慢训练，则关闭向上 LR 分支，保留 `LR=3.0e-3` 为 EF=2 主线锚点。","在 LR 轴结论明确前，不切换 optimizer，不改 K，也不改 TRUNK_RANK / NUM_CODES / STAGE1_RATIO / FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM。"],"notes_to_memory":["兼容性判断：`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 为扩展兼容；导出形式仍是 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + residual 字典库的有限加权和。","EF=2 已稳定满足 encoder 选择成本硬约束，当前可行 frontier 点为 `sel≈1.25x, deploy≈0.62x, FVU≈0.05811`。","本轮严格单变量，只改 `lr`；评估时必须同时检查曲线形状、`tokens_per_sec`、总耗时与 `final_total_tokens`，避免为微小 FVU 收益付出不成比例的训练代价。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"这符合当前主线顺序：EF 已确认在预算内，clean baseline 已补齐并复现，下一步应继续完成 LR 局部化，再考虑 optimizer。选择 `3.6e-3` 是对已验证有效的 `3.0e-3` 做单步上探，仍然只改一个主变量，归因清晰。","summary":"在已确认成本可行且可复现的 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` EF=2 主线上，仅将 `LR` 从 `3.0e-3` 上调到 `3.6e-3`，测试更高 signum 步长是否还能继续改善低成本 Pareto 点。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4788:research/history/logs/agent_action_0187.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"8"}],"expected_win":"pareto_improve","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j；其中 low-rank trunk 库 U、静态 soft-codebook 库 {c_m}、两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都可静态导出，因此可直接映射到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路，兼容性判断为扩展兼容。当前 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 仍满足 ≤1.5×h×n 硬约束。r133 的 `TRUNK_RANK=32` 与 r186 的 `TRUNK_RANK=16` 都未伤害终点 FVU，说明 trunk 容量可能仍有可压缩冗余。本轮只回答一个问题：将 `TRUNK_RANK` 进一步下调到 8，是否仍能保持接近当前主线的训练曲线与终点 FVU，同时继续降低 trunk 相关的 encoder 选择成本与部署查表成本，从而把兼容 Pareto 点继续推向更低总成本。","summary":"继续围绕同一主线 family 推进，不开新 family；固定 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=128, EF=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3`，仅把 `TRUNK_RANK` 从 16 再降到 8，测试更激进的 trunk 压缩是否仍能维持当前 LUTurbo 可部署质量。","needs_sanity":false,"notes_to_memory":["family 与导出路径不变，`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 在 `TRUNK_RANK=8` 下仍是扩展兼容：trunk 库 + soft-codebook 库 + two-stage residual 字典库的有限加权和。","`TRUNK_RANK=32` 与 `16` 都复现了约 0.0581 FVU，因此继续沿 trunk 容量轴下探比回到已多次无增益的 codebook 轴更有信息价值。","评估本轮必须同时比较 curve_start/mid/end、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，确认收益来自真实成本下降而不是运行时漂移。"],"next_hypotheses":["若 `TRUNK_RANK=8` 仍接近当前主线 FVU 且吞吐不恶化，可将更低 rank 视为新的低成本主线，并考虑一次 clean baseline 复验来确认曲线稳定性。","若 `TRUNK_RANK=8` 明显退化，则说明 trunk 容量下限更接近 16，下一轮回到 `TRUNK_RANK=16` 并转向 `NUM_CODES` 或其他单一成本轴。","若终点接近但吞吐显著变差，则把更低 trunk rank 视为负面系统信号，而不是仅凭 FVU 保留。"],"primary_variable":"trunk_rank","self_review":"本轮严格遵守单变量原则：family、EF、K、optimizer、LR 全部固定，只推进 `TRUNK_RANK` 这一直接作用于 encoder 选择成本和部署 trunk 成本的主变量。相比现在切回高风险的 optimizer 分支，这一步更稳、更可归因，也更贴近 LUTurbo 的真实总成本目标。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4791:research/history/logs/agent_action_0181.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_factorized_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_factorized_residual` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3.0e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk and the residual coefficients are chosen by a factorized scorer but still decode as a finite weighted sum over a static residual dictionary `B`. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export the trunk factors and residual dictionary as static vector libraries, then run `trunk branch + factorized support scoring + weighted sparse lookup-sum` online. The single question is whether a lower-cost factorized residual selector is worth continuing versus the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline in the low-EF feasible regime. This probe should stay safely within the encoder-cost budget and gives a clean read on whether scorer factorization is a viable architecture direction rather than another likely policy reject.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune exactly one cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.","If `lowrank_factorized_residual` underperforms on FVU and/or slows throughput without a compensating cost advantage, mark factorized residual scoring as not worth continuing in the current low-cost regime."],"notes_to_memory":["`lowrank_factorized_residual` is LUTurbo `扩展兼容`: the factorized encoder changes selector-side scoring only; decode remains a finite weighted sum over static trunk and residual libraries.","This matched probe tests a still-compatible low-cost architecture direction that has not recently been revisited under the current `K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3e-3` regime.","Review `tokens_per_sec`, wall-clock time, and `final_total_tokens` together with FVU; if factorization only saves selector cost proxy but trains materially slower or reconstructs worse, treat that as a negative signal."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Single-variable discipline is preserved: only `ARCHITECTURE` changes while `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, and `LR` remain fixed to the mainline recipe. This probe stays inside the compatible and likely feasible set, and it answers a distinct architectural question about whether factorized scoring is intrinsically worth keeping alive on the Pareto search path.","summary":"Probe `lowrank_factorized_residual` as the one matched architecture change. It is LUTurbo-exportable (`扩展兼容`) through a static low-rank trunk plus static residual dictionary, and it tests whether factorized residual scoring is worth continuing against the current soft-codebook two-stage mainline in the low-EF feasible regime.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4805:research/history/logs/agent_action_0119.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk、soft codebook、两阶段 residual 都是静态向量库上的有限加权和，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；该 family 属于扩展兼容。当前 EF=2 已稳定满足 encoder 选择成本硬约束，`signum + LR=3.0e-3` 是已复现的低成本主线锚点；将 `AUXK_ALPHA` 从 0.03125 降到 0.015625 后未见明显退化，说明辅助稀疏损失在该低 EF regime 里可能已非必要。本轮只改一个主变量 `AUXK_ALPHA`，进一步降到 `0.0`，回答唯一问题：完全去掉 auxiliary K loss 是否能减少对主重构目标的约束干扰，在不增加训练代价的前提下进一步改善 FVU 或曲线形状。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` 改善终点或曲线形状，且 `tokens_per_sec`、总耗时、`final_total_tokens` 基本不变，则再做一次 clean baseline 复现确认。","如果 `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` 出现退化，则关闭 auxk 降低分支，恢复默认 `0.03125` 或保留已验证等价的较小值，不再继续在该轴上消耗轮次。","在 loss/preprocess 轴未得到清晰正信号前，不改 K，也不改 TRUNK_RANK / NUM_CODES / STAGE1_RATIO / FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM。"],"notes_to_memory":["兼容性判断：`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 为扩展兼容；导出形式不变，仍是 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + residual 字典库的有限加权和。","`adam` 分支已爆炸，当前主线仍应固定在 `signum + LR=3.0e-3`。","本轮严格单变量，只改 `AUXK_ALPHA`；该改动不影响 encoder 选择成本，也不应显著增加训练时长，评估时继续同时检查曲线形状、`tokens_per_sec`、总耗时与 `final_total_tokens`。"],"primary_variable":"auxk_alpha","self_review":"这仍符合当前主线顺序。EF、clean baseline、LR 和 optimizer 结论都已基本清楚，而上轮把 `AUXK_ALPHA` 减半后没有负面信号，因此现在最小且可归因的后续问题就是测试 auxiliary loss 是否可以彻底移除。相比切换到更重的 preprocess 改动，这个问题更干净、代价更低。","summary":"保持 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual / EF=2 / K=128 / signum / LR=3.0e-3` 主线不变，仅将 `AUXK_ALPHA` 进一步降到 `0.0`，测试低成本 regime 下是否可以完全去掉 auxiliary K loss 来改善重构质量。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4812:research/history/logs/agent_action_0077.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 75 and 76 ruled out the simplest matched single-stage alternatives under the current `two_stage_residual` anchor: both `topk` and `jumprelu` were clearly worse at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`. The next single matched architecture probe should therefore test a structurally different exportable decomposition rather than another plain selector. `codebook_topk` is the highest-value remaining yes/no probe because it still maps to a finite weighted sum over static vector libraries, but may reduce LUTurbo online coefficient and lookup cost by reusing a compact static basis instead of a full staged residual path. This round asks one question only: under the exact current mainline recipe, is `codebook_topk` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to remain worth later consideration, or should it be ruled out as clearly inferior to `two_stage_residual`?","summary":"Use the one allowed matched architecture probe on `codebook_topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the same aux/runtime settings, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `two_stage_residual` to `codebook_topk`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `codebook_topk` stays reasonably close with a healthy curve, keep it in reserve because its shared-codebook structure may lower LUTurbo online lookup and coefficient cost; if it is clearly worse throughout, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"codebook_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 77 rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, and the rest of the recipe fixed. `codebook_topk` is a better use of the single probe than revisiting already-rejected plain selector variants because it tests a different cost-quality tradeoff that is still compatible with LUTurbo's static export contract. The main risk is that prior matched probing in an earlier regime already suggested weakness, but this remains the most informative remaining architecture-worthiness check under the current mainline anchor.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"codebook_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 77 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `codebook_topk` against the current `two_stage_residual` mainline recipe, because it represents a distinct static-library decomposition that may reduce LUTurbo online lookup and coefficient cost while preserving exportability.","Judge this probe as a family-worthiness test only: compare matched `codebook_topk@128` against the `two_stage_residual` reference at fixed `EF=12`, `signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, then return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `codebook_topk` is reasonably close with a healthy curve, return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round but keep one later `codebook_topk` revisit available because its shared-codebook path may be cheaper to deploy.","If matched `codebook_topk` is clearly worse than `two_stage_residual` across the curve, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.","If matched `codebook_topk` unexpectedly beats the current `two_stage_residual` reference, still return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round per policy, but record `codebook_topk` as a high-priority later follow-up family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
