research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4822:research/history/round_summaries/round_0001.json:105:    "description": "\u6267\u884c\u4e3b\u7ebf topk \u53c2\u8003\u914d\u65b9\u7684 clean baseline\uff0c\u4e0d\u5f00\u65b0 family\uff0c\u4e0d\u6539\u4ee3\u7801\uff0c\u4e0d\u5148\u52a8 K\u3002\u7528\u5b8c\u6574 env_overrides \u663e\u5f0f\u9501\u5b9a ARCHITECTURE=topk\u3001K=128\u3001EXPANSION_FACTOR=12\u3001OPTIMIZER=signum\u3001LR=8e-4 \u53ca\u5176\u4f59\u5173\u952e\u8fd0\u884c\u53c2\u6570\uff0c\u4f18\u5148\u6d88\u9664\u53d8\u91cf\u9694\u79bb\u5931\u6548\u98ce\u9669\uff0c\u5e76\u5efa\u7acb round 1 \u7684\u53ef\u6bd4\u8f83\u57fa\u7ebf\u3002",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4834:research/history/logs/agent_action_0134.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"architecture_value_signal","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"matched_probe","hypothesis":"候选架构的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i。low-rank trunk 基库 U、soft codebook 库 {c_m}、residual 字典库 {b_i} 都是静态可导出的固定向量库，因此可以直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 matched architecture probe 保持主线的 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变，只把 architecture 从 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 换成其更简单的单阶段父节点 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual，用来回答一个问题：在相同 recipe 下，去掉第二阶段 residual refinement 后，是否能以更低 selection_cost（约 0.75x vs 1.25x）和可能更低运行代价，换取仍可接受的 FVU，从而成为更优的成本侧 Pareto 候选。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 matched probe 的 FVU 接近当前两阶段主线且吞吐更好，则说明两阶段 refinement 在 EF=2 下边际收益不足，下一轮应回到主线并重新评估更简单 family 的成本优势。","若 matched probe 明显劣于两阶段主线，则说明第二阶段 residual refinement 仍然值得保留，下一轮回到 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 继续做成本轴微调。","若 matched probe 结果介于两者之间但训练显著更快，则可将 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 视为低成本备用主线，而非替代当前最优 FVU 点。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮是单次 matched architecture probe，严格保持 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变，只改 architecture。","lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 为扩展兼容 family，且在 EF=2 下 selection_cost 明显低于当前两阶段主线，适合作为是否值得继续的对照探针。","probe 完成后下一轮应回到主线，不连续扩展新 family。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"遵守本轮策略要求，只做一个 matched architecture probe，没有联动改 recipe。所选 family 来自主线的直接父节点，兼容性明确且成本更低，能够直接回答“架构本身是否值得继续”这个问题；风险是它的 FVU 可能已知偏弱，但这正是 probe 需要验证的。","summary":"插入一个与主线完全匹配 recipe 的架构探针：把 architecture 改为 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual，其余保持 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变，测量单阶段 soft-codebook 父节点在当前低成本 regime 下是否值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4835:research/history/logs/agent_action_0102.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 98 and 100 established `LR=2.4e-3` as the best reproduced signum recipe for `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=128` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, so the next single mainline question is optimizer choice. Holding that recipe fixed and switching only `OPTIMIZER` to `adam` tests whether this family is now limited by optimization dynamics rather than signum step size, and the result should be judged from the full training curve versus the settled signum anchor rather than the endpoint alone.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.4e-3` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the required sequence after baseline and LR localization: same family, same `K`, same `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and exactly one primary variable changes. It also fixes the Round 101 policy mistake by keeping `LR` fixed at the already localized signum anchor instead of coupling an optimizer change with a new LR search.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 102 corrects the prior policy error by isolating the optimizer comparison: `adam` at the settled `LR=2.4e-3` recipe for `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` `K=128` `EF=12`.","Judge this run by full-curve behavior against the reproduced signum anchor, especially whether `adam` improves mid/late descent or smooths the trajectory without sacrificing terminal FVU.","Do not open an optimizer-local LR callback unless this first `adam` run is at least competitive with the signum anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adam` is competitive with or better than signum at `LR=2.4e-3`, give `adam` exactly one LR callback next within the same family.","If `adam` is clearly worse or unstable, keep `signum` as the optimizer and move to the next single-axis mainline recipe question before touching `K`.","Do not change loss, preprocess, or architecture until the optimizer branch is cleanly resolved."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4844:research/history/logs/agent_action_0079.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_two_stage_residual` just produced a decisive matched win at `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=2.0e-3`, but before opening the LR branch the first question should be whether that result is a stable mainline anchor rather than a one-off trajectory. Re-running the exact same recipe is the cleanest way to inspect curve shape repeatability and establish a trustworthy baseline for subsequent single-variable tuning.","summary":"Stay on the new `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline and run a clean baseline confirmation with the exact reference recipe: `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the baseline aux/runtime settings unchanged. Judge the round by full curve repeatability against Round 78, not just terminal FVU; if the trajectory is similarly smooth and competitive, treat this family recipe as the confirmed anchor before any LR or optimizer change.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the Round 79 mainline policy exactly: no new family, no code edit, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` is explicit, and the round answers one question only about baseline stability. The cost is that this round may not improve frontier numerically, but establishing a repeatable anchor is higher-value than immediately touching LR after only one winning run on a freshly promoted family.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 79 is a clean baseline confirmation for the newly promoted `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline at `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=2.0e-3`.","Use curve-shape repeatability versus Round 78 as the decision signal; only after a stable repeat should LR tuning start on this family."],"next_hypotheses":["If the baseline repeat is stable, next round should change only `LR`, starting with a small downward probe to `1.6e-3` or upward probe to `2.4e-3` depending on whether Round 78 looked underdamped or still aggressively descending late.","If the repeat is materially worse or unstable, treat Round 78 as possibly optimistic and run one more anchor confirmation before touching optimizer or loss.","Do not move K until the family's K128 recipe is localized on baseline and LR per the operator sequence."],"primary_variable":"baseline_confirmation"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4847:research/history/logs/agent_action_0111.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"After five consecutive non-improving mainline rounds, the single highest-value matched architecture probe is the nearest strong alternative family `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`. It preserves the same LUTurbo-compatible static export form as the current `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline, but changes only the stage allocation structure. Holding `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed isolates one clean question: does the asymmetric two-stage variant remain competitive enough on the matched reference recipe to deserve future follow-up, or should focus stay on the simpler current mainline family.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If the matched `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` probe is clearly worse than the current mainline, return next round to `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` recipe work and do not extend this branch.","If the matched probe is competitive on full-curve shape or endpoint, record it as a viable reserve family but still return next round to the `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline.","Do not change `K`, optimizer, loss, or preprocess in this probe; this round is only about whether the architecture itself is worth keeping in consideration."],"notes_to_memory":["Round 111 uses the one allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` against the current `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline reference recipe.","Judge this probe by the whole curve versus the archived symmetric mainline at `K=128`, `EF=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, not only the terminal FVU.","Regardless of outcome, next round should return to the `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline rather than opening another new family immediately."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This follows the Round 111 probe policy exactly: one matched architecture probe, same `K`, same optimizer, same LR, explicit `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and only `ARCHITECTURE` changes. The chosen family is the strongest nearby LUTurbo-compatible alternative already seen in history, so it gives the highest information value without opening a broader search branch. The tradeoff is spending one round away from mainline recipe cleanup, but that is explicitly allowed for this single probe.","summary":"Use the one allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed and changing only `ARCHITECTURE`.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4848:research/history/logs/agent_action_0121.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j，可导出为 trunk 库 U、soft-codebook 库 {c_m} 与 residual 字典库 {b_i} 上的有限加权和，因此属于扩展兼容。基于当前可行主线点 K=128, EF=2, signum, LR=3.0e-3 已经满足 selection_cost≈1.25x 的预算约束，本轮只下调学习率到 2.4e-3，测试是否能在不改变 selection/deploy 成本的前提下减少高 K 配方的优化噪声并把 FVU 从 0.0581 继续压低。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 2.4e-3 曲线更平滑但收敛偏慢，回测 2.7e-3 作为同 family 的中间 LR。","若 signum 在 EF=2, K=128 下已明显平台化，再做 optimizer 轴切换并联动 LR retune。","若 K=128 的收益相对 K=96 不足以覆盖更高 deploy 成本，则回到 K 轴比较 96 vs 128 的系统性价比。"],"notes_to_memory":["本 family 维持扩展兼容：x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j，可静态导出到多个向量库。","本轮严格保持 family/K/EF/optimizer 不变，只测 LR，对 frontier 归因干净。","目标是验证可行预算区间内 K=128, EF=2 的主线点是否仍有纯优化改进空间。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"遵守了单变量原则，并继续沿当前主线 family 推进。缺点是我没有直接看到最新训练曲线，只能依据现有结果做保守 LR 下调；但这仍是当前优先级下最可解释、最低风险的一步。","summary":"在预算内主线 family 上做一次纯 LR 清洗：固定 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、K=128、EF=2、signum，仅把 LR 从 3.0e-3 下调到 2.4e-3，验证是否能以相同 selection_cost/deploy_cost 换取更低 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4849:research/history/logs/agent_action_0191.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","hypothesis":"最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i；其中 low-rank trunk U(Vx)、soft codebook 库 {c_m} 与 residual 字典 {b_i} 都可静态导出到 LUTurbo 的‘查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿’链路，因此该 family 属于扩展兼容。主假设：在保持 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 完全 matched 的前提下，去掉第二阶段 residual refinement 后，lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 仍可能以更低的 encoder 选择成本与更快训练吞吐保住一个有价值的 Pareto 点；若 FVU 明显回退，则说明 stage-2 是当前主线真正有效的结构增益。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若该 probe 的 FVU 仍显著落后于 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual，则下一轮回到主线，只调一个成本轴如 TRUNK_RANK / NUM_CODES / STAGE1_RATIO。","若该 probe 以更低 selection_cost 保持接近 FVU 且训练更快，可把 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 重新视为低成本支线继续做单轴 recipe 清洗。","继续避免 routed / bucketed matched probe at EF=2，因为其 selection_cost 约 2.25x h×n，已超 policy 预算。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮是 matched architecture probe；除 architecture 外显式保持 K=128、EF=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变。","lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 为扩展兼容，导出路径是 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + residual 字典库的有限加权和。","在 EF=2 下，lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 的 selection_cost 约 0.75x h×n，低于主线 two-stage 的 1.25x；routed / bucketed 同配方约 2.25x，当前不可行。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这不是全新 family，信息增益低于真正新结构；但在当前 matched、兼容、且满足成本约束的候选里，它是最干净的 probe。最近的 grouped/gated/asymmetric siblings 已给出负信号，而 routed/bucketed 在 EF=2 被预算拦截，因此本轮用 one-stage parent 来隔离‘第二阶段 residual 是否值得其额外成本’是最可解释的动作。","summary":"执行一个 matched architecture probe：把主线从 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 切到其 one-stage 父节点 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual，其余 recipe 保持 K=128 / EF=2 / signum / LR=3.0e-3 不变。该 family 的 LUTurbo 导出公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i，属扩展兼容；本轮重点看去掉 stage-2 后，是否能用更低 encoder 选择成本与更快训练代价维持一个值得保留的 Pareto 点。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4860:research/history/logs/agent_action_0155.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.3e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。r154 已在正常运行代价下把 LR=3.3e-3 复现到 FVU=0.0579389，优于 3.0e-3 baseline 的 0.0581065，且总耗时仅 264s，说明这次改善不再依赖异常慢速样本。本轮只回答一个问题：3.3e-3 的收益是否足够稳定到可以正式替代 3.0e-3 成为该 family 的 signum 主线 LR，因此再做一轮同配方 clean repeat，而不是继续上探或切 optimizer。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若本轮再次复现 0.05794 左右或更低 FVU，且 tokens_per_sec、总耗时、final_total_tokens 保持在正常区间，则把 3.3e-3 升格为该 family 的 signum 主线 LR。","若本轮回落到接近 3.0e-3 baseline，则把 3.3e-3 视为边际但不够稳的点，关闭 LR 上调分支并恢复 3.0e-3 作为主线锚点。","若本轮终点仍更好但曲线或运行代价开始恶化，则记录 3.3e-3 是质量更优但系统代价更敏感的 recipe，后续不再继续上探 LR，而转向 optimizer 或其他单变量轴。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 继续满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性仍为扩展兼容。","EF=2 继续满足选择成本预算；K 保持 128，避免把部署查表成本变化与 LR 复验混杂。","r154 已提供一次在正常运行代价下的正信号，本轮目标是确认它是否足够稳到升级为主线，而不是继续扩大 LR 搜索空间。","评估时必须同时记录 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时、final_total_tokens，确认收益来自更优收敛而非训练更长或吞吐异常。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：只改 LR，family、EF、K、optimizer 全部固定在当前主线 family。当前最有信息量的问题不是继续加大学习率或切优化器，而是确认 3.3e-3 是否已达到可升级为主线的稳定性门槛。","summary":"继续围绕主线 family 推进，不开新 family；保持 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、signum 不变，再运行一轮 LR=3.3e-3 的 clean repeat，确认它是否能稳定替代 3.0e-3 成为新的主线学习率。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4875:research/history/logs/agent_action_0103.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 101 and 102 showed that the controller still treats `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual K=128 EXPANSION_FACTOR=12 OPTIMIZER=signum LR=2.0e-3` as the official mainline reference recipe for single-axis comparisons, so the cleanest next question is optimizer choice at that exact anchor. Switching only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam` while holding the reference `LR=2.0e-3` fixed tests whether this family has any optimizer headroom before spending another round on an optimizer-local LR callback, and it should be judged by the full curve shape against the signum reference rather than only the terminal FVU.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This corrects the last two policy rejects by anchoring the optimizer comparison to the controller-declared reference recipe instead of the unofficial `LR=2.4e-3` signum probe. Only one primary variable changes, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` remains explicit, and the result will cleanly answer whether `adam` deserves exactly one follow-up LR callback in this family.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 103 re-asks the optimizer question on the controller's official mainline reference recipe after Rounds 101 and 102 were policy-rejected for effectively coupling optimizer selection with a non-reference LR.","Judge this run by the whole trajectory versus the archived signum reference at `K=128`, `EF=12`, `LR=2.0e-3`, especially early stability and mid/late descent shape.","Only if `adam` is competitive on this matched reference should it earn one optimizer-local LR callback next; otherwise keep `signum` and move on."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adam` is competitive with or better than matched `signum` at `LR=2.0e-3`, give `adam` exactly one LR callback next within `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`.","If `adam` is clearly worse or unstable at the matched reference recipe, keep `signum` and move to the next single-axis mainline recipe question before touching `K`.","Do not change loss, preprocess, or architecture until the optimizer branch is resolved cleanly on an accepted baseline."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4876:research/history/logs/agent_action_0074.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 73 answered the optimizer question clearly: `adam` on the `two_stage_residual` reference recipe failed catastrophically (`FVU=33.8917`), so the optimizer branch should be considered closed and `signum` remains the correct mainline optimizer for this family. Following the prescribed order, the next single mainline question is now loss shaping: with `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed, is the default auxiliary loss helping this staged residual decomposition, or does removing it improve the full training trajectory and final FVU?","summary":"Stay on the `two_stage_residual` mainline, return to the stable `signum` reference recipe, and change only the loss-side variable `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0`. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed. Judge this run by the whole curve against the archived baseline, not just the endpoint: if dropping the auxiliary loss improves or smooths the trajectory, keep loss tuning alive; if it regresses or destabilizes training, restore the default loss and move to preprocess next.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"mainline_improvement","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active mainline family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, uses an allowed `K`, and changes exactly one primary variable: `loss`. It follows the required progression because the optimizer branch has now been cleanly falsified, so there is no justification for an optimizer-local LR callback. The main risk is that aux removal may have only a small effect, but it is the next policy-clean question before preprocess or any K movement.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 73 strongly rejected `adam` for `two_stage_residual` on the reference recipe, so the optimizer branch should be treated as closed and `signum` remains the mainline optimizer.","Round 74 should isolate the loss question on the stable `two_stage_residual@128` signum anchor by setting `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` at fixed `EF=12` and `LR=2.0e-3`, evaluating the whole curve rather than endpoint alone."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` improves the `two_stage_residual` curve or endpoint, keep loss-side tuning alive with at most one nearby confirmation.","If removing the auxiliary loss is clearly worse or unstable, restore the default loss and move to the preprocess question next.","If the effect is neutral, treat loss as mostly settled and proceed to preprocess before any K change."],"primary_variable":"loss"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4879:research/history/logs/agent_action_0212.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_factorized_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"32"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r beta_r u_r + Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {u_r} 是静态 trunk 向量库、{b_i} 是静态 residual 向量库；factorized scorer 只影响在线选择与系数计算，不改变 decoder 端的静态库有限加权和形式，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路，兼容性为扩展兼容。单主变量选择 TRUNK_RANK：在保持 ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_factorized_residual、K=64、EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3 不变时，把 trunk_rank 从当前 auto≈128 下调到 32，测试当前 0.69x 点的主要冗余是否来自过大的 trunk 库；若 trunk 只是提供粗补偿而 residual 分支已承担主要表达，则可把 encoder+deployment 总成本一口气压入 <0.5x 区域，同时维持明显优于 topk@0.31x 的 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 TRUNK_RANK=32 仍保持明显优于 topk@EF1,K64 的 FVU 且进入 <0.5x，则固定该 family 后只沿 K 轴做一次补点。","如果 TRUNK_RANK=32 的 FVU 退化过大，则说明该 family 的收益高度依赖 trunk 容量，低开销主战场应回到更短链路的 topk 或新的轻量单库方案。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_factorized_residual 的导出形式稳定为 trunk 静态库 + residual 静态库的有限加权和，属于扩展兼容，可继续保留在兼容 frontier 候选集中。","r210 在 0.69x 处取得 0.1256 FVU，且 tokens_per_sec≈166.6k、总耗时 291s，明显快于近期 topk/soft-codebook 线；因此优先压缩 trunk_rank 比继续增大 K 更符合当前低开销与训练成本双目标。"],"primary_variable":"other_param","self_review":"这轮只改一个主轴 TRUNK_RANK，归因干净，且直接针对 r210 暴露出的成本结构问题。选择 32 而不是 64，是因为 64 大概率仍停留在 >0.5x 边界外；32 才有机会真正补上当前最缺的 <0.5x 前沿，但风险是 trunk 过度压缩后 FVU 可能明显反弹。","summary":"在扩展兼容的 lowrank_factorized_residual 上做一次低开销 param-only 探索：固定 K=64、EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，仅把 TRUNK_RANK 压到 32，目标是在保留 trunk+residual 双库导出形式的同时，把当前 0.69x 候选推进到 <0.5x 区域。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4888:research/history/logs/agent_action_0127.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"matched_probe","hypothesis":"本轮 matched architecture probe 只改 architecture。候选架构的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的‘查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿’链路，兼容性为扩展兼容。与当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 相比，它只去掉第二阶段 residual refinement，保持 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变。这个 probe 只回答一个问题：两阶段 residual refinement 在低 EF 可行预算区间内是否真的值得，还是单阶段 soft-codebook residual 已能以更低 selection_cost 给出更好的系统权衡。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 matched probe 明显差于两阶段主线，则说明第二阶段 residual 在低 EF=2 下仍然有价值，下一轮回到主线继续做 recipe/成本轴微调。","若 matched probe 接近或优于当前主线，同时训练更快或 selection_cost 更低，则可考虑把 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 纳入兼容 frontier。","若 matched probe FVU 略差但时间和成本明显更优，则后续可在该 family 内只做主线级别的小步 recipe 清洗，而不是立即扩大家族搜索。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮是单次 matched architecture probe，严格保持 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变，只改变 architecture。","选择 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 作为 probe，是为了直接测试‘第二阶段 residual 是否值得’这一最小结构差异问题。","该 probe family 为扩展兼容，可导出路径为 trunk 库 + soft-codebook 库 + residual 字典库。","评估时需同时比较 FVU、selection_cost、总耗时、tokens_per_sec、final_total_tokens，避免只按最终 FVU 做结论。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"遵守了本轮 matched architecture probe 规则，只改 architecture，且选择了与主线最接近、兼容且预算内的父节点做对照。风险是 deploy 成本差异可能不大，但它能最干净地回答两阶段 refinement 本身�soft-codebook variants because their EF=2 encoder selection cost is already over budget (~2.5x original matmul) and would be policy-blocked.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe with ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual while keeping K=128, EF=2, signum, and LR=3.0e-3 fixed. It is LUTurbo 扩展兼容 with reconstruction x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j, and it is the nearest feasible architecture variant to the current mainline without adding extra encoder-cost/routing overhead.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4889:research/history/logs/agent_action_0067.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 65 and 66 established a clean, reproducible `two_stage_residual` mainline baseline at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, so the next highest-value single question is whether a modest learning-rate reduction improves late-stage convergence without giving up the strong early progress. This round tests only that: does lowering `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` produce a smoother or better `two_stage_residual` training curve under the same matched recipe.","summary":"Run a single learning-rate adjustment within the `two_stage_residual` mainline by keeping `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, and changing only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"mainline_improvement","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the prescribed mainline order: the clean baseline has been confirmed, so the next step is a single LR test before touching optimizer, loss, or K. A modest LR reduction is the most interpretable first move because it probes whether the staged residual architecture is currently slightly underdamped near convergence rather than underpowered.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 67 is the first mainline recipe adjustment for `two_stage_residual` after the clean baseline repeat reproduced the Round 65 result.","Judge this run by curve shape as well as endpoint: the question is whether a slightly lower LR improves stability or late-stage descent relative to the archived `2.0e-3` baseline.","If `1.6e-3` is worse or simply slower everywhere, the next LR move should likely be upward rather than making more small downward steps."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=1.6e-3` improves the endpoint or gives a cleaner descending curve, archive it as the new `two_stage_residual` mainline recipe.","If `LR=1.6e-3` is clearly worse or just slower than `2.0e-3`, revert to the archived baseline and test a modest LR increase next.","If the curve shape is mixed, keep optimizer fixed and use one more LR probe before considering any optimizer change."],"primary_variable":"learning_rate"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4890:research/history/logs/agent_action_0132.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk 基库 U、soft codebook 库 {c_m}、两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都是静态可导出的固定向量库，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 时 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。由于 r131 的 optimizer 分支被 policy_reject，先停止继续扫 optimizer；本轮只回答一个问题：在主线 baseline（signum, LR=3.0e-3）上去掉 auxiliary K loss（AUXK_ALPHA=0.0）后，是否能改善训练末段收敛形状并在不增加选择成本、不过度拖慢 tokens_per_sec/总耗时的前提下降低 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 AUXK_ALPHA=0.0 曲线更平滑且终点更好，可继续围绕 aux loss 强度做单变量细扫。","若 AUXK_ALPHA=0.0 终点变差或训练早期明显失稳，则说明 auxiliary 信号仍有价值，回到 baseline 后再考虑 preprocess 轴。","若 AUXK_ALPHA=0.0 与 baseline 几乎等价，则结束 loss 轴试探，后续再评估更细的部署成本变量如 TRUNK_RANK 或 NUM_CODES。"],"notes_to_memory":["LUTurbo 导出形式未变，family 仍为扩展兼容；本轮不引入新 family。","EF=2 继续满足 selection_cost 预算；K 保持 128，避免把部署查表成本变化与 loss 轴混杂。","r131 optimizer 分支被 policy_reject，因此本轮转向更保守的 loss 轴单变量试探，而不是继续扩张 optimizer 搜索。"],"primary_variable":"auxk_alpha","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：family、EF、K、主优化器和 LR 都固定，只改 AUXK_ALPHA。该提案避开了刚被 policy 拒绝的 optimizer 分支，继续在兼容且成本可行的主线 family 上获取可解释信号；风险是 auxiliary loss 关闭后可能导致早期 support 学习变差，因此必须结合曲线形状与运行代价共同判断。","summary":"在已稳定复现的 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 主线上做一次 loss 轴最小改动：固定 EF=2、K=128、signum、LR=3.0e-3，仅关闭 auxiliary K loss，判断该辅助项是否在当前低 EF 可行区间内已经成为收敛噪声。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4896:research/history/round_summaries/round_0085.json:20:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe by switching only `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_residual_vq` while keeping the mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the baseline loss/runtime settings unchanged. Judge the probe by the full curve, not just endpoint FVU: if `lowrank_residual_vq` stays smooth and materially pressures the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, it remains worth keeping in reserve; if it is clearly weaker or less stable, close the family-worthiness question and return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4901:research/history/round_summaries/round_0085.json:80:    "description": "Run one matched architecture probe by switching only `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_residual_vq` while keeping the mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the baseline loss/runtime settings unchanged. Judge the probe by the full curve, not just endpoint FVU: if `lowrank_residual_vq` stays smooth and materially pressures the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, it remains worth keeping in reserve; if it is clearly weaker or less stable, close the family-worthiness question and return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4903:research/history/logs/agent_action_0179.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3.0e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk and the JumpReLU selector only changes which residual dictionary atoms `b_i` are activated and their coefficients. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export the trunk factors and residual dictionary as static vector libraries, then execute `trunk lookup + thresholded sparse selection + weighted lookup-sum` online. The probe asks one question only: in the low-EF feasible regime, does learned thresholding provide a better architecture tradeoff than the current soft-codebook two-stage mainline, or should this family be ruled out. Encoder selection cost should stay in the feasible band at `EF=2`, so this should produce a real signal instead of a policy reject.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune exactly one cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.","If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` underperforms the mainline on FVU or shows materially worse `tokens_per_sec`/runtime without compensating benefit, mark the family as not worth continuing in the low-cost regime."],"notes_to_memory":["`lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is LUTurbo `扩展兼容`: decode remains a finite weighted sum over a static low-rank trunk plus a static residual dictionary; JumpReLU only changes selector-side activation sparsity.","This matched probe stays inside the likely feasible encoder-cost regime and is more informative than another routed/bucketed-style over-budget probe.","When scoring the run, inspect `tokens_per_sec`, wall-clock time, and `final_total_tokens` together with FVU; a tiny quality gain with slower training is a negative signal."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Single-variable discipline is preserved: only `ARCHITECTURE` changes while `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, and `LR` remain fixed to the mainline recipe. This probe avoids another likely budget rejection and tests a remaining compatible architecture that can still deliver a clean go/no-go answer for the low-EF frontier.","summary":"Probe `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` as the one matched architecture change. It is LUTurbo-exportable (`扩展兼容`) through a static low-rank trunk plus static residual dictionary, and it should give a real low-cost signal on whether learned thresholding is worth continuing versus the current soft-codebook two-stage mainline.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4904:research/history/logs/agent_action_0135.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"architecture_value_signal","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"matched_probe","hypothesis":"候选架构的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i。low-rank trunk 基库 U 与 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都是静态可导出的固定向量库，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 matched architecture probe 严格保持主线的 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变，只把 architecture 改为更简单的 lowrank_residual，用来回答一个问题：在当前低 EF 可行区间内，soft codebook coarse branch 是否仍然必要，还是 low-rank trunk + 单阶段 residual 已足够形成更优的成本/时延权衡。该架构在 EF=2 下 selection_cost 约 0.62x h×n，低于当前主线的 1.25x，若 FVU 没有明显恶化且运行更快，则值得作为低成本备选继续保留。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 lowrank_residual 的 FVU 接近主线且吞吐更好，则说明当前 EF=2 下 coarse codebook 的边际收益有限，下一轮回到主线后应重新审视更简单 family 的成本优势。","若 lowrank_residual 明显劣于主线，则说明 soft codebook coarse branch 在低 EF 下仍然必要，下一轮回到 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 继续做成本轴微调。","若 lowrank_residual 介于主线与 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 之间且更快，可将其记为低成本备用点，但不替代当前最佳 FVU 主线。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮仍是单次 matched architecture probe，严格保持 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变，只改 architecture。","lowrank_residual 为扩展兼容 family，且在 EF=2 下 selection_cost 明显低于当前两阶段主线，适合回答 coarse codebook 是否必要。","r134 的 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual probe 被 policy_reject，因此本轮改用另一个已知兼容且更低成本的父节点进行架构价值判断。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"遵守本轮架构探针约束，没有联动改 recipe。选择 lowrank_residual 而非继续重复被拒的 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual probe，可以更直接测试 soft codebook 分支本身的必要性；风险是该 family 可能在 K=128 下 FVU 明显偏弱，但这正是探针需要确认的信号。","summary":"做一个新的 matched architecture probe：仅把 architecture 改为 lowrank_residual，其余保持 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变，测量去掉 soft codebook 与第二阶段 refinement 后，这个更低成本父节点是否还值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4905:research/history/logs/agent_action_0091.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`whitened_lowrank_residual` failed catastrophically at the matched K128 anchor, so the next matched architecture probe should avoid more whitening-style conditioning and instead test a different single-stage low-rank selector family. The most informative remaining probe is `lowrank_factorized_residual`: it preserves the low-rank trunk and static-library weighted-sum export path, but replaces the plain residual scorer with a factorized scorer. This answers one clean question: can a more structured single-stage selector recover enough of the two-stage mainline's quality to be worth continuing, or is the second residual stage itself the essential ingredient. If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is still clearly weaker under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then the remaining single-stage low-rank selector variants are likely not worth further follow-up in the current regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_factorized_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the round policy by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. I am explicitly avoiding `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` because with the current batch-size-1 regime it collapses to ordinary top-k behavior and would not be an informative matched probe. The main risk is that `lowrank_factorized_residual` may add selector complexity without helping quality or LUTurbo online cost, so this should be judged strictly as a yes/no family-worthiness test before returning to the mainline.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_factorized_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 91 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_factorized_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Avoid `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` in this batch-size-1 regime because its adaptive budget path degenerates to ordinary top-k and is not a meaningful architecture probe.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for a structured single-stage low-rank selector; return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, treat the remaining single-stage low-rank selector variants as low priority and resume mainline tuning next round.","If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a structured single-stage comparison point but still return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4906:research/history/logs/agent_action_0028.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `topk` mainline saturated for five rounds, the highest-value matched architecture probe is a directly compatible near-neighbor that changes support formation without changing the exported reconstruction form. `whitened_topk` keeps the same `K=128` sparse weighted-sum decoder contract as `topk` but adds input preconditioning before top-k competition, so this round asks one clean question: does that architectural change alone produce a meaningfully better curve or enough promise to justify follow-up work.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `whitened_topk`. Keep `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and the current stable non-compiled runtime/aux recipe fixed, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `topk` to `whitened_topk` to test whether this directly export-compatible variant is worth continuing as a family.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"whitened_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the Round 28 rule for a single matched architecture probe, changes exactly one primary variable (`architecture`), and chooses a candidate that remains close to LUTurbo's static-vector weighted-sum deployment contract. The main risk is that the preconditioning may add training complexity without improving reconstruction, but that is precisely the yes/no family-worthiness question this probe is meant to answer before returning to the mainline next round.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"whitened_topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 28 inserts exactly one matched architecture probe after five consecutive non-improving topk rounds; the probe must be judged as a family-worthiness test, not as a new mainline pivot.","`whitened_topk` is directly compatible with LUTurbo's deployment form because the final reconstruction remains a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architectural change is confined to encoder-side preconditioning and selection.","Judge this probe by full curve shape plus final FVU relative to the stabilized K128 topk control: if it is clearly worse or unstable, drop the family and return to topk; if it is competitive or better, it earns at most one follow-up slot later, but the immediate next round should still return to the topk mainline."],"next_hypotheses":["If `whitened_topk` is clearly worse than the stabilized `topk` control, archive it immediately and return to mainline topk recipe work next round.","If `whitened_topk` is roughly competitive with a smoother or still-descending curve, record it as a promising probe result but still return to the topk mainline next round per policy.","If `whitened_topk` beats the matched topk control, schedule exactly one later follow-up on the same family after the mandated return to the mainline."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4907:research/history/logs/agent_action_0038.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `gated` mainline has already shown smooth, still-improving curves at `K=128`, `K=96`, and `K=64`, but Round 38 should first fill the missing clean-baseline step in the prescribed order. Re-running the exact `gated` reference recipe with all reference aux/runtime knobs explicitly pinned answers one question only: does the true anchor still reproduce a clean curve under the current stack before we spend another round on lower `K` or renewed recipe tuning?","summary":"Run a clean control on the current `gated` mainline reference recipe. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=1.6e-3`, and explicitly lock the known reference aux/runtime settings so the next comparison is grounded in a fresh, fully specified anchor curve. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just terminal FVU: recent `gated` runs at `K=96` and `K=64` were still improving late, so we need a refreshed `K=128` control before deciding whether to continue down the K ladder or revisit LR.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the EF=12 constraint, and avoids opening a new branch. It also repairs the sequencing gap in the current mainline by adding the missing clean baseline before any further K move. The main risk is that it may not improve the frontier numerically, but right now the more important value is a fresh, comparable anchor curve for the next decision.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 38 backfills the missing clean-baseline step for the active `gated` mainline with the exact reference recipe explicitly pinned at `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3`.","Recent `gated` K sweeps at `K=96` and `K=64` both had smooth, still-improving curves, so a refreshed `K=128` control is needed before interpreting any further K descent or LR changes."],"next_hypotheses":["If the clean `gated@128` control reproduces the expected anchor with a healthy late curve, resume the K ladder and test `K=32` next to locate where `gated` stops beating `topk`.","If the refreshed baseline comes in materially different from the recorded anchor, treat baseline reproducibility as the immediate issue and avoid drawing more family-quality conclusions from the recent K sweep alone."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4908:research/history/logs/agent_action_0041.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 40 answered the LR question cleanly: `LR=2.4e-3` preserved a smooth curve but regressed slightly versus the new `2.0e-3` anchor, so the signum LR branch is now sufficiently localized around `2.0e-3`. The next single question in the prescribed order is therefore optimizer: with `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=128, EF=12, LR=2.0e-3` fixed at the refreshed anchor recipe, does swapping `signum` to `adam` produce a healthier curve or competitive FVU, or does `gated` still clearly prefer `signum`?","summary":"Keep the active `gated` family and move to the optimizer axis now that the LR sweep has identified `2.0e-3` as the best current signum setting. Run `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` with all reference aux/runtime knobs explicitly pinned, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge the result by the whole trajectory, not just endpoint: if `adam` descends more cleanly or closes the gap at the stronger `2.0e-3` anchor, it earns exactly one LR callback next; if it is flatter, noisier, or clearly worse again, lock `signum` as the gated optimizer and stop the optimizer branch.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same mainline family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `optimizer`. It follows the stated round order after the LR branch produced a modest win at `2.0e-3` and a slight regression at `2.4e-3`, which is enough evidence to stop spending more rounds on signum LR micro-tuning before checking optimizer. The main risk is that `adam` was already poor at `1.6e-3`, but that makes this a bounded confirmation rather than an open-ended sweep.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 40 slightly regressed from the `LR=2.0e-3` gated anchor while keeping a similarly smooth, still-improving curve, so the signum LR branch is localized enough to move on.","Round 41 switches the current `gated@128` anchor from `signum` to `adam` at fixed `LR=2.0e-3` to answer the next prescribed optimizer question under the updated mainline recipe rather than the older `1.6e-3` anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated+adam` at `LR=2.0e-3` is competitive or better with a healthy curve, run exactly one Adam LR callback next to test whether its usable range differs from signum.","If `gated+adam` at `LR=2.0e-3` is clearly worse again, keep `signum` as the gated optimizer and move on to the next recipe axis without further optimizer work."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4913:research/history/logs/agent_action_0204.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"smaller_k","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: factorized_topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 b_i 来自单个静态向量库，低秩 factor scorer 只参与在线选择、不改变 decoder 形式，因此对 LUTurbo/Lottable 属于直接兼容。单主变量选择 k：把当前 0.50x 前沿点 factorized_topk 从 K=128 下调到 K=64，保持 ARCHITECTURE/EF/OPT/LR 不变，可把 deployment cost 约从 0.12x 降到 0.06x，使 total_cost 约从 0.50x 降到 0.44x，直接补到 <0.5x 区域；预期 FVU 会升高，但仍可能成为该低开销区域的首个有效 Pareto 点。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 K=64 成功占住 <0.5x 前沿，再继续沿同一 family 单变量下探 K=32。","如果 K=64 的 FVU 退化过大，再回到 factorized_topk 固定 K=64，单变量下调 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM 以继续压 encoder 成本，或转向 topk/EF=1 做更低成本锚点。"],"notes_to_memory":["factorized_topk 的 decoder 仍是单静态字典加权和，属于直接兼容 family，可继续作为 <0.5x 区域主力低成本基线。","本轮只改 K，避免把 architecture/EF/LR 混入，便于归因低开销前沿是否主要受 lookup 成本驱动。"],"primary_variable":"k","self_review":"方案严格遵守单变量原则，且不需要改 sparsify/ 代码。主要风险是 K=64 的 FVU 可能明显差于现有 0.50x 点；但当前任务优先级是补 <0.5x 覆盖，这个风险是可接受的。","summary":"运行一个纯参数低开销探索：保持 factorized_topk, EF=2, signum, LR=3e-3 不变，仅将 K 从 128 降到 64，目标是在直接兼容前提下把 total_cost 压到约 0.44x，并为 <0.5x 区域建立首个可行 Pareto 候选。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4923:research/history/logs/agent_action_0010.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 8's failure at `adam@1.6e-3` is still most plausibly an Adam step-size mismatch rather than evidence that the optimizer branch is unusable. This round changes only the learning rate within the same `topk` family, backing Adam off to `8e-4` while keeping `K=128` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, to test whether Adam can produce a stable curve shape and recover competitive FVU under a smaller step size.","summary":"Execute the deferred Adam learning-rate callback: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=adam` fixed, and reduce `LR` from `1.6e-3` to `8e-4` to determine whether round 8 was primarily overshoot.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `topk` mainline, changes only one primary variable (`lr`), respects the fixed `EF=12` constraint, and follows the prescribed order by completing the new-optimizer LR callback before touching loss, preprocess, or K.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"8e-4"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 9 did not execute a training run, so the Adam branch is still unresolved and should not be judged from round 8 alone.","This round isolates Adam LR retuning by holding `topk/K128/EF12` fixed and only reducing the step size.","Evaluate this run primarily by full training-curve shape: early stability, mid-training descent, and whether late-stage FVU keeps improving, not only the final scalar."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adam@8e-4` is still unstable or clearly inferior, test an even smaller Adam LR before abandoning the branch.","If `adam@8e-4` is stable and competitive, continue Adam-only LR tuning within `topk`.","If `adam@8e-4` is stable but weak, compare its curve shape against signum before deciding whether the optimizer branch is worth another callback."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4931:research/history/logs/agent_action_0172.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library, `{c_m}` is a static soft-codebook library, and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary; the gate only changes single-sample support weighting before top-k, not the exported decoder basis. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one static codebook lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a static residual library, so inference still reduces to finite weighted sums over fixed vector banks. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost is expected to remain within the `≤ 1.5×h×n` hard budget because it adds one gate scorer on top of the already-feasible `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` path while staying below the current two-stage mainline’s selector complexity. The single question is whether the soft-codebook coarse branch remains worthwhile with a cheaper gated single-stage selector, or whether the current two-stage refinement is still clearly necessary.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` is clearly worse than the two-stage mainline in both FVU and runtime metrics, discard this family and return to `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round.","If it is modestly worse in FVU but materially better in throughput or total runtime, keep it as a lower-complexity compatible reserve branch, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy.","If it is unexpectedly close to the mainline at lower selector complexity, allow at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: `扩展兼容`. Export path is static trunk library + static soft-codebook library + static residual dictionary; gating affects only online selection, not decoder exportability.","This round is a strict matched architecture probe: keep `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` explicitly pinned, and change only `ARCHITECTURE`.","Evaluate with `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside FVU, because LUTurbo cares about total runtime cost rather than FVU alone; small quality changes with noticeably worse runtime are negative."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe. Repeating `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` has already failed twice on policy-detection rather than science, so the highest-value remaining matched probe is a nearby soft-codebook selector variant that should still be budget-feasible and avoids the same controller edge case. `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` directly tests whether the coarse codebook branch is the real source of value while simplifying the residual selector relative to the current mainline.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` with the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether a softer codebook-plus-gated single-stage architecture is worth any continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4939:research/history/logs/agent_action_0168.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary; the gate only changes how residual coefficients are selected, not the exported decoder basis. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a static residual vector library, with the gate absorbed entirely into online coefficient/selection logic. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost stays within the `≤ 1.5×h×n` hard budget and remains below the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline. The single question is whether this simpler low-rank gated selector is intrinsically strong enough in the current low-EF deployable regime to justify any later follow-up, or whether the mainline’s soft-codebook plus second stage is clearly necessary.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` is clearly worse than the mainline in both FVU and runtime metrics, discard it and return to `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round.","If it is modestly worse in FVU but materially better in throughput or total runtime, record it as a lower-cost compatible side branch, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy.","If it is unexpectedly close to the mainline at lower selection cost, schedule at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: `扩展兼容`. Export path is `U(Vx)` trunk lookup plus one sparse residual lookup over a fixed decoder library; gating affects only selection, not decoder exportability.","This round is a strict matched architecture probe: keep `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` explicitly pinned, and change only `ARCHITECTURE`.","Judge family worthiness using `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside final FVU, because a tiny quality gain with noticeably worse runtime would be negative for LUTurbo’s true objective."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe fields that caused recent policy confusion. `lowrank_gated_residual` is the highest-value remaining matched probe because it preserves LUTurbo exportability, stays within the EF=2 selection-cost budget, and tests whether a simpler one-stage low-rank selector can recover more quality than plain `lowrank_residual` without paying the full mainline cost. The main risk is that the added gate branch may not close enough of the FVU gap to justify even its moderate extra runtime.","summary":"Run one valid matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_residual` while keeping the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether a cheaper single-stage low-rank gated architecture is worth any continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4944:research/history/round_summaries/round_0180.json:25:    "self_review": "Single-variable discipline is preserved: only `ARCHITECTURE` changes while `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, and `LR` remain fixed to the mainline recipe. This probe stays within the compatible family set, is likely budget-feasible, and answers a clean architectural question without drifting into another over-budget selector variant.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4946:research/history/round_summaries/round_0180.json:78:    "self_review": "Single-variable discipline is preserved: only `ARCHITECTURE` changes while `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, and `LR` remain fixed to the mainline recipe. This probe stays within the compatible family set, is likely budget-feasible, and answers a clean architectural question without drifting into another over-budget selector variant.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4949:research/history/logs/agent_action_0025.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After two consecutive K128 loss-path probes (`AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` and `DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD=100000`) both failed to beat the declared `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/K=128/EF=12` anchor, the most useful single question is whether the exact reference recipe itself still reproduces a clean late-phase descent under the current stack. This round makes no recipe change; it reruns the fully explicit mainline baseline to refresh the curve-shape reference before any further LR or optimizer decisions.","summary":"Run a clean full baseline on the exact active topk reference recipe. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `K=128`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and explicitly lock the auxiliary/runtime knobs to their reference values so the next decision is grounded in a fresh comparable curve rather than in two regressed loss-side variants.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active family, respects the one-question rule, and follows the stated priority order by re-establishing a clean baseline before more recipe movement. The risk is no frontier gain this round, but with two consecutive non-improving non-core tweaks, re-anchoring the exact reference is the clearest way to avoid compounding noise and to judge later changes by curve shape rather than stale memory.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Rounds 23 and 24 both regressed the K128 anchor, so the loss-side branch currently looks unpromising without a fresh control run.","A full explicit rerun of the exact topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/K128/EF12 recipe is now the cleanest single-question action because it refreshes the reference curve shape under the current execution stack.","Judge this round primarily by reproducibility and late-phase slope: if the clean baseline again descends smoothly into the known FVU band, move next to LR or optimizer decisions with higher confidence; if it drifts materially, treat stack variance as a live factor before drawing more recipe conclusions."],"next_hypotheses":["If the clean baseline reproduces the anchor cleanly, the next mainline question should return to a core axis, starting with a narrow LR check or an optimizer comparison per policy order.","If the clean baseline comes in materially worse or with a different curve shape, pause further recipe interpretation and treat baseline reproducibility as the immediate issue.","If the clean baseline unexpectedly improves, promote the refreshed explicit recipe as the operative anchor before any further exploration."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4959:research/history/logs/agent_action_0072.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 71 gave a clean positive answer on the learning-rate axis for `two_stage_residual`: `LR=2.4e-3` improved the start (`0.173863` vs `0.176606`), mid-curve (`0.133819` vs `0.134559`), and endpoint (`0.127782` vs `0.127844`) relative to the archived `2.0e-3` baseline, so the signum LR question is now sufficiently clarified. The next single mainline question, in the prescribed order, is optimizer: with the stronger `two_stage_residual` recipe now anchored at `LR=2.4e-3`, does switching from `signum` to `adam` produce a healthier full training curve or competitive final FVU, or does this family still clearly prefer `signum`?","summary":"Stay on the `two_stage_residual` mainline and adopt the improved signum learning rate as the current anchor. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.4e-3` fixed, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge this run by the whole trajectory against the `signum` anchor, not just the endpoint: if `adam` is smoother and competitive, it earns one LR callback next; if it is clearly flatter, noisier, or worse, lock `signum` as the optimizer and move on.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"mainline_improvement","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active mainline family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, uses an allowed `K`, and changes exactly one primary variable: `optimizer`. It follows the required sequence after completing the initial within-family LR sweep, and it uses the strongest observed signum anchor rather than reopening K, loss, or preprocess prematurely. The main risk is that `adam` may underperform badly, but that is exactly the branch this round is meant to settle before any optimizer-specific LR callback.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 71 established `LR=2.4e-3` as the strongest observed `signum` setting for the current `two_stage_residual@128` mainline, with a modest but consistent improvement over the archived `2.0e-3` baseline across start, mid, and end of the curve.","Round 72 should answer the optimizer question on that stronger anchor by swapping only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam` at fixed `K=128`, `EF=12`, and `LR=2.4e-3`, judging the whole curve rather than endpoint alone."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adam` is competitive with or better than the `signum` anchor, give `adam` exactly one LR callback next within `two_stage_residual`.","If `adam` is clearly worse or noisier, keep `signum` as the settled optimizer and move to the loss or preprocess question next.","If `adam` is mixed, do not change K yet; use at most one optimizer-local LR probe only if the curve is plausibly salvageable."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4962:research/history/logs/agent_action_0189.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 probe family 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i；其中 low-rank trunk 库 U、静态 soft-codebook 库 {c_m}、以及 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都可静态导出，gated selector 只改变 residual support 的门控与打分方式，不改变最终 decode 仍是固定向量库上的有限加权和，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。在本轮 matched architecture probe 中，严格保持主线的 `K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3` 不变，只将 architecture 从 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 改为 `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual`，唯一问题是：在当前低 EF 可部署 regime 下，简单 gated residual selector 是否值得继续，还是它会像 grouped 版本一样在 FVU 与运行代价上都落后于当前两阶段 soft-codebook 主线。","summary":"插入 1 个 matched architecture probe：将当前主线 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 替换为 `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual`，其余 `K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3` 全部保持不变，用一轮干净对照判断 gated soft-codebook 路线在当前可部署低成本 regime 下是否值得继续。","needs_sanity":false,"notes_to_memory":["`lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` 满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性为扩展兼容：trunk 库 + soft-codebook 库 + residual 字典库。","本轮严格是 matched architecture probe：EF、K、optimizer、LR 与主线 recipe 全部固定，只改 architecture。","评估时必须同时检查 FVU、curve_start/mid/end、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，避免把架构质量与运行时波动混淆。"],"next_hypotheses":["若 `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` 明显落后于当前主线，则关闭 gated soft-codebook 分支，下一轮回到 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 主线。","若该 probe 的 FVU 接近主线且吞吐更好，可将其记录为较低选择复杂度的兼容备选，但下一轮仍回到主线。","若该 probe 意外优于当前主线，则说明 gated selector 在低 EF regime 值得继续，但本轮只做架构价值判断，不连续展开新 family。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"本轮遵守架构探针规则，只改一个主变量 architecture，并保持主线的 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变。选择 `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` 是为了在保留 LUTurbo 兼容的 trunk+codebook 主干下，测试比 grouped 更温和的 selector 改造是否本身值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4973:research/history/logs/agent_action_0001.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"在当前 frontier 为空且主线 family 仍是 topk 的情况下，先跑一轮显式锁定的 clean baseline，能先验证训练链路稳定、拿到可解释的曲线形状与基准 FVU，再决定后续优先做 lr 微调还是优化器切换。","summary":"执行主线 topk 参考配方的 clean baseline，不开新 family，不改代码，不先动 K。用完整 env_overrides 显式锁定 ARCHITECTURE=topk、K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=12、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=8e-4 及其余关键运行参数，优先消除变量隔离失效风险，并建立 round 1 的可比较基线。","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"这轮不是为了直接拿更低 FVU，而是为了建立干净基线。风险是收益偏信息获取而非性能提升，但这符合当前“frontier 为空先补 clean baseline”的主线策略，也避免在没有曲线参考时过早调 lr 或换优化器。","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"8e-4"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 1 先建立 topk clean baseline，避免 frontier 为空时直接做 lr/optimizer 归因不清。","本轮显式锁定 EF=12 与主线参考 recipe，重点观察整段训练曲线形状而不只看最终 FVU。","当前仓库无已记录 frontier，且执行层默认值与主线参考配方一致，适合先做一次变量完全隔离的基线运行。"],"next_hypotheses":["如果 baseline 曲线平稳但后段仍明显下降未收敛，下一轮优先围绕 topk 只调 LR。","如果 baseline 曲线早早平台化或震荡明显，可尝试只改 LR 做更稳的学习率回调。","只有在 baseline 与一轮 LR 调整后，才考虑切换 optimizer 做同 family 主线比较。"],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4977:research/history/round_summaries/round_0166.json:18:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe with ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_residual while keeping K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, and LR=3.0e-3 fixed. This yields a clean LUTurbo-compatible baseline to judge whether the mainline\u2019s extra soft-codebook and two-stage structure is worth continuing.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4984:research/history/logs/agent_action_0052.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 51 completed the downward K mapping: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) now owns every allowed frontier point from `K=128` down to `K=4`. With the K axis fully mapped, the next single question is whether the most deployment-stressed point is slightly overdriven: if we keep the same `gated@4` recipe fixed and lower only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3`, does the ultra-low-K training curve become smoother and finish lower, or is `2.0e-3` still the right setting even at the minimum support?","summary":"Stay on the active `gated` family and hold the newly established minimum-support point fixed at `K=4` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` to test whether the current ultra-low-K recipe is mildly overstepping rather than capacity-limited. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if the lower LR reduces early noise and yields a better finish than the current `gated@4` result (`0.447286`), then low-K gated wants a different step size than the `K=128` anchor; if the curve slows uniformly or the endpoint worsens, keep `2.0e-3` as the shared mainline LR across the whole K grid.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `lr`. It also avoids reopening the K axis now that the allowed grid has been completely mapped and instead asks the highest-value remaining recipe question at the most stressed deployment point. The main risk is that the poorer ultra-low-K quality is mostly capacity-driven rather than step-size-driven, but a single LR callback at `K=4` is the cleanest way to distinguish those explanations without introducing another family or coupled change.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"4"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 51 completed the full allowed-K sweep for the improved `gated` recipe: it now holds frontier points at `K=4,8,16,24,32,64,96,128` under `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`.","Round 52 returns from K mapping to recipe refinement and isolates the LR question specifically at `K=4`, where LUTurbo online cost is minimal and training dynamics are most likely to expose over-aggressive step size."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated@4` improves with `LR=1.6e-3`, run at most one nearby LR confirmation on the same `K=4` recipe to localize the low-K optimum.","If `LR=1.6e-3` is worse or only slower, keep `2.0e-3` as the shared mainline LR and consider the remaining low-K gap primarily a capacity issue rather than a tuning issue."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4987:research/history/logs/agent_action_0200.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe under the fixed mainline recipe. Final reconstruction formula is x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j, where the only structural change versus the current mainline is a front-loaded stage split with stage1_k≈0.75K and stage2_k≈0.25K. This is LUTurbo 扩展兼容 because the trunk term U(Vx), soft-codebook branch Σ_m pi_m c_m, and both residual sparse branches all decode from static vector libraries, so inference still exports to LUTurbo/Lottable as static lookup tables plus weighted sums plus optional residual compensation. The probe asks one question only: at K=128, EF=2, signum, LR=3.0e-3, is the asymmetric two-stage budget intrinsically better than the symmetric split enough to justify keeping this family alive?","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["After this probe, return to the lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual mainline next round.","If asymmetric two-stage again fails to beat the symmetric parent in the EF=2 feasible regime, mark this family not worth continuing."],"notes_to_memory":["Round 199 was policy-rejected because the action was framed as param_only; this retry keeps the exact same scientific hypothesis but uses the correct architecture-only probe schema.","Compatibility label: 扩展兼容. Export path remains low-rank trunk library + soft codebook library + residual dictionary library.","Feasibility check: this family stays within the 1.5x encoder selection-cost cap at EF=2, unlike routed/bucketed two-stage soft-codebook variants which would be over budget in the matched setting.","Because recent rounds have become slower, this probe should be judged on tokens_per_sec, total runtime, and final_total_tokens in addition to FVU; a tiny FVU gain with worse throughput is a negative signal."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This is a strict one-variable matched architecture probe: K, EXPANSION_FACTOR, OPTIMIZER, and LR remain fixed. I am reusing the same candidate as the rejected Round 199 attempt because the scientific question was valid and the rejection appears procedural rather than scientific. Routed and bucketed two-stage soft-codebook variants are intentionally excluded because their EF=2 encoder selection cost exceeds the hard budget and would likely be blocked again.","summary":"Retry the matched architecture probe with ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual under the unchanged mainline recipe. It is LUTurbo 扩展兼容, preserves the same deployable formula class as the current parent, and is the nearest feasible architecture perturbation for testing whether asymmetric stage allocation is worth continuing.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:4999:research/history/logs/agent_action_0002.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"在 topk/signum 基线已建立后，本轮只下调学习率，检验基线曲线末段的更新噪声是否来自步长偏大；若是，则较小 LR 应该在不改 family/optimizer/K 的前提下带来更平滑的收敛并改善 FVU。","summary":"继续主线 topk，不开新 family，不换优化器，不动 K。本轮唯一主变量是学习率：从 8e-4 下调到 6e-4，回答“当前 signum+topk 基线是否因 LR 略大而限制了收敛质量”这个单一问题。","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"这是按主线顺序进行的单变量 LR 回调，归因清晰。风险是收益可能有限，但相比直接换优化器或改 K，这一轮更符合当前策略，也更容易结合训练曲线判断是过冲/震荡还是单纯欠训练。","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"6e-4"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 2 保持 topk/signum/K128/EF12 不变，只做 LR 回调以提高归因清晰度。","本轮重点看训练曲线是否更平滑、后段是否仍持续下降，而不只比较最终单点 FVU。","如果 6e-4 明显更稳且更优，后续可继续在 signum 下做小范围 LR 精调；如果更差或收敛更慢，再考虑换 optimizer。"],"next_hypotheses":["如果 6e-4 改善了后段收敛和最终 FVU，下一轮继续只调 LR 做更细化回调。","如果 6e-4 过小导致下降变慢或 FVU 变差，下一轮可回到 8e-4 附近并改为更高或中间 LR。","如果 signum 在两档 LR 下都已明显平台化，再按顺序只改 optimizer 做同 family 对比。"],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5008:research/history/logs/agent_action_0078.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`two_stage_residual` has stalled at the matched `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=2.0e-3` anchor after several clean recipe checks and three weaker simple-family probes. A single matched probe on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` is the highest-value architecture question now: it preserves the same staged static-library decomposition contract while adding a stronger coarse low-rank trunk. If it cannot beat or clearly pressure the current `two_stage_residual` anchor under the exact same recipe, then the added coarse-path complexity is not worth continuing in this regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching only `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_two_stage_residual` while keeping the current `two_stage_residual` reference recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and baseline aux settings. This answers one question only: whether a stronger low-rank coarse stage is worth revisiting at all, or whether the simpler `two_stage_residual` should remain the active LUTurbo-aligned mainline.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is policy-clean: one matched architecture probe, one primary variable, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` is explicitly pinned. The main tradeoff is that `lowrank_two_stage_residual` likely raises online coefficient cost versus the current mainline, so it is only worth continuing if the FVU gain is material rather than marginal. I am choosing it over another simple selector family because recent matched probes already showed that lighter alternatives are clearly behind the current anchor.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 78 uses the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` against the exact `two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Interpretation rule: because `lowrank_two_stage_residual` adds online coarse-path compute, only a clear reconstruction win justifies future follow-up; a near-tie should still count against reopening this family."],"next_hypotheses":["Return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless, per the operator instruction.","If `lowrank_two_stage_residual` wins clearly, schedule exactly one clean confirmation round on that family before any LR or optimizer tuning.","If it loses or is only marginally better, treat the current stall as evidence that stronger coarse-trunk complexity is not the right next direction under the K128/EF12 LUTurbo-aligned regime."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5011:research/history/logs/agent_action_0008.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"在 signum 下把 LR 从 8e-4 提升到 1.8e-3 后，frontier 最优仍停在 1.6e-3，说明继续在 signum 上做更高 LR 外推的价值开始下降；本轮只切换优化器到 adam，并保持 topk/K128/EF12/LR=1.6e-3 不变，用来判断优化器本身是否能带来更稳的训练曲线和更好的 FVU。","summary":"继续围绕 topk 主线推进，不开新 family，不动 K。本轮按推荐顺序从学习率扫描切到优化器比较；唯一主变量是 OPTIMIZER：从 signum 改为 adam，同时保持 ARCHITECTURE=topk、K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=12、LR=1.6e-3 不变。","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"这轮满足单变量原则，也符合“先调学习率，再换优化器”的主线顺序。风险是 adam 直接沿用 1.6e-3 未必是其最佳 LR，但作为 optimizer 首轮对照这是可接受的，因为它能最大限度隔离优化器效应；若结果有潜力，下一轮再只调 adam 的 LR。","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 8 结束 signum 的主线 LR 上探，开始 topk family 内的 optimizer 对照。","r7 没有刷新 frontier，说明当前不能只追更高 LR，需要比较优化器对曲线形状和稳定性的影响。","本轮固定 LR=1.6e-3 做 adam 首轮对照；如果可行，下一轮应只调 adam 的 LR。"],"next_hypotheses":["如果 adam@1.6e-3 比 signum@1.6e-3 更稳且更优，下一轮继续留在 topk family，只调 adam 的 LR。","如果 adam@1.6e-3 可运行但偏不稳或偏弱，下一轮仍只调 LR，给 adam 一轮学习率回调。","如果 adam 明显不如 signum 且没有曲线优势，可结束该优化器分支并回到 signum 主线。"],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5012:research/history/logs/agent_action_0039.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 38 cleanly reproduced the `gated` anchor at `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3` with the same still-improving late curve, while the only prior LR callback (`1.2e-3`) was uniformly worse. The next single question is therefore whether the current recipe is slightly underdriven rather than overdriven: does a modest LR increase to `2.0e-3` improve the full training trajectory and beat the refreshed anchor?","summary":"Continue on the same `gated` mainline and probe only the learning-rate axis. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, explicitly pin the reference aux/runtime knobs, and raise `LR` from `1.6e-3` to `2.0e-3`. Read the whole curve, not just terminal FVU: if the higher LR preserves stability while improving mid-to-late descent below the refreshed `0.149936` control, then the current anchor was slightly conservative; if it becomes noisier or finishes worse, keep `1.6e-3` as the gated LR anchor and stop the LR branch.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `lr`. It also follows the prescribed order now that the clean baseline has been backfilled successfully. The main risk is that `2.0e-3` could overdrive training, but the evidence so far points the other way: `1.2e-3` was clearly slower/worse, and the refreshed `1.6e-3` baseline was still improving late.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 38 confirmed the clean `gated@128` control reproduces the anchor almost exactly and still shows late improvement, so baseline reproducibility is no longer the blocker.","Round 39 reopens the LR axis cleanly on the same `gated` mainline by testing an upward callback to `LR=2.0e-3` after the earlier downward callback to `1.2e-3` was uniformly worse."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated` at `LR=2.0e-3` improves the trajectory or final FVU while remaining stable, run one final nearby LR confirmation before moving on to optimizer or K.","If `gated` at `LR=2.0e-3` is noisier or worse than the refreshed control, lock `LR=1.6e-3` as the gated mainline anchor and move to the next prescribed recipe axis."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5017:research/history/round_summaries/round_0113.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4fdd\u6301\u4e3a x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + \u03a3_j alpha_j^(2) b_j\u3002\u5176\u4e2d low-rank trunk\u3001soft codebook\u3001\u4e24\u9636\u6bb5 residual \u90fd\u53ef\u9759\u6001\u5bfc\u51fa\u4e3a\u56fa\u5b9a\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u4e0a\u7684\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u843d\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u94fe\u8def\uff1b\u8be5 family \u5c5e\u4e8e\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002Round 112 \u5df2\u8bc1\u660e EF=2 \u65f6\u8be5\u4e3b\u7ebf family \u8fdb\u5165\u9009\u62e9\u6210\u672c\u9884\u7b97\u5185\uff08\u7ea6 1.25x h\u00d7n\uff09\u5e76\u5f97\u5230 FVU=0.05914\uff0c\u4f46\u8fd9\u53ea\u662f\u9996\u4e2a\u6210\u672c\u53ef\u884c\u70b9\u3002\u6309\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf\u987a\u5e8f\uff0c\u4e0b\u4e00\u8f6e\u5e94\u5148\u8865 clean baseline\uff1a\u5b8c\u5168\u590d\u73b0 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=2.4e-3`\uff0c\u786e\u8ba4\u8be5\u4f4e\u6210\u672c Pareto \u70b9\u662f\u5426\u53ef\u91cd\u590d\u3001\u66f2\u7ebf\u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u4fdd\u6301\u4ece 0.0966 -> 0.0655 -> 0.0591 \u7684\u5065\u5eb7\u4e0b\u964d\uff0c\u800c\u4e0d\u662f\u7acb\u5373\u518d\u52a8 LR \u6216\u5176\u4ed6\u914d\u65b9\u8f74\u3002",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5032:research/history/logs/agent_action_0151.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"该 matched probe 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是静态向量库上的有限加权和，可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。与当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 相比，这个 probe 只移除 soft-codebook coarse branch 与第二阶段 residual refinement，保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 与其余主 recipe 不变，因此只回答一个问题：在当前低 EF 预算内，soft-codebook + two-stage 这套更重结构是否真的提供了足够大的质量收益，值得相对 lowrank_residual 更高的 encoder 选择成本与部署查表成本。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 lowrank_residual 在显著更低 selection_cost 与 deploy 成本下仅小幅损失 FVU，则说明当前主线的复杂结构优势不足以覆盖其总成本，下一轮按规则回到主线后应谨慎继续投入该 family。","若 lowrank_residual 明显更差，则说明不仅第二阶段 refinement 有价值，soft-codebook coarse branch 本身也在 EF=2 下提供了必要结构收益，下一轮回到主线继续做主线 recipe/成本工作。","若 lowrank_residual 终点更差但训练明显更快，则把它记为更便宜的兼容对照点，但不在本轮直接替换主线。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮是单次 matched architecture probe，严格只改 architecture，其余 K、EF、optimizer、LR 全部与主线参考配方一致。","lowrank_residual 属于扩展兼容 family，不属于不兼容候选，可合法进入兼容 frontier 对照。","r150 已表明仅去掉第二阶段后的 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 仍明显落后于主线；本轮进一步测试若连 soft-codebook coarse branch 一并去掉，性能是否会继续明显下滑。","评估时必须同时记录 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时、final_total_tokens，区分是结构更简单带来的吞吐提升，还是确有更好的总成本-质量权衡。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"遵守本轮架构探针规则：只改 architecture，保持主线的 K、OPTIMIZER、LR、EXPANSION_FACTOR 与主要 recipe 不变。相比更远的 factorized_topk，这个 probe仍沿同一 low-rank residual inheritance line，归因更干净，也更直接回答 soft-codebook coarse branch 本身是否值得继续。","summary":"执行一次严格 matched architecture probe：把当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 换成更简单的 lowrank_residual，其余 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 全部保持不变，用一轮干净对照判断 soft-codebook + two-stage 结构相对基础 low-rank residual 是否值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5037:research/history/logs/agent_action_0058.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `gated` mainline now stable but non-improving for five rounds, the highest-value single matched architecture probe is the simplest directly compatible alternative: `topk`. It preserves LUTurbo's static-vector finite weighted-sum export form while potentially lowering online selection and coefficient cost relative to `gated`, so this round asks one clean yes/no question: under the exact current mainline recipe (`K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`), is `topk` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to be worth revisiting as a family, or does `gated` remain clearly superior even before runtime considerations are counted?","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `topk`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `topk` stays smooth and closes most of the gap to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is still worth later family-level consideration because its deployment path is simpler; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 58 matched-probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, and the rest of the settled mainline recipe fixed. `topk` is the best probe candidate because it remains directly export-compatible for LUTurbo and offers a simpler online path than `gated`; the main risk is that reusing the `gated`-tuned recipe may understate topk's ceiling, but that is acceptable here because this round is explicitly a family-worthiness screen, not a new topk tuning campaign.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 58 is a single matched architecture probe inserted after five consecutive non-improving `gated` rounds; it must be judged only as a family-worthiness test, and the next round should return to the `gated` mainline regardless of outcome.","`topk` is directly compatible with LUTurbo deployment because the reconstruction remains a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; compared with `gated`, it may also lower online selection and coefficient-computation cost if quality remains competitive.","Judge this probe by full curve shape and endpoint relative to the current `gated@128` anchor: if `topk` is clearly worse across the trajectory, archive it under the current matched recipe; if it is competitive, record that as evidence that the simpler architecture may still deserve a later dedicated revisit."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `topk` is clearly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round and treat this probe as closed.","If matched `topk` is roughly competitive with a healthy curve, still return to the `gated` mainline next round, but keep one later topk revisit available because its simpler deployment path may outweigh a small training-quality gap.","If matched `topk` unexpectedly beats the current `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy but schedule exactly one later topk follow-up under its own lane."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5038:research/history/logs/agent_action_0208.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"enter_low_cost_region_with_stronger_baseline","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 b_i 来自单个静态向量库；导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时仍是单样本 top-k 选择后的单库查表与加权求和，因此属于直接兼容。r207 表明在相同 K=64、EF=2 下，topk 的 FVU 明显优于 factorized_topk，说明 <0.5x 区域的主要瓶颈很可能来自 scorer factorization 而非纯预算。本轮保持 architecture=topk、K=64、optimizer、LR 不变，只把 EXPANSION_FACTOR 从 2 降到 1，直接压低 encoder selection cost，目标是在进入 <0.5x 区域的同时，测试非 factorized 单库 baseline 能否拿到明显优于 factorized_topk@0.44x 的 FVU。按成本表线性外推，selection cost 约可从 0.50x 降到 0.25x，total_cost 约落在 0.31x。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 topk@EF1,K64 的 FVU 仍明显优于 factorized_topk 在相近成本下的结果，则下一步可固定 EF=1，单变量扫描 K=96 或 K=128，寻找 <0.5x 内更好的 topk 前沿点。","如果 EF=1 导致 FVU 大幅恶化，则说明 topk 的有效区间仍依赖更大的字典规模，下一步应回到 EF=2 并尝试其他低成本 family，而不是继续压缩 topk 字典。"],"notes_to_memory":["r207 已证明在 K=64、EF=2 下，去掉 factorized scorer 能显著改善 FVU，因此值得沿 topk 继续走 encoder 降本轴。","本轮只改 EXPANSION_FACTOR，保持 K 不变，便于把性能变化归因为字典规模而不是 lookup 次数变化。"],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor","self_review":"该提案严格遵守单变量原则，并直接服务于当前 <0.5x 区域补点目标。主要风险是 EF=1 可能使 topk 表达能力下降较多，但其信息价值高，因为它能直接回答非 factorized 简单架构能否在真正低成本区站住脚。","summary":"在直接兼容的 topk family 上做单变量低成本下探：固定 K=64、signum、LR=3e-3，仅把 EXPANSION_FACTOR 从 2 降到 1，目标是在约 0.31x 总成本处建立一个比 factorized_topk 更强的 <0.5x 候选点。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5045:research/history/round_summaries/round_0084.json:20:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe by switching only `ARCHITECTURE` to `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` while keeping the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the baseline loss/runtime settings unchanged. Judge the probe by the whole curve, not just endpoint FVU: if routing stays smooth and materially challenges the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, it remains worth later reserve consideration; if it is clearly weaker or less stable, close the family-worthiness question and return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5049:research/history/round_summaries/round_0084.json:80:    "description": "Run one matched architecture probe by switching only `ARCHITECTURE` to `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` while keeping the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the baseline loss/runtime settings unchanged. Judge the probe by the whole curve, not just endpoint FVU: if routing stays smooth and materially challenges the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, it remains worth later reserve consideration; if it is clearly weaker or less stable, close the family-worthiness question and return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5050:research/history/logs/agent_action_0007.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"topk/signum 在 1.6e-3 仍有改善，但边际收益已开始变小；本轮只将 LR 小幅上调到 1.8e-3，检验当前主线是否还能继续受益于更大步长，还是已经接近稳定收敛上界。","summary":"继续围绕 topk 主线推进，不开新 family，不换优化器，不动 K。本轮唯一主变量仍是学习率：从 1.6e-3 上调到 1.8e-3，回答“signum+topk 的较优 LR 是否仍在 1.6e-3 以上”这个单一问题。","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"这轮继续遵守单变量原则，并保持主线顺序不变。当前连续多轮上调 LR 均有改善，继续小步上探仍然是最直接的信息增益来源；风险在于可能开始出现收益饱和或曲线震荡，但这正是本轮需要验证的重点，若不再改善，下一轮就有充分依据结束 signum 的 LR 扫描。","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.8e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 7 继续只调 LR，在 1.6e-3 基础上做一档上探，确认 signum 主线是否尚未触顶。","当前判断不能只看最终 FVU，要重点看曲线后段是否仍平滑下降，还是出现边际收益衰减与震荡增大。","如果 1.8e-3 不再明显优于 1.6e-3，可认为 signum 的较优 LR 区间已接近当前值，下一轮应按顺序切换 optimizer。"],"next_hypotheses":["如果 1.8e-3 继续改善且曲线稳定，下一轮可继续只调 LR 做更细化上探。","如果 1.8e-3 与 1.6e-3 接近但稳定性更差，下一轮应结束 signum 的 LR 扫描并只改 optimizer。","如果 1.8e-3 明显更差或出现过冲，说明 signum 的较优 LR 已在 1.6e-3 附近，下一轮按顺序切换 optimizer。"],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5053:research/history/round_summaries/round_0207.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d b_i \u6765\u81ea\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u5728\u7ebf\u53ea\u505a\u5355\u6837\u672c top-k \u9009\u62e9\uff0c\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u65f6\u5c31\u662f\u5355\u5e93\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u5c5e\u4e8e\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u4e0a\u4e00\u8f6e factorized_topk \u7684 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM \u964d\u672c\u5c1d\u8bd5\u88ab policy \u62e6\u622a\uff0c\u4e14\u5f53\u524d <0.5x \u533a\u57df FVU \u660e\u663e\u53d7 scorer \u5bb9\u91cf\u9650\u5236\uff1b\u56e0\u6b64\u672c\u8f6e\u56fa\u5b9a K=64\u3001EF=2\u3001optimizer\u3001LR\uff0c\u4ec5\u628a architecture \u4ece factorized_topk \u5207\u5230 topk\uff0c\u9a8c\u8bc1\u53bb\u6389\u4f4e\u79e9 scorer bottleneck \u540e\uff0c\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u5728\u63a5\u8fd1\u4f4e\u5f00\u9500\u8fb9\u754c\u7684\u603b\u6210\u672c\u4e0b\u663e\u8457\u6539\u5584 FVU\u3002\u9884\u8ba1 total_cost \u7ea6 0.56x\uff0c\u867d\u7565\u9ad8\u4e8e 0.5x\uff0c\u4f46\u53ef\u4f5c\u4e3a\u6700\u90bb\u8fd1\u7684\u8d28\u91cf\u951a\u70b9\uff0c\u5e2e\u52a9\u5224\u65ad <0.5x \u533a\u57df\u7684\u4e3b\u8981\u74f6\u9888\u662f\u5426\u6765\u81ea factorization\u3002",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5059:research/history/logs/agent_action_0150.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"该 probe 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。与当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 相比，这个 matched probe 只去掉第二阶段 residual refinement，保持 K=128、EF=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 与其余主 recipe 不变，因此它只回答一个问题：当前两阶段结构本身是否真的值得为约 1.25x 而不是 0.75x 的 encoder 选择成本继续付费，还是单阶段 soft-codebook 父节点已经给出更好的 LUTurbo 总成本-质量权衡。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 matched 的 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 在明显更低 selection_cost 下只小幅损失 FVU，说明两阶段结构优势不足以覆盖其额外选择成本，下一轮按规则回到主线后应更谨慎看待该 family 的继续投入。","若 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 明显更差，说明当前两阶段 refinement 在 EF=2 下仍有真实结构价值，probe 完成后下一轮回到主线继续做 recipe 或成本轴工作。","若两者终点接近但 probe 训练更快、tokens_per_sec 更高，则把它记为更强的低成本对照点，但不在本轮直接切主线。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮是单次 matched architecture probe，严格只改 architecture，其余 K、EF、optimizer、LR 全部与主线参考配方一致。","lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 为扩展兼容 family，不属于不兼容候选，可合法进入兼容 frontier 对照。","该 probe 同时提供更贴近 LUTurbo 真实目标的对照，因为它把 encoder 选择成本从约 1.25x 降到约 0.75x，而部署查表成本仍在同一量级。","评估时必须同时记录 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时、final_total_tokens，避免把吞吐差异误读为纯架构质量结论。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"遵守本轮架构探针规则：只改 architecture，保持主线的 K、EXPANSION_FACTOR、OPTIMIZER、LR 与主要 recipe 不变。相比改成更远的 factorized_topk 或 lowrank_residual，这个 probe 与当前主线只有一个结构差异点，归因最干净，也最能回答“两阶段 refinement 本身值不值得继续”的问题。","summary":"执行一次严格 matched architecture probe：把当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 换成其单阶段父节点 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual，其余 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 全部保持不变，用一轮干净对照判断两阶段结构本身是否值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5060:research/history/logs/agent_action_0061.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 60 showed that matched `jumprelu` is competitive enough to avoid immediate dismissal but still clearly trails the strengthened `gated` anchor (`0.148243` vs `0.142923`), so the next single architecture question should test the closest support-selection near-neighbor rather than another looser variant. `routed` preserves LUTurbo's static-vector finite weighted-sum reconstruction contract while separating support routing from activation magnitude, so this round asks one clean yes/no question: under the exact current mainline recipe (`K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`), is `routed` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to justify any later follow-up as a deployment-relevant family?","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `routed`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `routed`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `routed` stays smooth and lands near the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because decoupled routing may offer a better LUTurbo cost/quality tradeoff than full gating; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"routed","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 61 matched-probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, and the settled mainline recipe fixed. `routed` is the highest-value remaining probe because it stays very close to the successful `gated` family while changing only the support-selection mechanism, which is directly relevant to LUTurbo online cost. The main risk is that the matched `gated`-tuned recipe may not be ideal for routed support, but that is acceptable for a family-worthiness screen.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 60 showed that matched `jumprelu` is only modestly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor (`0.148243` vs `0.142923`), so simpler support-shaping variants are still worth probing when mainline progress stalls.","`routed` remains LUTurbo-compatible because the reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architectural change is confined to using a separate router for support selection while preserving the same export form.","Round 61 should judge `routed` purely as a family-worthiness probe against the current `gated@128` anchor: if it is clearly worse or unstable, archive it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, keep exactly one later follow-up slot available."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `routed` is clearly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round and close this probe.","If matched `routed` is roughly competitive with a healthy curve, still return to the `gated` mainline next round, but preserve one later revisit because decoupled routing may better align with LUTurbo online-cost goals.","If matched `routed` unexpectedly beats the current `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy but schedule exactly one later follow-up for this family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5063:research/history/logs/agent_action_0166.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on lowrank_residual with K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3 unchanged. Final reconstruction formula is x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i, where U(Vx) is a static low-rank trunk library and {b_i} is a static residual dictionary. This is 扩展兼容: LUTurbo can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one static sparse residual lookup over fixed vector libraries. The probe asks whether removing the soft-codebook coarse branch and second-stage refinement is still worth keeping as a materially cheaper, faster compatible architecture in the low-EF regime.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If FVU is much worse without a meaningful runtime or throughput benefit, return to lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual next round and stop probing simpler parents.","If runtime is clearly better and the FVU loss is moderate, keep lowrank_residual as a low-selection-cost compatible Pareto point, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: 扩展兼容. Export path is static low-rank trunk library + static sparse residual dictionary; no dynamic decoder branch.","This probe changes only ARCHITECTURE and stays within the known EF=2 feasible selection-cost table.","Probe intent is to test whether the coarse soft-codebook branch is actually necessary under LUTurbo cost constraints, not to replace the mainline immediately."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This is a conservative probe with limited upside on FVU, but it gives a clean architectural contrast against the mainline and is less likely to incur avoidable runtime overhead. It directly tests whether the extra coarse branch and second sparse stage are paying for themselves in the current feasible regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe with ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_residual while keeping K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, and LR=3.0e-3 fixed. This yields a clean LUTurbo-compatible baseline to judge whether the mainline’s extra soft-codebook and two-stage structure is worth continuing.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5066:research/history/round_summaries/round_0165.json:18:    "summary": "Run a single matched architecture probe with ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_soft_codebook_residual while keeping K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, and LR=3.0e-3 fixed. The probe tests whether the simpler one-stage soft-codebook parent is still worth continuing as a lower-cost LUTurbo-compatible branch relative to the current two-stage mainline.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5092:research/history/logs/agent_action_0063.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `gated` mainline now stalled for ten rounds and `group_topk` already coming back slightly but clearly worse, the next highest-value matched architecture probe is `bucketed_topk`: it preserves the same fixed-`K` static weighted-sum decoder contract while changing only the selector architecture to a simple input-conditioned bucket specialization. This round answers one question only: under the matched `K=128`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EF=12` recipe, is `bucketed_topk` intrinsically strong enough to justify any later follow-up, or should it be ruled out immediately.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `bucketed_topk` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"bucketed_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 63 policy by changing exactly one primary variable: architecture. `bucketed_topk` is a cleaner probe than batch-coupled variants because it stays single-sample and export-compatible, and it is a cleaner runtime-aligned probe than heavier multi-stage or multi-branch families because it only asks whether light selector specialization helps enough to matter at all.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 63 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `bucketed_topk` after `group_topk` proved only roughly competitive and not mainline-worthy.","`bucketed_topk` remains directly compatible with LUTurbo export because the final reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architecture change is confined to encoder-side bucket specialization before top-k selection.","Judge this probe strictly as a family-worthiness test against matched `gated` K128: if it is clearly worse, discard it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, record the result but still return to the mainline per policy."],"next_hypotheses":["If `bucketed_topk` is clearly worse than matched `gated`, discard the family and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","If `bucketed_topk` is roughly competitive, record it as a possible selector-specialization direction but still return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy.","If `bucketed_topk` unexpectedly beats matched `gated`, schedule at most one later follow-up after the mandated return to the `gated` mainline."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5095:research/history/round_summaries/round_0043.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the active `gated` family and restore the current anchor recipe at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, with the same runtime knobs pinned, and change only the preprocess variable by enabling `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Judge this round by the whole trajectory, not just terminal FVU: if Hadamard conditioning makes early and mid training smoother and finishes below the current `0.148156` anchor, keep preprocess live; if it is neutral or worse again, close the preprocess branch and then move on to K mapping.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5100:research/history/round_summaries/round_0043.json:104:    "description": "Stay on the active `gated` family and restore the current anchor recipe at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, with the same runtime knobs pinned, and change only the preprocess variable by enabling `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Judge this round by the whole trajectory, not just terminal FVU: if Hadamard conditioning makes early and mid training smoother and finishes below the current `0.148156` anchor, keep preprocess live; if it is neutral or worse again, close the preprocess branch and then move on to K mapping.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5152:research/history/logs/agent_action_0076.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 75 closed the simplest single-stage `topk` alternative: under the matched `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3` recipe it was clearly worse than the `two_stage_residual` mainline, so the next and only remaining high-value matched architecture probe this round should target a different deployment tradeoff rather than another plain top-k variant. `jumprelu` is the best single yes/no probe because it preserves LUTurbo's static-library finite weighted-sum form while potentially reducing online selection complexity through thresholded support shaping instead of a full staged residual path. This round asks one question only: under the exact current mainline recipe, is `jumprelu` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to remain worth later consideration, or should it be ruled out as clearly inferior?","summary":"Use the one allowed matched architecture probe on `jumprelu`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the same aux/runtime settings, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `two_stage_residual` to `jumprelu`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `jumprelu` stays reasonably close with a healthy curve, keep it in reserve because its thresholded single-stage support path may lower LUTurbo online selection cost; if it is clearly worse throughout, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 76 rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, and the rest of the recipe fixed. `jumprelu` is a better use of the single probe than another standard top-k family because it tests a distinct support-selection mechanism that may be cheaper to deploy online while still satisfying the export contract. The main risk is that prior matched probing under an earlier regime already suggested weak reconstruction quality, but this is still the most informative remaining architecture-worthiness check under the current mainline anchor.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 76 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `jumprelu` against the current `two_stage_residual` mainline recipe, because it represents a distinct thresholded selector that may reduce LUTurbo online selection cost while preserving static exportability.","Judge this probe as a family-worthiness test only: compare matched `jumprelu@128` against the `two_stage_residual` reference at fixed `EF=12`, `signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, then return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `jumprelu` is reasonably close with a healthy curve, return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round but keep one later `jumprelu` revisit available because its selector path may be cheaper to deploy.","If matched `jumprelu` is clearly worse than `two_stage_residual` across the curve, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.","If matched `jumprelu` unexpectedly beats the current `two_stage_residual` reference, still return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round per policy, but record `jumprelu` as a high-priority later follow-up family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5170:research/history/round_summaries/round_0186.json:20:    "summary": "继续围绕同一主线 family 推进，不开新 family；固定 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=128, EF=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3`，仅把 `TRUNK_RANK` 从已验证无损的 32 再降到 16，测试更激进的 trunk 压缩是否仍能维持当前 LUTurbo 可部署质量。",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5175:research/history/round_summaries/round_0186.json:82:    "description": "继续围绕同一主线 family 推进，不开新 family；固定 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=128, EF=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3`，仅把 `TRUNK_RANK` 从已验证无损的 32 再降到 16，测试更激进的 trunk 压缩是否仍能维持当前 LUTurbo 可部署质量。",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5183:research/history/logs/agent_action_0075.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `two_stage_residual` mainline now stalled for five rounds, Round 75 is the single allowed matched architecture probe. The highest-value yes/no question is whether the simplest directly compatible alternative, `topk`, is still strong enough under the exact current mainline recipe to deserve any later revisit. `topk` preserves LUTurbo's static-vector finite weighted-sum export form while likely reducing online selection, coefficient, and lookup complexity versus a staged residual decomposition, so this probe asks one question only: at matched `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, is `topk` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to remain deployment-relevant, or should it be treated as clearly inferior to `two_stage_residual`?","summary":"Use the one allowed matched architecture probe on `topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the same aux/runtime settings, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `two_stage_residual` to `topk`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `topk` stays reasonably close with a healthy curve, keep it in reserve because its simpler single-stage lookup path may lower LUTurbo online cost; if it is clearly worse throughout, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 75 rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, and the main recipe fixed. `topk` is the most informative matched probe because it is directly compatible with LUTurbo's export contract and has a materially simpler online path than `two_stage_residual`, so even a moderate training-quality gap could still be acceptable. The main risk is that `topk` is already known to be weaker in prior regimes, but this round is explicitly a family-worthiness screen under the new mainline anchor rather than a commitment to switch families.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 75 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `topk` against the current `two_stage_residual` mainline recipe, because `topk` is the simplest directly compatible LUTurbo candidate and may reduce online selection and compensation cost despite weaker reconstruction.","Judge this probe as a family-worthiness test, not a recipe-tuning round: compare the full curve of matched `topk@128` against the `two_stage_residual` reference at fixed `EF=12`, `signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, then return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `topk` is reasonably close with a healthy curve, return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round but keep one later `topk` revisit available because its simpler deployment path may outweigh a modest FVU gap.","If matched `topk` is clearly worse than `two_stage_residual` across the curve, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.","If matched `topk` unexpectedly beats the current `two_stage_residual` reference, still return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round per policy, but record `topk` as the highest-priority later follow-up family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5196:research/history/logs/agent_action_0175.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` under the mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j`, where the bucket gate only changes stage-1/2 selector scores and all decoded terms still come from static libraries `{U,V}`, codebook `C`, and residual dictionary `B`. This is `扩展兼容` with a clean LUTurbo export path, but the matched EF=2 selector is likely not worth continuing because bucketed dual scorers raise encoder selection cost to about `2.5x h×n`, so the policy should reject it before spending a long training run.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune one cost knob at a time (`TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`) to improve the feasible Pareto point without changing architecture.","If a future bucketed revisit is desired, only do it as a cost-reduction study on the bucketed family itself with primary variable `TRUNK_RANK` or `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM`, not as another matched-architecture probe."],"notes_to_memory":["`bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is LUTurbo `扩展兼容`: bucket mixing changes selector-side scoring only; decode remains a finite weighted sum over static trunk/codebook/residual libraries.","At matched `K=128, EF=2`, the bucketed two-stage soft-codebook family estimates to about `selection_cost=2.5x` and is therefore over the `1.5x` hard budget; this makes it a likely fast policy-reject probe rather than a training candidate."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Single-variable discipline is preserved: architecture is the only changed dimension, while `K/EF/optimizer/LR` are pinned to the mainline recipe. I am choosing an intentionally decisive probe: it is informative even if rejected, because the low-EF budget constraint is now the main gate and this family is known to be runtime-heavier. This does not claim the family is universally bad; it only answers whether it is worth continuing on the current feasible low-cost frontier.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` with the mainline recipe unchanged otherwise. The family is LUTurbo-exportable (`扩展兼容`) via a static trunk library plus static codebook and residual dictionaries, but its matched EF=2 selector cost is expected to exceed budget (`~2.5x h×n`), so the likely result is a cheap policy rejection that cleanly answers: this architecture is not worth continuing as a low-cost mainline candidate right now.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5209:research/history/round_summaries/round_0130.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4fdd\u6301\u4e3a x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + \u03a3_j alpha_j^(2) b_j\u3002\u8fd9\u91cc low-rank trunk \u7684\u57fa\u5411\u91cf\u5e93 U\u3001soft codebook \u5e93 {c_m}\u3001\u4ee5\u53ca\u4e24\u9636\u6bb5 residual \u5b57\u5178\u5e93 {b_i} \u90fd\u662f\u9759\u6001\u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u7684\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff1b\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u8be5 family \u5728 EF=2 \u65f6 selection_cost \u7ea6 1.25x h\u00d7n\uff0c\u6ee1\u8db3 \u22641.5x \u7684\u786c\u7ea6\u675f\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u56de\u7b54\u4e00\u4e2a\u95ee\u9898\uff1a\u5728\u6700\u8fd1\u8bad\u7ec3\u8017\u65f6\u6ce2\u52a8\u4e0a\u5347\u4e14 LR=2.4e-3 \u5df2\u7ecf\u9a8c\u8bc1\u65e0\u6536\u76ca\u540e\uff0c\u53c2\u8003\u914d\u65b9 ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, EF=2, K=128, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3 \u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u7136\u7a33\u5b9a\u590d\u73b0\u5f53\u524d feasible frontier\uff0c\u5e76\u7ed9\u51fa\u5e72\u51c0\u7684 tokens_per_sec\u3001\u603b\u8017\u65f6\u3001final_total_tokens \u53c2\u7167\u70b9\u3002",
