research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5252:research/history/round_summaries/round_0144.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4fdd\u6301\u4e3a x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + \u03a3_j alpha_j^(2) b_j\u3002low-rank trunk \u57fa\u5e93 U\u3001soft codebook \u9759\u6001\u5e93 {c_m}\u3001\u4ee5\u53ca\u4e24\u9636\u6bb5 residual \u9759\u6001\u5b57\u5178\u5e93 {b_i} \u90fd\u53ef\u79bb\u7ebf\u5bfc\u51fa\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u6620\u5c04\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff1b\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u8be5 family \u5728 EF=2 \u65f6 encoder selection_cost \u7ea6 1.25x h\u00d7n\uff0c\u6ee1\u8db3 \u22641.5x \u786c\u7ea6\u675f\u3002\u7ecf\u8fc7 r141-r143 \u7684 matched architecture probes \u540e\uff0c\u5f53\u524d\u5df2\u7ecf\u91cd\u65b0\u786e\u8ba4 two-stage soft-codebook \u4e3b\u7ebf\u5728\u8d28\u91cf\u4e0a\u663e\u8457\u4f18\u4e8e lowrank_soft_codebook_residual\u3001lowrank_residual \u4e0e factorized_topk\uff0c\u4f46\u8fd9\u4e9b probe \u7684\u603b\u8017\u65f6\u66f4\u77ed\uff0c\u8bf4\u660e\u8fd1\u671f\u8fd0\u884c\u4ee3\u4ef7\u7ed3\u8bba\u53ef\u80fd\u6df7\u6742\u4e86\u67b6\u6784\u5dee\u5f02\u800c\u975e\u4e3b\u7ebf recipe \u6f02\u79fb\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u56de\u7b54\u4e00\u4e2a\u95ee\u9898\uff1a\u56de\u5230\u4e3b\u7ebf\u53c2\u8003\u914d\u65b9 ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual\u3001K=128\u3001EF=2\u3001signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u505a\u4e00\u6b21 clean baseline \u590d\u9a8c\uff0c\u5f53\u524d feasible \u4e3b\u7ebf\u7684 FVU\u3001\u8bad\u7ec3\u66f2\u7ebf\u3001tokens_per_sec\u3001\u603b\u8017\u65f6\u4e0e final_total_tokens \u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u7a33\u5b9a\u53ef\u590d\u73b0\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u4e3a\u540e\u7eed\u7ee7\u7eed\u505a\u4e3b\u7ebf recipe \u8c03\u6574\u63d0\u4f9b\u5e72\u51c0\u951a\u70b9\u3002",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5305:research/history/round_summaries/round_0054.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and keep the family reference recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` to complete the downward side of the LR localization around the current Hadamard anchor. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if the lower LR yields a smoother mid/late descent and finishes below `0.142923`, then Hadamard shifted the preferred step size downward; if it is flatter or worse, lock `2.0e-3` as the operative mainline LR and stop the LR branch again.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5310:research/history/round_summaries/round_0054.json:104:    "description": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and keep the family reference recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` to complete the downward side of the LR localization around the current Hadamard anchor. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if the lower LR yields a smoother mid/late descent and finishes below `0.142923`, then Hadamard shifted the preferred step size downward; if it is flatter or worse, lock `2.0e-3` as the operative mainline LR and stop the LR branch again.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5314:research/history/round_summaries/round_0103.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Rounds 101 and 102 showed that the controller still treats `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual K=128 EXPANSION_FACTOR=12 OPTIMIZER=signum LR=2.0e-3` as the official mainline reference recipe for single-axis comparisons, so the cleanest next question is optimizer choice at that exact anchor. Switching only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam` while holding the reference `LR=2.0e-3` fixed tests whether this family has any optimizer headroom before spending another round on an optimizer-local LR callback, and it should be judged by the full curve shape against the signum reference rather than only the terminal FVU.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5372:research/history/round_summaries/round_0112.json:58:      "\u82e5 EF=2 \u7684 FVU \u9000\u5316\u8fc7\u5927\uff0c\u5219\u4fdd\u7559\u8be5 family \u4f46\u8f6c\u5411\u5355\u53d8\u91cf\u964d\u4f4e FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM \u6216 TRUNK_RANK\uff0c\u63a2\u7d22 EF=2 \u4e0b\u66f4\u4fbf\u5b9c scorer \u7684\u6700\u4f18\u70b9\u3002"
