research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5528:research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:20:    "summary": "Adopt the reproduced Hadamard recipe as the current `gated` reference and begin K mapping under that stronger setting. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `K` from `128` to `96`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory as well as the endpoint: if the improved recipe yields a smooth curve and clearly beats the old `gated@96` control (`0.168960`), then the preprocess gain transfers to a lower-cost point and the family deserves at least one more K step; if it falls back toward the earlier K96 result or loses its curve advantage, keep the improved recipe mainly as a K128 anchor.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5532:research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:104:    "description": "Adopt the reproduced Hadamard recipe as the current `gated` reference and begin K mapping under that stronger setting. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `K` from `128` to `96`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory as well as the endpoint: if the improved recipe yields a smooth curve and clearly beats the old `gated@96` control (`0.168960`), then the preprocess gain transfers to a lower-cost point and the family deserves at least one more K step; if it falls back toward the earlier K96 result or loses its curve advantage, keep the improved recipe mainly as a K128 anchor.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5548:research/history/round_summaries/round_0057.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the active `gated` family and hold the now-settled mainline recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `128` to `96` to refresh the first lower-cost deployment point under the finalized recipe. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just terminal FVU: if the curve remains smooth and lands near or below the current `gated@96` frontier (`0.160940`), then the strengthened recipe is stable enough to treat that lower-cost point as a reliable LUTurbo candidate; if it degrades materially, re-open the question of whether the prior K sweep depended on transient recipe-state rather than the settled mainline.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5552:research/history/round_summaries/round_0057.json:104:    "description": "Stay on the active `gated` family and hold the now-settled mainline recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `128` to `96` to refresh the first lower-cost deployment point under the finalized recipe. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just terminal FVU: if the curve remains smooth and lands near or below the current `gated@96` frontier (`0.160940`), then the strengthened recipe is stable enough to treat that lower-cost point as a reliable LUTurbo candidate; if it degrades materially, re-open the question of whether the prior K sweep depended on transient recipe-state rather than the settled mainline.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5556:research/history/round_summaries/round_0042.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the active `gated` family and return to the `signum` anchor at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, with the same runtime knobs pinned, and change only the loss-side variable `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0`. Judge this run by curve shape as well as terminal FVU: if dropping aux yields a smoother or lower full trajectory than the current `0.148156` anchor, then the stronger LR has made the auxiliary term unnecessary or harmful; if it regresses or destabilizes training, keep the default aux loss and move on to preprocess.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5560:research/history/round_summaries/round_0042.json:104:    "description": "Stay on the active `gated` family and return to the `signum` anchor at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, with the same runtime knobs pinned, and change only the loss-side variable `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0`. Judge this run by curve shape as well as terminal FVU: if dropping aux yields a smoother or lower full trajectory than the current `0.148156` anchor, then the stronger LR has made the auxiliary term unnecessary or harmful; if it regresses or destabilizes training, keep the default aux loss and move on to preprocess.",
