research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5677:research/history/round_summaries/round_0074.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 73 answered the optimizer question clearly: `adam` on the `two_stage_residual` reference recipe failed catastrophically (`FVU=33.8917`), so the optimizer branch should be considered closed and `signum` remains the correct mainline optimizer for this family. Following the prescribed order, the next single mainline question is now loss shaping: with `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed, is the default auxiliary loss helping this staged residual decomposition, or does removing it improve the full training trajectory and final FVU?",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5712:research/history/round_summaries/round_0206.json:17:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: factorized_topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4ecd\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d b_i \u662f\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u4e2d\u7684\u57fa\u5411\u91cf\uff1b\u4f4e\u79e9 factor scorer \u53ea\u5f71\u54cd\u5728\u7ebf\u9009\u62e9\u5206\u6570\uff0c\u4e0d\u6539\u53d8\u6700\u7ec8 decoder \u7684\u5355\u5e93\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c\u5f62\u5f0f\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u4e3a\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u4fdd\u6301 K=64\u3001EF=2\u3001optimizer\u3001LR \u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u53ea\u5355\u53d8\u91cf\u4e0b\u8c03 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM \u5230 256\uff0c\u76ee\u6807\u662f\u5728\u4fdd\u7559\u5f53\u524d <0.5x \u4e3b\u70b9\u7684\u67e5\u8868\u94fe\u8def\u957f\u5ea6\u4e0d\u53d8\u65f6\uff0c\u8fdb\u4e00\u6b65\u538b\u4f4e encoder selection cost \u4e0e\u8bad\u7ec3\u65f6\u5ef6\uff0c\u4e89\u53d6\u62ff\u5230\u6bd4 0.44x \u66f4\u4f4e\u3001\u4e14 FVU \u660e\u663e\u597d\u4e8e K=32 \u7684\u65b0\u4f4e\u5f00\u9500\u70b9\u3002",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0221.stdout.log:5751:research/history/round_summaries/round_0058.json:20:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe on `topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `topk`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `topk` stays smooth and closes most of the gap to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is still worth later family-level consideration because its deployment path is simpler; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.",
