research/history/round_summaries/round_0060.json:80:      "`jumprelu` remains LUTurbo-compatible because the reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architectural change is confined to threshold-based support shaping before top-k selection.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0060.json:81:      "Round 60 should judge `jumprelu` purely as a family-worthiness probe against the current `gated@128` anchor: if it is clearly worse or unstable, archive it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, keep exactly one later follow-up slot available."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0060.json:84:      "If matched `jumprelu` is clearly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round and close this probe.",
