research/history/logs/agent_action_0207.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"quality_anchor_near_low_cost_boundary","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 b_i 来自单个静态向量库；在线只做单样本 top-k 选择，导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时就是单库查表 + 加权求和，因此属于直接兼容。上一轮 factorized_topk 的 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM 降本尝试被 policy 拦截，且当前 <0.5x 区域 FVU 明显受 scorer 容量限制；因此本轮固定 K=64、EF=2、optimizer、LR，仅把 architecture 从 factorized_topk 切到 topk，验证去掉低秩 scorer bottleneck 后，是否能在接近低开销边界的总成本下显著改善 FVU。预计 total_cost 约 0.56x，虽略高于 0.5x，但可作为最邻近的质量锚点，帮助判断 <0.5x 区域的主要瓶颈是否来自 factorization。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 topk@K64 相比 factorized_topk@K64 明显改善 FVU，则说明当前低开销区主要受低秩 scorer 限制，下一步应考虑在更接近 0.5x 的边界上探索更轻但非 factorized 的选择机制。","如果 topk@K64 提升有限，则说明问题主要来自预算本身而非 factorized scorer，下一步应转向新的低成本 family 或更激进的小库/小K 结构，而不是继续在 scorer 形态上纠缠。"],"notes_to_memory":["topk 是最干净的直接兼容单库基线，可用于判断 factorized_topk 在低成本区的 FVU 损失到底有多少来自 scorer factorization。","本轮只改 architecture，保持 K=64 这个当前最佳 <0.5x 邻近点的查表预算不变，便于归因。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"该提案严格满足单变量原则，并针对 r206 的 policy_reject 与当前开放假设做了最小转向。代价是总成本会从 0.44x 上升到约 0.56x，不能直接补 <0.5x 前沿，但它能高信息量地判断 factorized scorer 是否是低开销区 FVU 过差的主因。","summary":"切换到直接兼容的 topk family，固定 K=64、EF=2、signum、LR=3e-3，只改变 architecture，获得一个贴近低开销边界的质量锚点，用来判断去掉 factorized scorer 后 FVU 能提升多少。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0169.json:7:  "family_name": "lowrank_jumprelu_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0169.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary; JumpReLU only changes the single-sample support/coef shaping before top-k, not the exported decoder basis. This is `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a fixed residual vector library, with the learned thresholds used only in online selection. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost should stay within the `\u2264 1.5\u00d7h\u00d7n` hard budget and remain below the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline. The single question is whether this thresholded low-rank single-stage selector is intrinsically worth keeping in the current low-EF deployable regime, or whether the mainline\u2019s soft-codebook plus two-stage refinement remains clearly necessary.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0169.json:20:    "summary": "Run one valid matched architecture probe on `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` while keeping the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether a thresholded single-stage low-rank selector is worth any continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0169.json:23:    "family_name": "lowrank_jumprelu_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0169.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe fields. After `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` and `lowrank_gated_residual` both failed to pressure the mainline, `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is the highest-value remaining feasible matched probe because it preserves LUTurbo exportability, stays in the low-EF budgeted regime, and tests a simpler thresholded selector that could reduce total online complexity if quality holds up. The main risk is that historical evidence for JumpReLU-style selectors has been weak, so this may mainly confirm that a single-stage thresholded low-rank branch cannot recover enough quality.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0169.json:30:        "value": "lowrank_jumprelu_residual"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0169.json:56:      "If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is clearly worse than the mainline in both FVU and runtime metrics, discard it and return to `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0169.json:69:    "architecture": "lowrank_jumprelu_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0169.json:78:    "description": "Run one valid matched architecture probe on `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` while keeping the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether a thresholded single-stage low-rank selector is worth any continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0169.json:79:    "self_review": "This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe fields. After `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` and `lowrank_gated_residual` both failed to pressure the mainline, `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is the highest-value remaining feasible matched probe because it preserves LUTurbo exportability, stays in the low-EF budgeted regime, and tests a simpler thresholded selector that could reduce total online complexity if quality holds up. The main risk is that historical evidence for JumpReLU-style selectors has been weak, so this may mainly confirm that a single-stage thresholded low-rank branch cannot recover enough quality.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0224.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: lowrank_factorized_residual\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_r \u03b2_r u_r + \u03a3_i \u03b1_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {u_r} \u662f\u9759\u6001 trunk \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u3001{b_i} \u662f\u9759\u6001 residual \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u5728\u7ebf\u4fa7\u53ea\u8ba1\u7b97 trunk \u7cfb\u6570 \u03b2_r \u4e0e residual \u7a00\u758f\u7cfb\u6570 \u03b1_i\uff0c\u518d\u6267\u884c trunk \u67e5\u8868 + residual \u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002r223 \u5df2\u786e\u8ba4 `topk@EF1,K248` \u7684 recipe \u8f74\u7ee7\u7eed\u5411\u4e0a\u63a8 LR \u53ea\u5e26\u6765\u66f4\u5dee FVU \u548c\u660e\u663e\u66f4\u5dee\u541e\u5410\uff0c\u8bf4\u660e\u5f53\u524d <0.5x \u6700\u5f3a topk \u951a\u70b9\u5df2\u57fa\u672c\u9971\u548c\uff1b\u540c\u65f6 r221 \u8bf4\u660e\u76f4\u63a5\u538b `TRUNK_RANK` \u4f1a\u7834\u574f lowrank_factorized_residual \u7684 trunk \u8868\u8fbe\u3002\u57fa\u4e8e r210 \u8fd9\u4e2a\u9ad8\u8d28\u91cf\u53c2\u8003\u70b9\uff0c\u672c\u8f6e\u4e25\u683c\u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a env \u53c2\u6570 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96`\uff0c\u4fdd\u7559 `K=64, EF=1, signum, LR=3e-3` \u4e0e\u5b8c\u6574 trunk \u5206\u652f\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u7528\u66f4\u77ed\u7684 factorized scorer \u94fe\u8def\u66ff\u4ee3\u9ed8\u8ba4\u8f83\u5bbd\u9690\u85cf\u5c42\uff0c\u6d4b\u8bd5\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u628a\u8be5 family \u7684 total_cost \u4ece 0.69x \u538b\u5230\u7ea6 0.48x\uff0c\u540c\u65f6\u5c3d\u91cf\u4fdd\u7559\u663e\u8457\u4f18\u4e8e\u540c\u6210\u672c topk \u7684 FVU\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0224.json:35:      "r223 \u7ed9\u51fa\u660e\u786e\u8d1f\u9762\u4fe1\u53f7\uff1a`topk@EF1,K248` \u7684\u5411\u4e0a LR \u5206\u652f\u5df2\u4e0d\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\uff0c\u540e\u7eed\u5e94\u628a\u6ce8\u610f\u529b\u4ece topk recipe \u6e05\u6d17\u8f6c\u56de\u65b0\u4f4e\u6210\u672c\u7ed3\u6784\u3002",
