research/history/round_summaries/round_0013.json:17:    "hypothesis": "The `signum` learning-rate sweep has now mapped a narrow optimum region around `1.7e-3` to `1.75e-3`, with no clear additional gain from pushing LR higher. This round changes only the loss-shaping axis by lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` from the current implicit baseline `0.03125` to `0.015625` while keeping `topk/signum/K128/EF12/LR=1.7e-3` fixed, to test whether a weaker auxiliary dead-feature pressure improves late-stage reconstruction once the main LR regime is already near its peak.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0013.json:18:    "summary": "Stay on the `topk` mainline and move to the next recipe axis after LR refinement: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=1.7e-3` fixed, and reduce `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.015625` to answer whether lighter auxiliary regularization yields a better training curve and lower final FVU.",
