research/history/round_summaries/round_0028.json:79:      "Round 28 inserts exactly one matched architecture probe after five consecutive non-improving topk rounds; the probe must be judged as a family-worthiness test, not as a new mainline pivot.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0028.json:80:      "`whitened_topk` is directly compatible with LUTurbo's deployment form because the final reconstruction remains a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architectural change is confined to encoder-side preconditioning and selection.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0028.json:81:      "Judge this probe by full curve shape plus final FVU relative to the stabilized K128 topk control: if it is clearly worse or unstable, drop the family and return to topk; if it is competitive or better, it earns at most one follow-up slot later, but the immediate next round should still return to the topk mainline."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0028.json:84:      "If `whitened_topk` is clearly worse than the stabilized `topk` control, archive it immediately and return to mainline topk recipe work next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0028.json:85:      "If `whitened_topk` is roughly competitive with a smoother or still-descending curve, record it as a promising probe result but still return to the topk mainline next round per policy.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0028.json:86:      "If `whitened_topk` beats the matched topk control, schedule exactly one later follow-up on the same family after the mandated return to the mainline."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0028.json:97:    "architecture": "whitened_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0028.json:105:    "description": "Run one matched architecture probe on `whitened_topk`. Keep `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and the current stable non-compiled runtime/aux recipe fixed, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `topk` to `whitened_topk` to test whether this directly export-compatible variant is worth continuing as a family.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0065.json:19:    "hypothesis": "With the `gated` mainline stalled for twelve rounds and recent single-stage selector probes (`group_topk`, `bucketed_topk`, `codebook_topk`) all failing to beat it, the next highest-value matched architecture probe is `two_stage_residual`: it remains LUTurbo-compatible because the reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over static libraries, but distributes the fixed `K=128` budget across two sequential residual passes. This round answers one question only: under the matched `signum`/`LR=2.0e-3`/`EF=12` recipe, is that staged residual decomposition intrinsically strong enough to justify any later follow-up, or should it be ruled out immediately.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0023.json:7:  "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0023.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 14 showed that lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` below the `topk/signum/K128/EF12/LR=1.6e-3` reference did not improve FVU, which leaves the opposite loss-shaping question open: the current mainline may be slightly under-regularized rather than over-regularized. This round changes only `AUXK_ALPHA`, increasing it from `0.03125` to `0.0625` while keeping the exact K128 reference recipe fixed, to test whether stronger dead-feature pressure improves late-stage reconstruction or curve stability.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0023.json:20:    "summary": "Run a single loss-axis check on the exact topk mainline reference recipe: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `K=128`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and raise `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.0625` to answer whether the current baseline benefits from stronger auxiliary pressure.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0023.json:23:    "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0023.json:25:    "self_review": "This stays on the active `topk` family, changes no core axis relative to the declared mainline reference recipe, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and avoids repeating the invalid Round 22 pattern that mixed a non-core tweak with `K=96`. The main risk is that stronger auxiliary pressure could slightly hurt reconstruction, but after the weaker-aux test already failed on K128, this is the cleanest remaining single-variable loss-shaping question on the true reference backbone.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0023.json:30:        "value": "topk"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0023.json:73:    "architecture": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0023.json:82:    "description": "Run a single loss-axis check on the exact topk mainline reference recipe: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `K=128`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and raise `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.0625` to answer whether the current baseline benefits from stronger auxiliary pressure.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0023.json:83:    "self_review": "This stays on the active `topk` family, changes no core axis relative to the declared mainline reference recipe, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and avoids repeating the invalid Round 22 pattern that mixed a non-core tweak with `K=96`. The main risk is that stronger auxiliary pressure could slightly hurt reconstruction, but after the weaker-aux test already failed on K128, this is the cleanest remaining single-variable loss-shaping question on the true reference backbone.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0213.json:17:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: lowrank_factorized_residual\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_r beta_r u_r + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {u_r} \u662f\u9759\u6001 trunk \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff0c{b_i} \u662f\u9759\u6001 residual \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u5728\u7ebf\u4fa7\u53ea\u8ba1\u7b97\u7cfb\u6570 beta_r \u4e0e alpha_i\uff0c\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u65f6\u53ef\u62c6\u6210 trunk \u5e93\u67e5\u8868\u52a0\u6743\u548c\u4e0e residual \u5e93\u67e5\u8868\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u4e24\u90e8\u5206\u90fd\u6ee1\u8db3\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u4e0a\u7684\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u57fa\u4e8e r210 \u5df2\u5728\u5f53\u524d family \u4e0a\u62ff\u5230 0.69x / 0.1256 \u4e14 tokens_per_sec \u7ea6 166.6k\u3001\u603b\u8017\u65f6 291s\uff0c\u5f53\u524d\u6700\u503c\u5f97\u56de\u7b54\u7684\u5355\u4e00\u95ee\u9898\u4e0d\u662f\u518d\u6362 family\uff0c\u800c\u662f\u8be5\u70b9\u7684\u9ad8\u6210\u672c\u662f\u5426\u4e3b\u8981\u7531 trunk \u8fc7\u5bbd\u5bfc\u81f4\uff1b\u672c\u8f6e\u4ec5\u5c06 TRUNK_RANK \u4e0b\u8c03\u5230 16\uff0c\u6d4b\u8bd5\u80fd\u5426\u5728\u4fdd\u6301\u660e\u663e\u4f18\u4e8e topk@0.31x \u7684 FVU \u524d\u63d0\u4e0b\uff0c\u628a total_cost \u5c3d\u91cf\u538b\u5411\u5e76\u6700\u597d\u538b\u5165 <0.5x \u533a\u57df\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0213.json:33:      "r210 \u8bf4\u660e lowrank_factorized_residual \u5728\u4f4e EF \u4e0b\u5177\u5907\u5f88\u5f3a\u8d28\u91cf\u6f5c\u529b\uff0c\u4e14\u8fd0\u884c\u541e\u5410\u4f18\u4e8e\u8fd1\u671f topk \u7ebf\uff1b\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u8981\u77db\u76fe\u662f\u6210\u672c\u800c\u975e\u8bad\u7ec3\u4e0d\u7a33\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0213.json:37:      "\u5982\u679c TRUNK_RANK=16 \u8fdb\u5165 <0.5x \u4e14 FVU \u4ecd\u660e\u663e\u4f18\u4e8e topk@EF1,K64\uff0c\u5219\u56fa\u5b9a\u8be5 family \u540e\u53ea\u6cbf K \u8f74\u8865\u4e00\u4e2a\u70b9\u3002",
research/history/logs/agent_action_0220.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_factorized_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"32"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r beta_r u_r + Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {u_r} 是 trunk 静态向量库、{b_i} 是 residual 静态向量库；factorized residual scorer 只影响在线选择与系数计算，不改变 decoder 端导出形态，因此可直接落到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路，兼容性判断为扩展兼容。基于 r210 已证明该 family 在 K=64、EF=1 下能以 0.69x 拿到 0.1256 FVU，当前主矛盾是 trunk 成本过高而不是训练质量不足；本轮严格锚定 r210，只改一个主轴 TRUNK_RANK，从 auto≈256 下调到 32，测试是否能把 total_cost 明确压入 <0.5x 区域，同时尽量保留明显优于同成本 topk 的 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 TRUNK_RANK=32 仍明显优于 <0.5x 区域 topk 前沿，则继续相对本轮单变量下探 TRUNK_RANK=16，检查成本-质量拐点。","如果 TRUNK_RANK=32 的 FVU 退化过大，则保留 r210 作为质量锚点，转向同 family 的单变量 K 轴或回到 topk 前沿继续补点。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_factorized_residual 的导出形式稳定为 trunk 静态库 + residual 静态库的有限加权和，满足 LUTurbo 扩展兼容约束。","r210 的质量信号很强且训练吞吐约 166.6k tokens/s、总耗时 291s，说明该 family 值得优先做成本压缩而不是直接放弃。","在 EF=1、K=64 下，TRUNK_RANK 是同时影响 encoder 与 deployment 的最高杠杆单变量；先压 trunk 比继续加 K 更符合当前 <0.5x 目标区。"],"primary_variable":"other_param","reference_round":210,"self_review":"该提案满足单变量原则：相对 r210 只改 TRUNK_RANK，其余核心配方保持不变。选择 32 而不是 16，是因为它仍应明显低于 0.5x，同时比更激进的 trunk 压缩更有机会保住 r210 展现出的质量优势；主要风险是 trunk 过窄后 coarse 补偿能力不足，FVU 可能回落到接近 topk。","summary":"相对 r210 的 lowrank_factorized_residual@K64,EF1 做一次严格 param_only 成本压缩，只下调 TRUNK_RANK 到 32，优先验证能否把该高质量 family 推入 total_cost < 0.5x 区域。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0219.json:7:  "family_name": "factorized_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0219.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: factorized_topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {b_i} \u6765\u81ea\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u4f4e\u79e9 factorized scorer \u53ea\u5f71\u54cd\u5728\u7ebf\u6253\u5206\u4e0e\u9009\u5740\uff0c\u4e0d\u6539\u53d8 decoder \u7aef\u4ecd\u662f\u5355\u5e93\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u5355\u5e93\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u4e3a\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002r214-r218 \u5df2\u8868\u660e topk@EF1 \u6cbf K \u8f74\u7ee7\u7eed\u52a0\u9884\u7b97\u4ecd\u80fd\u6539\u5584 FVU\uff0c\u4f46\u6700\u8fd1\u4e24\u8f6e\u6536\u76ca\u5df2\u660e\u663e\u53d8\u5c0f\u4e14\u603b\u8017\u65f6\u4e0a\u5347\u5230 417s\uff0c\u8bf4\u660e\u5355\u7eaf\u5806 topk \u67e5\u8868\u9884\u7b97\u63a5\u8fd1\u8fb9\u9645\u6536\u76ca\u6781\u9650\uff1b\u672c\u8f6e\u56e0\u6b64\u5207\u5230\u66f4\u4f4e encoder \u6210\u672c\u7684 factorized_topk\uff0c\u5e76\u628a K \u63d0\u5230 EF=1 \u4e0b\u7684\u6ee1\u5b57\u5178 256\uff0c\u6d4b\u8bd5\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u5728\u603b\u6210\u672c\u4ecd\u9884\u8ba1\u7ea6 0.44x\u3001\u7ee7\u7eed\u4f4d\u4e8e <0.5x \u533a\u57df\u7684\u524d\u63d0\u4e0b\uff0c\u7528\u66f4\u4fbf\u5b9c\u7684 selector \u6362\u53d6\u66f4\u9ad8\u53ef\u7528 K\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u62ff\u5230\u63a5\u8fd1\u6216\u4f18\u4e8e topk@0.49x \u7684\u4f4e\u5f00\u9500 FVU\u3002",
