research/history/round_summaries/round_0015.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` on the accepted `topk/signum/K128/EF12/LR=1.6e-3` recipe did not improve FVU, which suggests the current K128 recipe is close to saturated on the loss-shaping axis. This round changes only `K`, dropping from `128` to `64` while keeping the same family, optimizer, LR, and EF fixed, to test whether LUTurbo can gain a materially cheaper decomposition point with still-acceptable reconstruction quality on the current best-understood topk recipe.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0015.json:20:    "summary": "Move to the K axis on the stabilized topk mainline: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and set `K=64` to measure the first real quality-cost tradeoff point in the allowed K set.",
