research/history/logs/agent_action_0026.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 25 crashed with `first_step_timeout` while rerunning the exact K128 anchor, so the immediate question is not recipe quality but whether the timeout was caused by compile-time startup overhead rather than by the `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/K=128/EF=12` recipe itself. This round changes only `COMPILE_MODEL`, turning it off on the exact reference backbone to test whether the baseline can complete cleanly and recover an interpretable curve.","summary":"Run a runtime-stabilization check on the exact active topk reference recipe: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and the reference aux/runtime knobs fixed, and change only `COMPILE_MODEL` from `1` to `0` to see whether the recent `first_step_timeout` is a compile-path startup issue rather than a recipe issue.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active family, answers one blocker-first question, and is the smallest interpretable response to a fresh `first_step_timeout`. The main risk is that disabling compile changes throughput and may slightly affect absolute training dynamics, but right now stable execution is more important than squeezing recipe conclusions out of a run that never reached a trustworthy curve.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 25 failed with `first_step_timeout` on the exact reference baseline, so the immediate blocker is run stability rather than any new recipe conclusion.","The cleanest single-variable runtime probe is to disable `COMPILE_MODEL` on the same anchor recipe and check whether startup completes and the training curve becomes observable again.","Judge this round first by whether it clears the timeout and produces a normal curve; only if it runs cleanly should the resulting shape be used to inform the next LR or optimizer decision."],"next_hypotheses":["If `COMPILE_MODEL=0` clears the timeout and reproduces the expected K128 curve band, resume mainline recipe work from the stabilized anchor.","If the run still hits `first_step_timeout`, treat the blocker as broader runtime instability rather than compile-specific and choose the next round around execution stability rather than recipe tuning.","If `COMPILE_MODEL=0` runs but materially alters curve shape or final quality, keep that distinction explicit and avoid mixing it with recipe conclusions from compiled runs."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
