research/history/round_summaries/round_0011.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Because the policy layer validates `param_only` rounds against the current topk family best and only accepts one changed core axis, the deferred Adam callback cannot be isolated cleanly from the `signum@1.6e-3` reference. This round returns to the accepted mainline axis and changes only `LR`, setting `topk/signum/K128/EF12` to `1.7e-3` to resolve whether the useful region is a narrow band just above `1.6e-3` or whether the `1.8e-3` degradation already marks the onset of instability.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0011.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the topk mainline and do a pure signum learning-rate refinement: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `K=128`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and move `LR` from `1.6e-3` to `1.7e-3` to answer one question about the local peak of the current stable recipe.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0011.json:23:    "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0011.json:25:    "self_review": "This action is compatible with the stricter single-axis validator because only `lr` changes relative to the current topk reference recipe. It also stays within the active family and avoids another policy rejection while still extracting useful curve-shape information near the current best signum regime.",
