research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 28 showed that `whitened_topk` is not worth continuing: under a matched probe it failed catastrophically, so the next and only remaining useful question in this probe slot is whether a different directly compatible support-selection variant has any architectural merit at all. `gated` preserves the same static-dictionary weighted-sum reconstruction form as `topk` while changing only how support is selected and scaled, so this round asks a single yes/no question: is `gated` competitive enough under a matched K128/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF12 probe to justify any future follow-up.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:20:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe on `gated`. Keep `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and the current stabilized runtime/aux recipe fixed, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `topk` to `gated` to test whether this directly export-compatible family is worth continuing.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the matched-probe rule by changing only the architecture axis, keeps the core mainline recipe fixed, and selects a family that remains compatible with LUTurbo's static-vector weighted-sum deployment contract. The main risk is that the extra gating branch may add training complexity without improving quality or runtime-aligned sparsity behavior, but that is exactly the family-worthiness question this probe is intended to answer before returning to the topk mainline.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:79:      "Round 28 ruled out `whitened_topk` as a promising matched probe candidate because it was massively worse than the topk control.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:81:      "Judge this round as a pure family-worthiness probe against the stabilized K128 topk control: if it is clearly worse or unstable, archive it and return to topk next round; if it is competitive, record that but still return to the mainline per policy."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:84:      "If `gated` is clearly worse than matched `topk`, archive it immediately and return to the topk mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:85:      "If `gated` is competitive but not clearly better, record it as a plausible alternative family and still return to the topk mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:86:      "If `gated` beats the matched `topk` control, schedule at most one later follow-up after the mandated return to the mainline."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:105:    "description": "Run one matched architecture probe on `gated`. Keep `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and the current stabilized runtime/aux recipe fixed, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `topk` to `gated` to test whether this directly export-compatible family is worth continuing.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:106:    "self_review": "This obeys the matched-probe rule by changing only the architecture axis, keeps the core mainline recipe fixed, and selects a family that remains compatible with LUTurbo's static-vector weighted-sum deployment contract. The main risk is that the extra gating branch may add training complexity without improving quality or runtime-aligned sparsity behavior, but that is exactly the family-worthiness question this probe is intended to answer before returning to the topk mainline.",
research/history/logs/agent_action_0212.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_factorized_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"32"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r beta_r u_r + Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {u_r} 是静态 trunk 向量库、{b_i} 是静态 residual 向量库；factorized scorer 只影响在线选择与系数计算，不改变 decoder 端的静态库有限加权和形式，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路，兼容性为扩展兼容。单主变量选择 TRUNK_RANK：在保持 ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_factorized_residual、K=64、EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3 不变时，把 trunk_rank 从当前 auto≈128 下调到 32，测试当前 0.69x 点的主要冗余是否来自过大的 trunk 库；若 trunk 只是提供粗补偿而 residual 分支已承担主要表达，则可把 encoder+deployment 总成本一口气压入 <0.5x 区域，同时维持明显优于 topk@0.31x 的 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 TRUNK_RANK=32 仍保持明显优于 topk@EF1,K64 的 FVU 且进入 <0.5x，则固定该 family 后只沿 K 轴做一次补点。","如果 TRUNK_RANK=32 的 FVU 退化过大，则说明该 family 的收益高度依赖 trunk 容量，低开销主战场应回到更短链路的 topk 或新的轻量单库方案。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_factorized_residual 的导出形式稳定为 trunk 静态库 + residual 静态库的有限加权和，属于扩展兼容，可继续保留在兼容 frontier 候选集中。","r210 在 0.69x 处取得 0.1256 FVU，且 tokens_per_sec≈166.6k、总耗时 291s，明显快于近期 topk/soft-codebook 线；因此优先压缩 trunk_rank 比继续增大 K 更符合当前低开销与训练成本双目标。"],"primary_variable":"other_param","self_review":"这轮只改一个主轴 TRUNK_RANK，归因干净，且直接针对 r210 暴露出的成本结构问题。选择 32 而不是 64，是因为 64 大概率仍停留在 >0.5x 边界外；32 才有机会真正补上当前最缺的 <0.5x 前沿，但风险是 trunk 过度压缩后 FVU 可能明显反弹。","summary":"在扩展兼容的 lowrank_factorized_residual 上做一次低开销 param-only 探索：固定 K=64、EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，仅把 TRUNK_RANK 压到 32，目标是在保留 trunk+residual 双库导出形式的同时，把当前 0.69x 候选推进到 <0.5x 区域。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0143.json:7:  "family_name": "factorized_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0143.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 architecture \u7684\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {b_i} \u662f\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5b57\u5178\u5e93\u4e0a\u7684\u56fa\u5b9a\u5411\u91cf\uff0calpha_i \u4e3a\u9009\u51fa\u7684\u7a00\u758f\u7cfb\u6570\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff1b\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u4e0e\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual \u76f8\u6bd4\uff0cfactorized_topk \u4e0d\u518d\u4f7f\u7528 trunk\u3001soft codebook \u6216\u4e24\u9636\u6bb5 refinement\uff0c\u800c\u662f\u7528\u4f4e\u79e9 scorer \u505a\u5355\u5e93\u7a00\u758f\u9009\u62e9\uff0c\u4ecd\u4fdd\u6301\u9759\u6001\u5e93\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\u7684\u90e8\u7f72\u5f62\u5f0f\uff1b\u5728 EF=2 \u4e0b\u5176 encoder selection_cost \u7ea6 0.38x h\u00d7n\uff0c\u663e\u8457\u4f4e\u4e8e\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf\u7684\u7ea6 1.25x\uff0c\u6ee1\u8db3 \u22641.5x \u786c\u7ea6\u675f\uff0c\u90e8\u7f72\u4fa7\u4e5f\u53ea\u9700\u5355\u5e93 sparse lookup\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u56de\u7b54\u4e00\u4e2a matched architecture probe \u95ee\u9898\uff1a\u5728 K=128\u3001EF=2\u3001signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u5b8c\u5168\u4e0d\u53d8\u65f6\uff0c\u8fd9\u79cd\u66f4\u6fc0\u8fdb\u7684\u4f4e\u79e9\u5355\u5e93\u9009\u62e9\u673a\u5236\u662f\u5426\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\uff0c\u8fd8\u662f\u5b83\u5728\u5f53\u524d\u4f4e EF regime \u4e0b\u4f1a\u56e0\u8868\u793a\u80fd\u529b\u4e0d\u8db3\u800c\u660e\u663e\u843d\u540e\u4e8e\u73b0\u6709 soft-codebook/two-stage \u4e3b\u7ebf\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0143.json:20:    "summary": "\u63d2\u5165\u4e00\u4e2a\u4e25\u683c\u5339\u914d\u7684\u67b6\u6784\u63a2\u9488\uff1a\u628a\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual \u6362\u6210\u66f4\u4f4e\u6210\u672c\u3001\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u7684 factorized_topk\uff0c\u5176\u4f59 K=128\u3001EF=2\u3001signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u5168\u90e8\u4fdd\u6301\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u7528\u4e00\u6b21\u5e72\u51c0\u5bf9\u7167\u5224\u65ad\u4f4e\u79e9\u5355\u5e93\u9009\u62e9\u673a\u5236\u5728\u5f53\u524d LUTurbo \u6210\u672c\u7ea6\u675f\u4e0b\u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\u3002",
