research/history/round_summaries/round_0143.json:78:    "description": "\u63d2\u5165\u4e00\u4e2a\u4e25\u683c\u5339\u914d\u7684\u67b6\u6784\u63a2\u9488\uff1a\u628a\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual \u6362\u6210\u66f4\u4f4e\u6210\u672c\u3001\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u7684 factorized_topk\uff0c\u5176\u4f59 K=128\u3001EF=2\u3001signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u5168\u90e8\u4fdd\u6301\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u7528\u4e00\u6b21\u5e72\u51c0\u5bf9\u7167\u5224\u65ad\u4f4e\u79e9\u5355\u5e93\u9009\u62e9\u673a\u5236\u5728\u5f53\u524d LUTurbo \u6210\u672c\u7ea6\u675f\u4e0b\u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0143.json:79:    "self_review": "\u9075\u5b88\u5355\u53d8\u91cf\u539f\u5219\u4e0e\u672c\u8f6e probe \u7ea6\u675f\uff1a\u53ea\u6539 architecture\uff0c\u672a\u8054\u52a8 K\u3001EF\u3001optimizer\u3001LR \u6216\u5176\u4ed6 recipe\u3002\u9009\u62e9 factorized_topk\uff0c\u662f\u56e0\u4e3a\u5b83\u5728 EF=2 \u4e0b selection_cost \u660e\u663e\u4f4e\u4e8e\u5f53\u524d\u6240\u6709\u517c\u5bb9 frontier \u70b9\uff0c\u4e14\u5c5e\u4e8e\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u7684\u5355\u5e93\u9759\u6001\u8868\u793a\uff0c\u80fd\u76f4\u63a5\u56de\u7b54\u201c\u66f4\u6fc0\u8fdb\u7684\u4f4e\u79e9\u5355\u5e93\u9009\u62e9\u673a\u5236\u662f\u5426\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\u201d\u8fd9\u4e00\u72ec\u7acb\u67b6\u6784\u95ee\u9898\u3002\u98ce\u9669\u662f\u8be5 family \u5728\u65e7\u7684\u9ad8 EF regime \u66fe\u660e\u663e\u504f\u5f31\uff0c\u4f46\u5f53\u524d\u4f4e EF \u6210\u672c\u7ea6\u675f\u5df2\u53d1\u751f regime shift\uff0c\u8fd9\u6b63\u662f\u672c\u8f6e probe \u7684\u4fe1\u606f\u4ef7\u503c\u6240\u5728\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:7:  "family_name": "group_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:19:    "hypothesis": "With the `gated` mainline stalled for nine rounds, the highest-value Round 62 matched architecture probe is `group_topk`: it preserves the same static decoder-library weighted-sum export contract and fixed `K=128`, while changing only support formation to a group-local winner scheme that could reduce selection complexity if reconstruction stays competitive. This probe answers one question only: is `group_topk` intrinsically strong enough under the matched `signum`/`2.0e-3`/`EF=12` recipe to merit any later follow-up.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:20:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `group_topk` and keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:23:    "family_name": "group_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:25:    "self_review": "This respects the Round 62 policy: one probe only, one main variable only, and the full mainline recipe stays matched except for architecture. `group_topk` is a better probe than heavier multi-branch variants because it is directly LUTurbo-compatible and has a plausible path to lower online selection cost rather than only improving training-side expressiveness.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:30:        "value": "group_topk"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:51:      "Round 62 uses the single allowed matched architecture probe on `group_topk` rather than expanding the search broadly.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:52:      "`group_topk` remains directly compatible with LUTurbo because reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library; only the encoder-side selection rule changes.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:53:      "The main deployment-relevant reason to test `group_topk` is not just FVU but whether grouped winner selection looks promising enough to justify later work on lower selection overhead under the same decoder contract."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:56:      "If `group_topk` is clearly worse than matched `gated` at `K=128`, discard the family and return to the `gated` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:57:      "If `group_topk` is roughly competitive, record it as a potentially deployment-friendlier selector but still return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:58:      "If `group_topk` unexpectedly beats matched `gated`, schedule at most one later follow-up after the mandated return to the `gated` mainline."
