research/history/round_summaries/round_0152.json:70:    "architecture": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0152.json:79:    "description": "\u6267\u884c\u4e00\u6b21\u4e25\u683c matched architecture probe\uff1a\u628a\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual \u6362\u6210\u6700\u7b80\u5355\u7684 topk\uff0c\u5176\u4f59 K=128\u3001EF=2\u3001signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u5168\u90e8\u4fdd\u6301\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u7528\u4e00\u8f6e\u5e72\u51c0\u5bf9\u7167\u5224\u65ad\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf\u590d\u6742\u7ed3\u6784\u76f8\u5bf9\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u5355\u5e93\u65b9\u6848\u662f\u5426\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0077.json:7:  "family_name": "codebook_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0077.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Rounds 75 and 76 ruled out the simplest matched single-stage alternatives under the current `two_stage_residual` anchor: both `topk` and `jumprelu` were clearly worse at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`. The next single matched architecture probe should therefore test a structurally different exportable decomposition rather than another plain selector. `codebook_topk` is the highest-value remaining yes/no probe because it still maps to a finite weighted sum over static vector libraries, but may reduce LUTurbo online coefficient and lookup cost by reusing a compact static basis instead of a full staged residual path. This round asks one question only: under the exact current mainline recipe, is `codebook_topk` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to remain worth later consideration, or should it be ruled out as clearly inferior to `two_stage_residual`?",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0077.json:20:    "summary": "Use the one allowed matched architecture probe on `codebook_topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the same aux/runtime settings, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `two_stage_residual` to `codebook_topk`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `codebook_topk` stays reasonably close with a healthy curve, keep it in reserve because its shared-codebook structure may lower LUTurbo online lookup and coefficient cost; if it is clearly worse throughout, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0077.json:23:    "family_name": "codebook_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0077.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the Round 77 rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, and the rest of the recipe fixed. `codebook_topk` is a better use of the single probe than revisiting already-rejected plain selector variants because it tests a different cost-quality tradeoff that is still compatible with LUTurbo's static export contract. The main risk is that prior matched probing in an earlier regime already suggested weakness, but this remains the most informative remaining architecture-worthiness check under the current mainline anchor.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0077.json:30:        "value": "codebook_topk"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0077.json:75:      "Round 77 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `codebook_topk` against the current `two_stage_residual` mainline recipe, because it represents a distinct static-library decomposition that may reduce LUTurbo online lookup and coefficient cost while preserving exportability.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0077.json:76:      "Judge this probe as a family-worthiness test only: compare matched `codebook_topk@128` against the `two_stage_residual` reference at fixed `EF=12`, `signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, then return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0077.json:79:      "If matched `codebook_topk` is reasonably close with a healthy curve, return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round but keep one later `codebook_topk` revisit available because its shared-codebook path may be cheaper to deploy.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0077.json:80:      "If matched `codebook_topk` is clearly worse than `two_stage_residual` across the curve, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0077.json:81:      "If matched `codebook_topk` unexpectedly beats the current `two_stage_residual` reference, still return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round per policy, but record `codebook_topk` as a high-priority later follow-up family."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0077.json:92:    "architecture": "codebook_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0077.json:101:    "description": "Use the one allowed matched architecture probe on `codebook_topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the same aux/runtime settings, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `two_stage_residual` to `codebook_topk`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `codebook_topk` stays reasonably close with a healthy curve, keep it in reserve because its shared-codebook structure may lower LUTurbo online lookup and coefficient cost; if it is clearly worse throughout, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0077.json:102:    "self_review": "This obeys the Round 77 rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, and the rest of the recipe fixed. `codebook_topk` is a better use of the single probe than revisiting already-rejected plain selector variants because it tests a different cost-quality tradeoff that is still compatible with LUTurbo's static export contract. The main risk is that prior matched probing in an earlier regime already suggested weakness, but this remains the most informative remaining architecture-worthiness check under the current mainline anchor.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0163.json:25:    "self_review": "\u8fd9\u8f6e\u9075\u5b88\u67b6\u6784\u63a2\u9488\u89c4\u5219\uff0c\u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a\u4e3b\u53d8\u91cf architecture\uff0c\u5e76\u4fdd\u6301\u4e3b\u7ebf\u7684 K\u3001EF\u3001optimizer\u3001LR \u4e0d\u53d8\u3002\u9009\u62e9 gated \u662f\u56e0\u4e3a\u5b83\u662f\u5f53\u524d\u5c1a\u672a\u5728\u8fd9\u4e00\u4e25\u683c matched \u914d\u65b9\u4e0b\u8865\u9f50\u7684\u53ef\u884c\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u5355\u5e93\u5bf9\u7167\uff0c\u80fd\u56de\u7b54\u7b80\u5355\u95e8\u63a7\u662f\u5426\u8db3\u4ee5\u5f25\u8865\u7eaf topk \u8def\u7ebf\u8868\u8fbe\u4e0d\u8db3\u8fd9\u4e00\u5269\u4f59\u95ee\u9898\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0163.json:53:      "r159-r162 \u5df2\u8986\u76d6 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual\u3001lowrank_residual\u3001factorized_topk\u3001topk\uff1b\u672c\u8f6e\u8865\u5145 gated \u8fd9\u4e00\u5269\u4f59\u53ef\u884c\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u4f4e\u6210\u672c\u8def\u7ebf\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0163.json:80:    "self_review": "\u8fd9\u8f6e\u9075\u5b88\u67b6\u6784\u63a2\u9488\u89c4\u5219\uff0c\u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a\u4e3b\u53d8\u91cf architecture\uff0c\u5e76\u4fdd\u6301\u4e3b\u7ebf\u7684 K\u3001EF\u3001optimizer\u3001LR \u4e0d\u53d8\u3002\u9009\u62e9 gated \u662f\u56e0\u4e3a\u5b83\u662f\u5f53\u524d\u5c1a\u672a\u5728\u8fd9\u4e00\u4e25\u683c matched \u914d\u65b9\u4e0b\u8865\u9f50\u7684\u53ef\u884c\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u5355\u5e93\u5bf9\u7167\uff0c\u80fd\u56de\u7b54\u7b80\u5355\u95e8\u63a7\u662f\u5426\u8db3\u4ee5\u5f25\u8865\u7eaf topk \u8def\u7ebf\u8868\u8fbe\u4e0d\u8db3\u8fd9\u4e00\u5269\u4f59\u95ee\u9898\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0201.json:23:    "self_review": "This obeys the one-variable rule and avoids the previously policy-rejected asymmetric candidate. It is the most informative matched probe because it differs from the current mainline by exactly one structural element: the existence of the second residual stage. More distant probes like factorized_topk or lowrank_residual answer broader questions but are less diagnostic for the current mainline family.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0038.json:83:      "If the clean `gated@128` control reproduces the expected anchor with a healthy late curve, resume the K ladder and test `K=32` next to locate where `gated` stops beating `topk`.",
research/history/logs/agent_action_0240.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"K","value":"56"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"frontier_mapping","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；在线侧只做单样本 top-k 选择与系数计算，部署侧仍是单库查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 推理链路，兼容性判断为直接兼容。相对 reference_round=r239 只改一个 env 参数 `K=56`，保持 `ARCHITECTURE=topk`、`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`、`OPTIMIZER=signum`、`LR=0.003`、`AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` 及其余配置不变，测试在约 0.30x-0.31x 总成本处，`topk` 左侧低开销前沿是否继续沿 K 轴平滑改善，把 `K=48` 的 FVU=0.2840 进一步压低，并补出 `K=48 -> K=64` 之间缺失的过渡点。选择这一步而不是直接跳到 `K=64`，是因为 `K=64` 已有旧前沿点，当前更高信息量的问题是左端 Pareto 斜率是否连续、以及 `K=48` 的正信号是否来自真实趋势而不是离散偶然点。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `topk@EF1,K56` 在约 0.30x-0.31x 成本处继续显著优于 `K48`，且 `tokens_per_sec`、`duration_sec`、`final_total_tokens` 没有明显恶化，则相对本轮继续单变量回接到 `K=64` 做一次 clean confirm，巩固左侧前沿。","如果 `K56` 只带来极小改善，则说明左端低成本区的收益主要集中在较粗粒度跃迁上，后续不必再在 `K32-64` 区间做更细密映射。","如果质量改善存在但运行显著更慢，则按运行时优先级将其记为负面系统信号，不把该配方升格为左侧前沿点。"],"notes_to_memory":["r238 和 r239 已连续证明 plain `topk` 而不是 `factorized_topk` 主导 `<0.31x` 左端低成本前沿：`K32` 和 `K48` 都优于现有 `factorized_topk@0.30x`。","r239 从 `K32` 到 `K48` 的 FVU 改善明显，且总时长从 413s 降到 332s，没有出现运行时代价恶化；当前最有信息量的动作是继续沿同一单变量补一个中间点，而不是重新切回已给出负信号的 family。","评估本轮必须同时比较 `val_fvu`、`tokens_per_sec`、`duration_sec`、`final_total_tokens`；若只是小幅质量收益但运行明显更慢，应直接视为负面信号。"],"reference_round":239,"self_review":"该提案严格遵守单变量原则：相对 r239 只改 `K`，不联动 architecture、EF、LR、optimizer、AUXK_ALPHA 或任何新参数。主要风险是 `K56` 可能只是一个被 `K64` 支配的过渡点；但当前 consecutive_no_improve 已归零，最合理的动作是先把左端低成本 frontier 的形状测清，而不是过早切回高不确定性新 family。","summary":"相对 r239 的 `topk@EF1,K48` 做一次严格 param_only 左端补点，仅设置 `K=56`，验证 plain topk 是否继续沿低成本左侧前沿平滑改善，并补出 `K48` 与已有 `K64` 之间的过渡 Pareto 点。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0004.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"topk/signum 在 1e-3 上已经优于 8e-4，说明当前主线仍处于“加大学习率能改善收敛”的区间；本轮只把 LR 小幅上调到 1.2e-3，检验收益是否还能继续延续，还是已经开始进入不稳定区。","summary":"继续围绕 topk 主线推进，不开新 family，不换优化器，不动 K。本轮唯一主变量是学习率：从 1e-3 小幅上调到 1.2e-3，回答“signum+topk 的更优 LR 是否在 1e-3 之上”这个单一问题。","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"这轮仍然严格遵守单变量原则，并延续当前最强主线配方做局部 LR 外推，归因清晰。风险是 1.2e-3 可能开始带来震荡或后段恶化，但这正是当前最该确认的信息；若出现不稳，就有充分依据结束 signum 的 LR 扫描并转向 optimizer 维度。","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.2e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 4 继续只调 LR，基于 r3 的改进结果向 1e-3 以上做小步外推。","当前重点不是只看最终 FVU，而是判断 1.2e-3 的曲线是否仍平滑下降，还是开始出现更大震荡和后段退化。","如果 1.2e-3 不再改善或稳定性变差，可认为 signum 的主线 LR 最优区间已接近 1e-3，下一轮应按顺序切换 optimizer。"],"next_hypotheses":["如果 1.2e-3 继续改善且曲线稳定，下一轮可继续只调 LR 做更细化上探。","如果 1.2e-3 与 1e-3 接近但更不稳，下一轮应结束 signum 的 LR 扫描并只改 optimizer。","如果 1.2e-3 明显更差或震荡增大，说明 signum 的合适 LR 峰值已在 1e-3 附近，下一轮切换 optimizer 更有价值。"],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0233.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: lowrank_factorized_residual\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_r \u03b2_r u_r + \u03a3_i \u03b1_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {u_r} \u662f\u9759\u6001 trunk \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u3001{b_i} \u662f\u9759\u6001 sparse residual \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u5728\u7ebf\u4fa7\u5148\u7528\u4f4e\u79e9 trunk \u5206\u652f\u7ed9\u51fa\u4f4e\u7ef4\u4e3b\u6210\u5206\u91cd\u6784\uff0c\u518d\u5bf9\u5269\u4f59\u6b8b\u5dee\u505a\u6709\u9650\u4e2a\u9759\u6001 residual \u5411\u91cf\u7684\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff1atrunk \u5206\u652f\u4f5c\u4e3a\u4e00\u7ec4\u56fa\u5b9a\u5e93\u9879\u67e5\u8868\u6c42\u548c\uff0cresidual \u5206\u652f\u4f5c\u4e3a\u7b2c\u4e8c\u7ec4\u56fa\u5b9a\u5e93\u9879\u67e5\u8868\u6c42\u548c\uff0c\u6700\u7ec8\u4e24\u652f\u7ebf\u6027\u76f8\u52a0\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u76f8\u5bf9 r210 \u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a env \u53c2\u6570 `K=32`\uff0c\u4fdd\u6301 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_factorized_residual`\u3001`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`\u3001`signum`\u3001`LR=0.003` \u53ca\u5176\u4f59\u914d\u7f6e\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u6d4b\u8bd5\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u628a\u5f53\u524d\u5df2\u9a8c\u8bc1\u53ef\u884c\u7684 `lowrank_factorized_residual@K64` \u4ece\u7ea6 0.69x \u603b\u6210\u672c\u8fdb\u4e00\u6b65\u538b\u5230\u7ea6 0.66x \u5de6\u53f3\uff0c\u540c\u65f6\u4ecd\u663e\u8457\u4f18\u4e8e `<0.5x` \u533a\u57df topk \u524d\u6cbf\u7684 FVU\u3002\u9009\u62e9\u8fd9\u4e00\u6b65\u7684\u539f\u56e0\u662f\uff1ar232 \u5df2\u7ecf\u8bf4\u660e\u7ee7\u7eed\u4e0a\u63a2 `JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD` \u53ea\u5e26\u6765\u66f4\u5dee FVU \u4e0e\u66f4\u957f\u65f6\u957f\uff0c\u9608\u503c\u521d\u59cb\u5316\u7ebf\u5e94\u5f53\u5173\u95ed\uff1b\u800c\u5f53\u524d\u5269\u4f59\u4f4e\u6210\u672c\u65b0 family \u4e2d\uff0c`factorized_topk`\u3001`group_topk` \u5df2\u88ab\u8bc1\u4f2a\uff0c`adaptive_budget_topk` \u5728 batch_size=1 \u4e0b\u9000\u5316\u4e3a\u666e\u901a topk\uff0c`gated/routed/whitened/codebook/two_stage` \u4e0e\u5927\u591a\u6570\u4f4e\u79e9\u6b8b\u5dee\u53d8\u4f53\u5728 EF=1 \u4e0b\u90fd\u8d85\u9884\u7b97\u3002\u6b64\u65f6\u6700\u6709\u4ef7\u503c\u7684\u52a8\u4f5c\u4e0d\u662f\u518d\u505a\u4e00\u4e2a\u9ad8\u6982\u7387\u65e0\u6548\u7684\u65b0 family probe\uff0c\u800c\u662f\u628a\u552f\u4e00\u4ecd\u53ef\u884c\u3001\u4e14\u8d28\u91cf\u660e\u663e\u4f18\u4e8e plain topk \u7684\u4f4e\u79e9\u6b8b\u5dee\u4e3b\u7ebf\u6cbf K \u8f74\u5411\u4f4e\u5f00\u9500\u65b9\u5411\u62c9\u8fd1\uff0c\u8865\u4e00\u679a 0.5x-0.7x \u8fc7\u6e21\u951a\u70b9\u3002",
