research/history/logs/agent_action_0019.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 18 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=16` still maintained a negative late-phase FVU slope instead of fully stalling, even though dead-feature pressure rose sharply. This round changes only `K`, moving from `16` to `8`, to answer whether the current export-compatible topk recipe can still support one more major cost reduction before reconstruction quality and compensation burden become clearly impractical.","summary":"Continue the active topk low-K boundary search: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `K` from `16` to `8` to test whether the practical LUTurbo cost-quality frontier extends below `K=16`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `topk` family, changes exactly one primary variable (`k`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule and allowed-K set, and follows directly from the observed `K=16` curve shape. The main risk is that `K=8` may push the recipe past the useful regime, but `K=16` still improved through the end rather than hard-plateauing, so the next clean question is whether the true boundary sits at `K=8` or between `8` and `16`.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"8"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 18 (`K=16`) reached `FVU=0.3084372282028198`; the late-phase slope remained negative, so training was still improving rather than collapsing early.","At `K=16`, `dead_pct` and `auxk` rose sharply in the late phase, indicating meaningful capacity stress and likely growing reliance on online compensation if K is reduced further.","For LUTurbo, probing `K=8` is now the most informative single-variable action because it directly tests whether the current topk recipe still offers a viable lower-cost deployment point or whether `K=16` is already near the practical floor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=8` is still usable, run `K=4` to locate the hard lower bound of the current topk/signum regime.","If `K=8` degrades sharply or the late curve nearly flatlines, treat `K=16` as the current practical low-K boundary for this recipe.","If `K=8` is borderline, compare it against `K=16` as a deployment tradeoff point rather than against the K128 anchor alone."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0012.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 11 improved over the current frontier at `signum@1.7e-3`, which suggests the useful learning-rate region extends beyond `1.6e-3` and that the `1.8e-3` failure may have skipped past a narrow optimum. This round changes only `LR`, moving to `1.75e-3` while keeping `topk/signum/K128/EF12` fixed, to test whether there is a local peak between `1.7e-3` and `1.8e-3` with better final FVU and acceptable curve stability.","summary":"Continue the topk mainline with one more narrow signum LR refinement: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `K=128`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and raise `LR` from `1.7e-3` to `1.75e-3` to answer whether the best stable point sits between the successful `1.7e-3` run and the degraded `1.8e-3` run.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active topk family and changes only the learning-rate axis, which matches the current validator and the round policy. The main risk is that `1.75e-3` may already be too close to the instability boundary seen at `1.8e-3`, but that is exactly the single question this round is meant to resolve.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.75e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 11 indicates the signum optimum was not exhausted at `1.6e-3`; there is still credible headroom just below the failed `1.8e-3` point.","This round performs a narrow interpolation test at `1.75e-3` rather than a broad sweep, preserving clean attribution on the LR axis.","Evaluate the run by curve shape as well as terminal FVU: a better late descent without amplified oscillation would support adopting a higher-LR mainline anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `signum@1.75e-3` improves again and remains smooth, promote it as the new mainline anchor before touching other recipe dimensions.","If `signum@1.75e-3` matches `1.7e-3` but is less stable, keep `1.7e-3` as the practical optimum.","If `signum@1.75e-3` regresses toward the `1.8e-3` behavior, conclude the stable peak is around `1.7e-3` and stop LR refinement."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0088.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `lowrank_residual_vq`, `lowrank_jumprelu_residual`, and `lowrank_gated_residual` all failed to pressure the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, the most informative remaining matched architecture probe is `lowrank_grouped_residual`. It preserves the same low-rank trunk and static-vector export contract, but replaces full global residual selection with group-local winner selection, which is directly relevant to lowering LUTurbo's online selection cost while keeping the reconstruction as a finite weighted sum over a static library. If this grouped selector is still clearly weaker under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then grouped single-stage low-rank selection is not worth continuing in the current regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_grouped_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the round policy by changing exactly one primary variable: `architecture`. The mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe remains fixed, and I am not coupling this with any extra `group_topk_size` change. `lowrank_grouped_residual` is a better LUTurbo-aligned probe than heavier soft-codebook or multi-branch variants because its grouped local competition could reduce online selection work rather than increase it. The risk is that constraining support selection to per-group winners may lose too much quality at K128 and simply confirm that the two-stage residual path is necessary.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 88 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_grouped_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for grouped local winner selection under the low-rank trunk; the question is whether cheaper support selection can stay close enough to the mainline quality to merit future consideration.","Do not open another new family next round; return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline after this probe regardless of outcome."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, discard it and resume mainline tuning on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` next round.","If `lowrank_grouped_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a viable lower-selection-cost branch but still return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
