research/history/logs/agent_action_0221.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"32"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r β_r u_r + Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {u_r} 是静态 trunk 向量库、{b_i} 是静态 residual 向量库；在线侧只计算 β_r 与 α_i，再执行 trunk 查表 + residual 查表 + 加权求和，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路，兼容性判断为扩展兼容。r220 的 blocker 不是质量，而是 TRUNK_RANK override 没有真正进入训练配置；当前执行链已具备 `TRUNK_RANK -> --trunk_rank -> sae.trunk_rank` 路径，因此本轮应严格锚定有效参考轮 r210，只改一个 env 参数 `TRUNK_RANK=32`，先验证 `research/history/logs/round*.config.json` 与 checkpoint `config.json` 都记录 `sae.trunk_rank=32`，再判断该 family 是否能以预估 total_cost≈0.36x 保持显著优于 <0.5x 区域 topk 前沿的 FVU，同时保住其更高吞吐/更短总时长。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果配置审计通过且 `TRUNK_RANK=32` 仍明显优于 `topk@0.38x` 的 FVU=0.1968，并且吞吐接近 r210 的 166.6k tokens/s，则下一轮继续相对本轮单变量下探 `TRUNK_RANK=16`，寻找更低成本拐点。","如果配置审计通过但 `TRUNK_RANK=32` 的 FVU 退化过大，则仍保留这轮作为有效成本点，下一轮在同 family 内回退到更温和的 `TRUNK_RANK=64` 做单变量 bracket，而不是立即切去新 family。","如果这轮再次出现 `TRUNK_RANK` 未进入 runtime/checkpoint config，则停止解读任何 FVU，直接转入接线修复验证轮。"],"notes_to_memory":["r220 无效的根因是参数接线而非架构质量；下一轮必须把“参数确实进入 runtime_config 与 checkpoint config”作为第一判据。","本地 `selection_cost_estimate()` 显示 `lowrank_factorized_residual@K64,EF1,TRUNK_RANK=32` 的 combined_ratio 约为 0.36x，显著低于 r210 的 0.69x，也低于当前 `topk@K248,EF1` 的 0.49x。","若该点质量接近 r210 的 FVU=0.1256，同时维持其约 166.6k tokens/s、291s 级别的训练代价，则会成为 <0.5x 区域比 topk 更强的高价值 Pareto 点。"],"reference_round":210,"self_review":"这轮继续遵守单变量原则：相对有效 reference r210 只改 `TRUNK_RANK`，不重复把 `ARCHITECTURE/K/EF/LR` 写进 patch，也不使用已经被审计标记无效的 r220 作为锚点。选择复跑 `TRUNK_RANK=32` 而不是直接去 `16`，是因为当前最高优先级是先消除变量隔离失效这个 blocker，并拿到第一条真实有效的低 trunk-rank 证据；在审计通过之前，不应把结果当成架构结论。","summary":"复跑 r220 的科学问题，但按合法 `param_only` 形式严格锚定有效参考轮 r210，仅下发 `TRUNK_RANK=32`。本轮先做参数生效确认，再评估 lowrank_factorized_residual 是否能以约 0.36x total_cost 进入 <0.5x Pareto 主前沿。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0210.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_factorized_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r beta_r u_r + Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 u_r 是静态 trunk 向量库，b_i 是静态 residual 向量库；在线侧只计算系数 beta_r 与 alpha_i，并在 LUTurbo/Lottable 端导出为两个静态向量库上的有限加权和，因此属于扩展兼容。r209 对 topk@EF1,K96 的继续加大查表预算被 policy 拦截，说明单纯沿 topk 的 K 轴上探不稳；本轮保持 K=64、EF=1、optimizer、LR 不变，只把 architecture 从 topk 切到 lowrank_factorized_residual，测试在仍瞄准 <0.5x 区域的前提下，加入极轻 low-rank trunk 与 factorized residual scorer 后，是否能显著优于 topk@0.31x 的 FVU。按现有成本表外推，该配置有希望落在低开销区或其边界附近，同时提供比纯单库 topk 更强的表达。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 lowrank_factorized_residual@EF1,K64 成功落入 <0.5x 且明显优于 topk@EF1,K64，则下一步固定该 family，单变量扫描 K 或 TRUNK_RANK，补齐低开销前沿。","如果该配置仍超出 <0.5x 或 FVU 改善有限，则说明低开销区需要更短链路而非增加 trunk 分支，下一步应回到 topk/factorized_topk 或探索更小静态库方案。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_factorized_residual 的导出形式是 trunk 静态库加 residual 静态库的有限加权和，满足 LUTurbo 扩展兼容约束。","本轮只改 architecture，保持 K=64 和 EF=1 不变，便于判断在同等低字典规模与相近 lookup 预算下，增加轻 trunk 是否值得。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"该提案遵守单变量原则，并直接回应 r209 的 policy_reject：不再继续沿 topk 的 K 轴加预算，而是测试更有信息量的新低成本 family。主要风险是 deployment 侧 trunk 成本可能把 total_cost 推到 0.5x 附近甚至略上，但这仍能为低开销区提供关键边界信号。","summary":"切换到扩展兼容的 lowrank_factorized_residual，固定 K=64、EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，只改变 architecture，验证轻量 trunk+residual 结构能否在低开销区附近拿到明显优于 topk 的 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0013.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `signum` learning-rate sweep has now mapped a narrow optimum region around `1.7e-3` to `1.75e-3`, with no clear additional gain from pushing LR higher. This round changes only the loss-shaping axis by lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` from the current implicit baseline `0.03125` to `0.015625` while keeping `topk/signum/K128/EF12/LR=1.7e-3` fixed, to test whether a weaker auxiliary dead-feature pressure improves late-stage reconstruction once the main LR regime is already near its peak.","summary":"Stay on the `topk` mainline and move to the next recipe axis after LR refinement: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=1.7e-3` fixed, and reduce `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.015625` to answer whether lighter auxiliary regularization yields a better training curve and lower final FVU.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the active family unchanged and modifies only one non-core recipe variable, which fits the single-variable rule and avoids the optimizer-callback policy trap encountered earlier. The risk is that lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` may weaken dead-feature management and hurt utilization, but at this stage the more important question is whether the current LR-tuned regime is now over-regularized in reconstruction terms.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.7e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.015625"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The signum LR sweep suggests the practical optimum is near `1.7e-3`; pushing to `1.75e-3` did not yield a meaningful additional gain.","With LR mostly mapped, the next clean single-variable question is whether current loss shaping is slightly over-constraining reconstruction.","Judge this round by full curve shape plus terminal FVU: if lower `AUXK_ALPHA` improves late descent without obvious instability, the mainline recipe should shift on the loss axis rather than continuing micro-LR sweeps."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.015625` improves FVU and keeps the curve smooth, continue tuning aux loss strength within the same topk recipe.","If the lower aux weight hurts stability or feature health without improving reconstruction, revert to `0.03125` and treat LR-tuned signum as the current clean anchor.","If the effect is neutral, the topk mainline may be recipe-saturated at K=128 and the next useful step will be a K move once policy order permits."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0060.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 59 ruled out `factorized_topk` as a strong matched alternative under the current `gated` recipe: at `0.229180` it was clearly too weak, so the next single architecture question should move to a different export-compatible support-formation mechanism rather than another heavier scoring path. `jumprelu` preserves LUTurbo's static-vector finite weighted-sum reconstruction contract while replacing the learned input-conditioned gate with per-latent thresholding, so this round asks one clean yes/no question: under the exact current mainline recipe (`K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`), is `jumprelu` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to justify any later follow-up as a potentially cheaper deployment family?","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `jumprelu`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `jumprelu`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `jumprelu` stays smooth and remains reasonably close to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because its thresholded support path may reduce LUTurbo online selection overhead versus a full gating branch; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 60 matched-probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, and the settled mainline recipe fixed. `jumprelu` is a sensible LUTurbo-oriented probe because it preserves the same static library weighted-sum output form while simplifying support shaping relative to `gated`; the main risk is that the matched `gated`-tuned recipe may not be ideal for its threshold dynamics, but that is acceptable for a family-worthiness screen.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 59 showed that matched `factorized_topk` is not promising under the strengthened mainline recipe: its `0.229180` endpoint is far from the `gated@128` anchor, so that family should not be prioritized for LUTurbo-oriented follow-up.","`jumprelu` remains LUTurbo-compatible because the reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architectural change is confined to threshold-based support shaping before top-k selection.","Round 60 should judge `jumprelu` purely as a family-worthiness probe against the current `gated@128` anchor: if it is clearly worse or unstable, archive it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, keep exactly one later follow-up slot available."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `jumprelu` is clearly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round and close this probe.","If matched `jumprelu` is roughly competitive with a healthy curve, still return to the `gated` mainline next round, but preserve one later revisit because its thresholded support path may better align with LUTurbo online-cost goals.","If matched `jumprelu` unexpectedly beats the current `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy but schedule exactly one later follow-up for this family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
